(5209,'Continued Fuel for the Fire','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I need to gather some Cobalt Chiori to help feed the New Combine troops at the Salt Breeze encampment.',0,'I\'ve given Amli the Cobalt Chiori that he needs. This should get those New Combine soldiers plenty amped up!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5210,'Becoming a Crafter','Timorous Deep','Timorous Deep',1,3,'I should visit Rozokal Niba\'mok in Gorowyn to learn how to harvest and craft objects.',2630133,'I have spoken with Rozokal Niba\'mok.','Quests/TimorousDeep/BecomingACrafter.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5211,'The Search for Ariana','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',15,9,'I met Orwen Neovra at a nomad camp in the Commonlands. His wife Ariana was captured by orcs, and taken into the Wailing Caves. I told him I would look for her while he worked on a weapon for his own journey into the caves.',330137,'I found Ariana in a cell in the Wailing Caves. She sacrificed her life for the rest of her people, and agreed to stay with the orcs, halting an attack on their camp. She wanted Orwen to move on so as not to hurt himself and rekindle the orcs\' threat. She gave me a necklace to give to Orwen to convince him that she wasn\'t alive. Orwen accepted the news and gave me the stiletto he made.','Quests/Commonlands/TheSearchForAriana',0,1,0,0,0),
(5212,'Far Seas Requisition - WC 124','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',330260,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/Commonlands/FarSeasRequisitionWC124',0,1,0,0,0),
(5213,'Far Seas Requisition - WC 002','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',330260,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/Commonlands/FarSeasRequisitionWC002.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5214,'Far Seas Requisition - WC 154','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',330260,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/Commonlands/FarSeasRequisitionWC154.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5215,'Far Seas Requisition - WC 077','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',330260,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/Commonlands/FarSeasRequisitionWC077.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5216,'Far Seas Requisition - WC 045','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',330260,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/Commonlands/FarSeasRequisitionWC045.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5217,'A Strange Stone Wedge','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',18,1,'I\'ve found a dull chipped hatchet head and while normally such things would be thrown away quickly this may prove to be useful once remade.',0,'I finished remaking Chickenbane.','Quests/Commonlands/AStrangeStoneWedge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5218,'Bloodskull Orc Bounty   ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',14,1,'I found a bounty issued by the Freeport Militia calling for able citizens to aid in the resistance against the Bloodskull threat. The bounty promises a generous reward to those who give a lot of twenty Bloodskull earrings to Captain Vrondell as proof of their contribution.',5590132,'I found a bounty issued by the Freeport Militia calling for able citizens to aid in the resistance against the orcish threat. I acquired ten Bloodskull earrings, quite blood stained, and brought them to Captain Vrondell. I was awarded for my contribution to the cause.','Quests/Commonlands/BloodskullOrcBounty.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5219,'Quell The Undead','Wailing Caves','Wailing Caves',13,1,'I\'ve spoken recently with Ronam Olansk, the leader of a nomad band just south of the Wailing Caves. I\'ve sold my services to drive back the undead that infest the caverns in the hope that the menace will lessen.',330215,'I drove back the undead to protect the nomads, though I feel they shall soon return. Those souls shall never rest for long, I fear. Ronam Olansk kept to his word and rewarded me for my effort, though I believe they may be in vain should he not relocate his people.','Quests/WailingCaves/quell_the_undead.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5220,'That Cheating Gnome!','Oakmyst Forest','Oakmyst Forest',6,0,'Jorn Sorefoot is searching for a gnome named Fluwkowir Haggleton who cheated in a game of cards and then fled to the Oakmyst Forest. Jorn last saw him heading toward the docks on the western end of Oakmyst Forest. Jorn wants revenge, but more than that he needs his money to pay his rent. Should I need to leave Oakmyst Forest, I may return via any mariner bell within the City of Qeynos.',1950012,'I found Fluwkowir. After confronting him he attacked me. On him he had a small satchel, in that satchel I found Jorn\'s money but also some strange notes written in Lucanic.','Quests/OakmystForest/that_cheating_gnome.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5221,'Returning to Captain Feralis','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',18,1,'Tecera has thanked me for her help and suggested I return to Captain Feralis who will want to reward me.',330199,'Captain Feralis thanked me for the help I provided and gave me a reward.','Quests/TheCommonlands/ReturningToCaptainFeralisFinal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5222,'Quenching Their Thirst','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',12,1,'Madam Vi wants me to fill three flasks with water from a nearby freshwater lake, a river to the north, and from the sea to the northeast.',330179,'I filled the three flasks for Madam Vi.','Quests/TheCommonlands/QuenchingTheirThirst.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5223,'Far From Home','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',16,1,'Madam Vi wants me to take water flasks to her parched comrades. I should look for a camp of nomads to the northwest.',330179,'I located Madam Vi\'s lost entourage and gave them the water flasks.','Quests/TheCommonlands/FarFromHome.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5224,'No Risk, No Reward','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',16,1,'Madam Vi wants me to find a gem for her inside the Wailing Caves. I should look for a clump of stone near the vibrant blue rocks at the mouth of the caves.',330179,'I brought the clump of stone to Madam Vi at the Crossroads.','Quests/TheCommonlands/NoRiskNoReward.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5225,'Seer Stone','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',19,1,'Madam Vi wants some final components that she can use to create her Seer Stone.',330179,'I collected all of the components for Madam Vi\'s Seer Stone.','Quests/TheCommonlands/SeerStone.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5226,'Do or Die, Says Irizan ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'Given no choice, I must aid the Inquisitor of Freeport. I\'m to get my assignment from a merchant at the Crossroads by the name of Edmond. I have no idea what lies in store for me, but I feel that I better do what Irizan tells me to.',330177,'I was merely a pawn in a spy game on an individual who claims to be from Qeynos. I have no idea what is really going on; it would be best for me to stay clear of this lot. Though he promised to give me something, all I got were a few coins. I\'m steering clear of this group from now on; they don\'t seem very trustworthy.','Quests/TheCommonlands/DoOrDieSaysIrizian.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5227,'Narin Heirloom','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,9,'V\'tal Narin is going to pay me to search for her brother in Fallen Gate and return with information about the heirloom he was looking for.',330173,'V\'tal Narin\'s brother was dead, but I found the box and returned it to her.','Quests/TheCommonlands/NarinHeirloom.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5228,'In His Name','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',10,1,'I have been asked to report to Gerun Pontian at the gates to the City of Freeport in the Commonlands. It would seem my service is requested in the Commonlands.',330014,'I have found Gerun Pontian. He is interested in providing work for me while I am in the Commonlands.','Quests/TheCommonlands/InHisName.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5229,'Components for Gimble','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',13,9,'While traveling north of the crossroads, I ran into an odd little gnome named Gimble Cognoggin. He required some items from the Wailing Caves to make some sort of potion or spell. He wasn\'t very specific about it. But he promised to pay me for my effort, so I took the job.',330187,'Having delved deeply into the Wailing Caves, I can now say that goo is disgusting! That place is filled with slime and skeletons. But I did see something that piqued my interest. There were a couple of live orcs in that cave of a clan named the Ree. I wonder what they\'re doing there.','Quests/TheCommonlands/ComponentsForGimble.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5230,'The Wheel of Vaniki','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I met a surveyor who asked me to help the roekillik recover a talisman of some sort, the Wheel of Vaniki. Apparently they have tracked it to a camp in the Commonlands but due to some past disagreements with the camp\'s residents, the roekillik cannot get the Wheel back. I\'ll check out the camp and recover their Wheel.',330133,'After doing a bit of leg work, I restored the Wheel of Vaniki. Turns out it\'s not a mystical ancient artifact as I thought, but a huge wheel of cheese! Even though the roekillik and I didn\'t exactly see eye-to-eye on things, at least they paid me for my efforts.','Quests/TheCommonlands/TheWheelOfVaniki.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5231,'An Abandoned Boat','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',11,1,'There is a nice little boat near a pond, but the fishing hole is completely ruined by stinking carrion hounds that like to lurk nearby. They shouldn\'t be too terribly difficult to take out.',0,'I have destroyed quite a few of the carrion hounds.','Quests/TheCommonlands/an_abandoned_boat.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5232,'An Engraved Stump','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',15,1,'The stump claims ten kerran rogues slain. I can beat that easily! I will slay TWELVE kerran rogues in the Commonlands! Rumor has it their hideout is a village southwest of the Crossroads, across the river.',0,'Hah! I have slain twelve kerran rogues, who can top that?!','Quests/TheCommonlands/an_engraved_stump.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5233,'Stop the Bloodskull Lumberjacks','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',14,1,'There seems to be some crazy upsurgence of Bloodskull lumberjacks in the area, not that there is very much wood for them to cut down. I shouldn\'t allow them to get the wood, they may use it for weapons or armor.',0,'I have destroyed quite a few of the Bloodskull lumberjacks.','Quests/TheCommonlands/stop_the_bloodskull_lumberjacks.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5234,'The Secret Valley','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',15,1,'It seems there may be an outside presence in a nearby valley. Apparently Merchant Marcus in The Commonlands may have more information on the situation.',0,'Now that I have the Potion of Earthwalking I should be able to enter the Valley of the Rogue Magi.','Quests/TheCommonlands/the_secret_valley.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5235,'Grum\'s Inspiring Axe','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',18,1,'I have found the legendary axe of Grum the Giant Slayer. While I cannot take the axe for my own, I can make my own fortune becoming a giant slayer myself. I must kill the sandstone giants and prove myself!',0,'I have slain the sandstone giants, but there are no parades or crowds cheering me on. Perhaps being a giant slayer wasn\'t as glamorous as I thought it would be.','Quests/TheCommonlands/grums_inspiring_axe.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5236,'Completing a Coward\'s Job','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',12,1,'I found a discarded decree from the Overlord that some coward must have hidden, obviously too scared to do his duty. I shall carry out this task myself, and slay the Bloodskull warriors in the Commonlands.',0,'I have slain twenty five Bloodskulls to fulfill the Overlord\'s decree.','Quests/TheCommonlands/completing_a_cowards_job.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5237,'The Plunder of Gunthak','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',14,1,'I found a barrel amongst some shipwreckage that appeared to be untouched by nature\'s fury. Opening it I found items once bound for Freeport that had been acquired by Gunthak pirates. If this kind of treasure is still around, I wonder what else they might have.',0,'I have found the pirates. From their corpses, I treated myself to some of their booty.','Quests/TheCommonlands/the_plunder_of_gunthak.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5238,'The Giggling Orc','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',13,1,'In between these stones, I have found a parchment. It seems this is a wanted poster with a picture of a smiling orc.',0,'The giggling orc has been found and put to rest!','Quests/TheCommonlands/the_giggling_orc.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5239,'Valley of the Rogue Magi ','Access Quest','The Commonlands',20,1,'Now that I consumed this potion I will be able to pass through the rockpile, allowing me to enter the Valley of the Rogue Magi.',0,'I have discovered the secrets of the Valley of the Rogue Magi.','Quests/TheCommonlands/valley_of_the_rogue_magi_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5240,'Far Seas Requisition - FG 016','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',23,9,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order, I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/TheCommonlands/far_seas_requisition__fg_016.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5241,'Far Seas Requisition - FG 073','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order, I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in The Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/TheCommonlands/far_seas_requisition__fg_073.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5242,'Far Seas Requisition - FG 158 ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order, I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/TheCommonlands/far_seas_requisition__fg_158_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5243,'Far Seas Requisition - FG 212','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order, I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/TheCommonlands/far_seas_requisition__fg_212.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5244,'Far Seas Requisition - FG 244','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have discovered a Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. It looks like this order was placed by Taskmaster Kozma in The Commonlands. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order, I can deliver the order to the Taskmaster for a reward.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the Taskmaster at the crossroads in the Commonlands. I have been paid in full for this work.','Quests/TheCommonlands/far_seas_requisition__fg_244.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5245,'An Order of Orc Tongue   ','Language','Multiple Zones',1,1,'I have discovered a requisition for seized goods between the orcs and smugglers. The order is written in both Norrathian and orc. I can learn the orc language if I had other orders to study.',0,'I have studied a great amount of orc smuggler requisitions written in both Norrathian and orc. I now understand the language, Orcish.','Quests/MultipleZones/an_order_of_orc_tongue_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5246,'A Ring\'s Calling','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',17,1,'I have found a brilliant gold ring. Upon placing the ring upon my finger I was overtaken by a powerful vision of a paladin falling to his death atop the tower of a castle\'s ruins. I am driven to visit these ruins. I feel I must face the souls of my vision.',0,'After finding a brilliant gold ring I was drawn to the ruins of an ancient castle, Val\'marr. There I brought this ring that somehow caused an ancient spirit to awaken. I was forced to battle undead crusaders. I feel as though I have released their souls now.','Quests/TheCommonlands/a_rings_calling.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5247,'The Training Grounds','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',19,1,'While adventuring in the Commonlands, I found a broken harness similar to the ones used by the Bloodskull Orcs to ride their war elephants. Despite being broken this harness is quite new, which means that the Bloodskull Orcs are breeding elephants once more for another assault on Freeport. It\'s doubtful that the Orcs there will be low in numbers, so it is best that I gather some other friends or adventurers first before making my way to Bloodskull Valley in the Southeastern Commonlands.',0,'I\'ve made the journey to the elephant training grounds.','Quests/TheCommonlands/the_training_grounds.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5248,'A Tour of the Commonlands ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I have acquired a book titled \'Bootstrutter\'s Field Guide to the Commonlands\'. It appears to detail numerous points of interest within the region of the Commonlands. I have decided to visit each location beginning with the first page and following in succession.',0,'I visited all the locations listed in \'Bootstrutter\'s Field Guide to the Commonlands\', having done so I decided to return the book to Freeport\'s Academy of Arcane Science, keeper of all knowledge. The Tome Warden was delighted and rewarded me with a valuable piece of Bootstrutter Gear.','Quests/TheCommonlands/a_tour_of_the_commonlands_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5249,'Lion Mane Helm','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',15,1,'I\'ve found a helmet that looks like it was hammered out but then neglected before it was completed. I think that I can probably turn this unfinished helmet into something a little better than what it is now.',0,'Through much effort, I\'ve been able to turn the unfinished helmet into to a nice Lion Mane Helm.','Quests/TheCommonlands/lion_mane_helm.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5250,'Elephant Hide Boots  ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',18,1,'I\'ve found a pair of holey boots that looked like they were worthless. Upon closer inspection, it might be possible to repair these durable shoes.',0,'Through much work, I\'ve been able to repair these boots. They\'re now a nice set of Elephant Hide Boots.','Quests/TheCommonlands/elephant_hide_boots_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5251,'An Eroded Key','Access Quest','The Commonlands',15,1,'A fallen blackguard was sent on a mission to scout a Bloodskull messenger. When discovered he was defeated in battle and left for dead by the orc. He believes that the messenger was carrying something of importance.',330069,'I\'ve completed this quest.','Quests/TheCommonlands/an_eroded_key.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5252,'Key to Fallen Gate','Access Quest','City of Freeport',18,1,'Kanos X\'aphon has tasked me to track down a key to a place called the Fallen Gate. He claims the gate is the entrance to the ancient home of the dark elves, a city called Neriak. If he is correct, there could be untold riches buried in the long-dead city.',5590592,'After slaying every Thexian in the building, I managed to get both a key for myself and Kanos. He certainly took his time in getting to the meeting, that\'s for certain. He\'s covered up the mess, but only at the cost of enlisting my services at an unnamed point in the future.','Quests/CityofFreeport/key_to_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5253,'Help the Troll Get Ahead  ','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',30,1,'A troll I met in the Commonlands has offered to pay me for giant-hunting services. I felt rather badly for the poor thing. He\'d been removed from his clan for not being smart enough apparently. At any rate, I\'m to go to the Nektulos forest, and bring back the head of a Nightfall giant.',330219,'Sadly, I had to put Kregnok Legbreaker down after I returned the head to him. Apparently he felt proving himself meant he needed to kill me too. Smart plan for a troll though... hey... maybe... no... it couldn\'t be... could his request have been to trick someone into killing a giant for him?','Quests/TheCommonlands/help_the_troll_get_ahead_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5254,'An Orcish Trinket','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',20,1,'I found an interesting orc object in a chest. I should find someone who knows about orcs and see if they can tell me anything about the object.',0,'I found all the pieces of Raegnir\'s blade and returned them to him. I also told Raegnir the true story of what happened when he died. He thanked me for both the blade and the truth.','Quests/TheCommonlands/an_orcish_trinket.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5255,'The Traveler\'s Three Meanings of Life   ','Nektulos Forest','Nektulos Forest',28,1,'I met the Traveling Augur at Port Naythex in Nektulos. He wants me to learn three of the meanings of life, apparently whether I want to learn them or not. It might be interesting, if nothing else.',1790046,'Like all mystical ventures, I\'m supposed to draw my own conclusions as to what I\'ve learned about the meanings of life. I believe that being alive beats the alternative, but the Traveling Augur probably has something else in mind. At least he paid me for my time.','Quests/NektulosForest/the_travelers_three_meanings_of_life_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5256,'Prove Yourself','Nektulos Forest','Nektulos Forest',21,1,'Bruhn K\'Viir of the Order of Nektulos has asked me to take supplies to the two scout camps along the beach, and one out past the path leading out into the forest.',1790260,'I resupplied the scouts at all of the camps. They then promptly ambushed me, and I promptly disposed of them.','Quests/NektulosForest/prove_yourself.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5257,'Lore and Legend: Orc  ','Lore and Legend','Multiple Zones',1,1,'I am searching for orc body parts in order to gain knowledge about their kind.',0,'I have learned the secrets of the orc.','Quests/MultipleZones/lore_and_legend_orc_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5258,'Trust Must Be Earned, Part 1','Nektulos Forest','Nektulos Forest',22,1,'Bruhn K\'Viir of the Order of Nektulos has tasked me with retrieving the Nerius Pirate attack plans from the tent of the Tactician.',1790260,'I have retrieved the plans and taken them to Bruhn K\'Viir.','Quests/NektulosForest/trust_must_be_earned_part_1.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5259,'Trust Must Be Earned, Part 2','Nektulos Forest','Nektulos Forest',22,1,'After examining the Nerius Pirate attack plans, Bruhn K\'Viir has decided that the Nerius Commander and Tactician must be killed. I have been given this task.',1790260,'I have killed the Nerius Commander and Tactician for Bruhn K\'Viir.','Quests/NektulosForest/trust_must_be_earned_part_2.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5260,'Balancing the Gangs  ','The Sprawl','The Sprawl',8,1,'I found a note on a Guttersnipe crook that seems to be meant for a member of the Black Magi Ratongas. It seems from the look of it that the dervish wanted an ally against the biggest gang in the Sprawl, the Giantslayers. I think I\'ll help even the sides a little.',0,'I finished roughing up the Giantslayers. That should shift the power balance a little more to even around here.','Quests/TheSprawl/balancing_the_gangs_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5261,'Reward For A Missing Music Box   ','The Ruins','The Ruins',8,1,'I found a musicbox among a ratonga\'s belongings after I dispatched him. The box had the name of Lucilla Quietus on it. Maybe if I find this person I can get a reward for returning the music box. I hope it turns out to be a precious family heirloom.',0,'I found Lucilla and demanded a reward for the return of her stolen music box. She finally consented to pay and I gave her the music box. I wish I would have checked out the music box more thoroughly...','Quests/TheRuins/reward_for_a_missing_music_box_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5262,'An Axe\'s Revenge  ','The Ruins','The Ruins',15,1,'I found an axe among the remains of an orc I had slain. After inspecting it and looking over the orc letters carved into the handle I feel an irresistible urge to exact revenge upon the orcs.',0,'I had to kill six orcs before the urge left me. The axe now rests quietly with me.','Quests/TheRuins/an_axes_revenge_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5263,'Bring Out Your Souls','Scale Yard','Scale Yard',8,1,'Zekvila Dizelk has given me instructions to kill the undead. As they are laid to rest, I am to hold out this crystal and it will supposedly absorb their spirits. Let\'s hope this works.',1390128,'Zekvila was pleased with the crystal. She claims that it will help her topple her rival\'s rule. I think I may ask her later if she needs any more help, in case she actually is successful.','Quests/Graveyard/bring_out_your_souls.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5264,'Darkblades and Dirty Rats','Thieves Way','Thieves Way',9,1,'I found a very small ratonga hiding out while I was in the Thieves\' Sewer. It seems that she was the lone survivor of a Darkblade death squad\'s assault. In return for killing the Darkblade Brigands in Thieves\' Way, she\'ll tell me the location of their secret lair filled with riches.',1540001,'I had a feeling something wasn\'t on the up and up with that little ratonga. It turns out she wanted me to kill off the Darkblades and recover the key to their secret den so she could plunder without interruptions. I wasn\'t amused by her scheming; I had to kill her. Now the den is open for me to plunder.','Quests/ThievesWay/darkblades_and_dirty_rats.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5265,'Fresh Samples','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',17,1,'I came across a gnome in the serpent sewer by the name of Marcus Puer. He\'s working on potions which contain key elements from fresh samples from the creatures down here in these sewers. I have offered to aid him by recovering the samples from the creatures that he needs while he continues his research.',1550056,'I\'ve returned to Marcus and he was pleased with the samples that I brought him. Perhaps I will help him again. He seems to be a useful character to know.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/fresh_samples.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5266,'Zizl\'s Message in a Bottle','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',20,1,'Someone by the name of Zizl has been captured by the Murkwater abettors. I\'m already down here, so I might as well see if I can find him, there might be a reward in it for me.',1550063,'I have slain an abettor and found a \"Kill @amp Capture\" list on his body; it would appear the Zizl was not so lucky.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/zizls_message_in_a_bottle.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5267,'A Sewage Problem','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',19,1,'I found a device that appears to be pumping something bad into The Serpent Sewer. The pump appears to be gnomish, so the only explanation for this must be the crazed channel menders are up to no good. I will put a stop to them!',1550026,'I have no idea how to stop the pump, but I know how to handle crazed channel menders! They won\'t be bothering anyone any more.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/a_sewage_problem.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5268,'A Warning to the Murkwaters','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',18,1,'You\'d be amazed at what you can find down here in these sewers. Looks like I found someone\'s dirty laundry list. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/a_warning_to_the_murkwaters.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5269,'A Drudge Problem','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',20,1,'A Qeynosian supporter is receiving shipments of dangerous creatures deep inside the recesses of Serpent Sewer. The most recent shipment appears to be drudge globules, which should be eliminated immediately in the name of Freeport!',1550066,'I have slain quite a few of the drudge globules in the area.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/a_drudge_problem.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5270,'Crazy Talking Skull ','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',1,1,'The darnedest thing happened to me today - I met a talking skull. No fooling. Down in The Serpent Sewer, this skull asked me to find his body, or what\'s left of his body, in the hope that it will put its soul - or whatever it is - to rest.',1550068,'That\'s the last time I help a talking skull. After I returned the remains to the skull, it formed into a skeleton and attacked me! In retrospect, I can\'t say I\'m all too surprised... after all it was a skull I was dealing with.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/crazy_talking_skull_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5271,'Elimination of the Infected   ','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',17,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'I\'ve carried out the tasks stated in the note.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/elimination_of_the_infected_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5272,'A Forgotten Poster','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',16,1,'I found an old decree of the Overlord underneath a bed roll in Serpent Sewer. I\'ve decided that it would be in my best interest to carry out his orders, no matter how old they are.',1550067,'I have done as I have been bidden by the Overlord.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/a_forgotten_poster.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5273,'A Gift From the Serpent\'s Mouth','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',20,1,'I found an intact and very sharp fang inside of Stench the serpent\'s mouth. There may be someone in the area that could make use of this tooth.',0,'Marcus Puer was able to craft me a weapon from the fang once I was able to collect the materials he needed.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/a_gift_from_the_serpents_mouth.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5274,'The Fallen Retriever','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',9,1,'I have found a note that clearly belonged to someone of importance. I must go to seek out someone that bears the name of Azroth, perhaps a relative.',0,'I have found Alexandria Tal`Azroth and learned that her brother was the original keeper of this tattered note. I visited Qalantir to discover that Horatio was dead and then collected blood vials for the Academy of Arcane Science. I was rewarded with coin for my services.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/the_fallen_retriever.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5275,'Sticky Situation','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',13,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/sticky_situation.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5276,'Discarded Pets','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',17,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/discarded_pets.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5277,'Gnasher','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',18,1,'I\'ve found the perfect edge of an axe. It is comprised of very small teeth. It might be possible to return this axe to its former glory if I can find other pieces.',0,'I\'ve been able to reconstruct this axe to its former glory. I\'ve name it The Gnasher in honor of its numerous, little teeth. I\'m certain this axe will inflict much pain to my opponents.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/gnasher.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5278,'Channel Mender Tea','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',19,1,'After a bout with one of the crazed channel menders I recovered some tea leaves he had been carrying. The leaves had a complex, flowery aroma and a lively flavor. I\'ve decided to acquire more of these leaves for my personal use.',0,'I\'ve acquired an ample supply of the channel menders tea leaves, it should last me for a good while.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/channel_mender_tea.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5279,'Crazed Mender Coins','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',19,1,'After a run-in with one of the crazed channel menders I found a rather odd coin. It\'s not currency of any type I\'ve ever seen and I\'m curious as to what it is used for. I\'ll see if I can\'t find out more about these coins while I\'m down here in the Serpent Sewer.',0,'I have found a couple more of these coins and I\'m still at a loss as to their purpose.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/crazed_mender_coins.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5280,'Marked Murkwater Cards','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',19,1,'I found an incomplete set of cards on one of the Murkwaters down here in the Serpent Sewer. The cards were marked and I\'ve decided to find the rest of the marked deck.',0,'I\'ve recovered the rest of the marked cards off one of the Murkwaters, but I better not use these cards if I value my life.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/marked_murkwater_cards.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5281,'Murkwater Coffee','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',19,1,'The pungent aroma of the Murkwater coffee grounds has prompted me to secure more for myself to consume at a later date.',0,'I\'ve found enough of the grounds to satisfy my thirst for the bold viscous brew for a short while.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/murkwater_coffee.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5282,'Foul Order','The Serpent Sewer','The Serpent Sewer',21,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheSerpentSewer/foul_order.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5283,'The Failed Assassin','Thieves Way','Thieves Way',12,8,'It appears that I have unwittingly slain an agent of the Freeport Militia. This agent was undoubtedly ordered by the Freeport Militia to assassinate Lord Marius Darkblade. Perhaps there is something to be gained in completing the agent\'s mission myself.',0,'I unwittingly killed an agent who was ordered by the Freeport Militia to assassinate Lord Darkblade. I have taken it upon myself to kill Lord Marius Darkblade in the agent\'s stead. Captain Molacus awarded me for the deed.','Quests/ThievesWay/the_failed_assassin.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5284,'Saving the Sewage Pumps','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',22,1,'The gland I cut away from that sludge mucus must be acidic! I can feel its acid burning my hands! I can\'t allow these creatures near the sewage pumps of Freeport, lest they erode them into disrepair! I must dispatch them quickly!',0,'Six sludge mucus were slain. They no longer present a threat to the sewer pumps!','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/saving_the_sewage_pumps.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5285,'Crab Meat Hunt   ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',25,1,'After seeing the crab meat in the cup, I have gotten the urge to seek out some of my own. I\'ve heard that there are some large crabs called \"juvenile sludgewalkers\" in the Edgewater Drains, perhaps I should go hunt some.',0,'I have found some large chunks of passable crab meat from these creatures. I think that will be enough though.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/crab_meat_hunt_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5286,'A Dangerous Lesson','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',25,1,'I read a note that said I could gain some good knowledge practicing my fighting skills on the bile toad foragers. We shall see about this.',0,'I have slain quite a few bile toad foragers, and I definitely think I\'m getting better at fighting from that.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/a_dangerous_lesson.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5287,'Exterminating the Contaminated Rats','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',22,1,'I noticed that some of the contaminated rats carry the seal of Qeynos! I shouldn\'t allow them to corrupt the city! The rats must die!',0,'Seven rats were exterminated; the threat to Freeport\'s citizens has been averted!','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/exterminating_the_contaminated_rats.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5288,'The Mucus Feeding Machine','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',22,1,'Some crazy gnome took it upon himself to make a machine that feeds the drudge mucus in Edgewater Drains. I have no desire to see those things get any bigger, so I am going to exterminate them.',0,'I have slain many of the drudge mucus. I\'m surprised that the salt water doesn\'t affect them at all.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/the_mucus_feeding_machine.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5289,'Dangerous Waters ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',26,1,'The Edgewater Drains is a very dangerous place, especially in its deeper areas. The massive needleteeth always pose a threat to those who must swim through these parts, so I have decided to hunt them down.',0,'I have slain some of the massive needleteeth. The waters are still dangerous, but at least people won\'t have to deal with so many of those things anymore.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/dangerous_waters_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5290,'The Coin of Battle   ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',24,1,'I found a coin that says I will reap the rewards of battle if I find others of its kind. I found the coin in a pile of bones on the floor in the Edgewater Drains, perhaps the rotting skeletons would have more of these.',0,'I feel much more knowledgeable in battle having collected the coins from the rotting skeletons.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/the_coin_of_battle.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5291,'Avenge the Freeport Trooper ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',24,1,'The only way a Murkwater henchman could get this Freeport Trooper signet would be off of his corpse! I will make them pay for what they have done!',0,'Six Murkwater henchmen were slain. They have paid the price for their murderous ways!','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/avenge_the_freeport_trooper_.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5292,'A Belt with Potential','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',29,1,'I\'ve retrieved what I thought was a belt off a Murkwater ratonga only to discover that it may have once had a more sinister purpose. It was likely scavenged from the filth that filters down to the lowest level of the sewers that they call home. It appears to have once been part of a whip. I might be able to remake it into something a little more useful.',0,'I have found all the pieces I needed to rebuild the Whip of the Furies.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/a_belt_with_potential.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5293,'Outbreak   ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',22,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.\r\n','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/outbreak.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5294,'A Sandwich Affair  ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',25,1,'I\'ve had one of the best sandwiches I\'ve ever tasted and it was down here in the Edgewater Drains of Freeport. I\'d kill for another one of those Murkwater sandwiches, literally.',0,'I\'ve ruffed up quite a few of the Murkwaters and I got the sandwiches I wanted. And that\'s all that really matters.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/a_sandwich_affair.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5295,'Vengeance ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',25,1,'The severed head of a ratonga spoke to me demanding that I kill his fellow Murkwaters that let him die. Who am I to disagree with a talking head?',0,'The last wish of vengeance towards the Murkwaters has been avenged.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/vengeance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5296,'What Once Was Found, Now is Forever Lost   ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',25,1,'You don\'t know who or what bumped into you, but you\'re very upset that what ever it was it made you drop and lose the pearl earring forever.',0,'I\'ve slaughtered enough living creatures down here. I\'m pretty sure that what ever it was that bumped into me is now dead.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/what_once_was_found_now_is_forever_lost.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5297,'Incredible Edible Egg ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',27,1,'After fending off one of the sewage vipers down in the Edgewater Drains I had recovered one of its eggs. I was bold enough to taste the egg and have determined they are quite palatable. After determining that they were fairly safe I have decided to stock up on a few for later consumption.\r\n',0,'I\'ve taken enough of the viper eggs to last me a little while and this should suffice.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/incredible_edible_egg.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5298,'Overgrowth Impact   ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',27,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/overgrowth_impact.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5299,'Viper Attacks  ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',27,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/viper_attacks.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5300,'Edgewater Needletooth Pudding  ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',29,1,'While in the Edgewater Drains I found a recipe for \"Needletooth Pudding.\" Sounds pretty gross, but I figure why not give it a shot. All of the ingredients are here in the Edgewater.',0,'I\'ve gathered all of the ingredients needed for the this \"Needletooth Pudding,\" but actually eating it, now that\'s another story.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/edgewater_needletooth_pudding.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5301,'Employee Hazards ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',29,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/employee_hazards.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5302,'Mutilated Employees ','Edgewater Drains','Edgewater Drains',29,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these sewers. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/mutilated_employees.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5303,'Inside the Edgewater Drains','Access Quest','Edgewater Drains',20,9,'Bendik Jonkers, a gnome I met in the Edgewater Drains, said that some of gnome inventor Bodwin Zevuwickle\'s discards can still be found in the sewers. He\'ll reward me for finding five particular pieces and bringing them back to him.',1560021,'After finding all five of the discarded parts for Bendik Jonkers, I learned that the Murkwater henchmen stole my reward. After slaying several Murkwater Henchmen, I obtained a key to their hideout, where I confronted and brought down their leader, Madame Kisa.','Quests/EdgewaterDrains/inside_the_edgewater_drains.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5304,'Components for Gimble','Wailing Caves','The Commonlands',1,9,'While traveling north of the crossroads, I ran into an odd little gnome named Gimble Cognoggin. He required some items from the Wailing Caves to make some sort of potion or spell. He wasn\'t very specific about it. But he promised to pay me for my effort, so I took the job.',330187,'Having delved deeply into the Wailing Caves, I can now say that goo is disgusting! That place is filled with slime and skeletons. But I did see something that piqued my interest. There were a couple of live orcs in that cave of a clan named the Ree. I wonder what they\'re doing there.','Quests/TheCommonlands/components_for_gimble.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5305,'Lost Friend in Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',24,1,'A rather distraught halfling by the name of Logan Belchbottom told me the story of him and his companion getting separated. He pleaded for me to help find his companion Mr. Burpbelly. I told him I\'d see what I could do while I\'m down here.',1190017,'I found Logan Belchbottom\'s friend in a cauldron. Looks like the Trolls and Ogres where making a stew. I told Logan of what I sawn and he didn\'t seem to take the new very well, as to be expected.','Quests/FallenGate/lost_friend_in_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5306,'Kill \'em All','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',19,1,'Logan Belchbottom wants to leave the Fallen Gate, but is scared of all the mobs between him and the exit. He asked if I would kill them all so he could have a clear way to the exit. I\'ll help by killing as many of them between him and the exit.',1190017,'I\'ve slain many of the creatures that stand between Logan and the exit. Now it\'s up to him.','Quests/FallenGate/kill_em_all.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5307,'Searching the Depths of Fallen Gate','Access Quest','Fallen Gate',25,6,'The journal I recovered made note that a sealed door somewhere in the wreckage of Fallen Gate is unable to be opened via normal means. The writer of the journal seems to think that there may be a tome in Freeport that has a method of opening the door.',0,'I\'ve managed to complete the incantation and the door at the bottom of Fallen Gate now opens for me. Based on what I\'ve learned so far, a great evil has been sealed behind this barrier, perhaps the being which is responsible for the animation of all the dead in Fallen Gate.','Quests/FallenGate/searching_the_depths_of_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5308,'Charge of the Leatherfoot Brigade - Tippytoe','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',22,6,'I\'ve spoken with the ghost of a halfling in the Fallen Gate. It seems the ghost is replaying the events that led up to his death. He even thinks I\'m one of his soldiers, Lumpy Rumbletummy a.k.a. Special Agent Tippytoe.',1190020,'I\'ve scouted the areas that the Sarge mentioned, but it didn\'t make much of a difference to him','Quests/FallenGate/charge_of_the_leatherfoot_brigade__tippytoe.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5309,'Charge of the Leatherfoot Brigade - Doopy','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',22,1,'If I understood correctly, Special Agent Tippytoe never came back from his scouting, so the Sarge has moved onto Plan B. Now the Sarge thinks I\'m Private Doopy and has reluctantly given me... er... him the task of luring some of the Teir\'Dal to their doom.',1190020,'I\'ve scouted the areas that the Sarge mentioned, but it didn\'t make much of a difference to him.','Quests/FallenGate/charge_of_the_leatherfoot_brigade__doopy.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5310,'Charge of the Leatherfoot Brigade - Frambert','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',22,1,'If I\'m following along, Doopy completely messed up Plan B, and has now been assigned to guarding this \"doohickey\" thing they brought with them. The Sarge has now moved onto Plan C, which involves Frambert... who the Sarge now thinks is me.',1190020,'I\'ve tried smashing the alarms like Frambert was supposed to do, but was unable to do so.\r\n','Quests/FallenGate/charge_of_the_leatherfoot_brigade__frambert.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5311,'Charge of the Leatherfoot Brigade - The Sarge','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',24,6,'From what Sarge is yelling about, it seems that Private Doopy had set off the device they brought with them to destroy Fallen Gate. Apparently, Special Agent Tippytoe was the only one who had the ability to turn off whatever the device was.',1190020,'It seems that at the last moments of Sarge\'s life, he took the device and ran deep into the former city of Neriak. From what is left of the place, it seems he managed to do what he intended.','Quests/FallenGate/charge_of_the_leatherfoot_brigade__the_sarge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5312,'The Broken Halfling Skull','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',22,1,'The visions I gained from the halfling skull seem to ask me to take revenge on tormented dragoons within the Fallen Gate.',0,'The visions have left and the halfling spirit seems to be at peace. For my part, I found a good bit of coin on the last of those tormented dragoons to make this worth my time and effort!','Quests/FallenGate/the_broken_halfling_skull.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5313,'Shadowed Heart Signet','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',24,1,'I\'ve found an odd object - a snapped ring. I think there is more to this object than meets the eye.',0,'Applying a little bit of effort, I\'ve been able to change the snapped ring into Shadowed Heart Signet.','Quests/FallenGate/shadowed_heart_signet.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5314,'Scorched Wooden Staff','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',25,1,'I\'ve found a wooden staff that looks like it has seen better days. The markings on its burnt and charred surface seem to hint at some purpose beyond a normal walking stick.',0,'I have found all the pieces and reassembled the Scorched Wooden Staff. It seems to have only a measure of the power it once possessed but yet is still strong despite the appearance.','Quests/FallenGate/scorched_wooden_staff.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5315,'Ye Olde One-Time Pick','Fallen Gate','Fallen Gate',20,1,'I\'ve uncovered the broken remains of what looks like a military pick. It\'s missing the haft and the metal claw has been sheared off. The metal still looks strong if I can find some replacement pieces this might become a serviceable weapon.',0,'I have found replacements for the pick and reassembled the weapon which was once known as Skullcrusher.','Quests/FallenGate/ye_olde_onetime_pick.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5317,'The Lost Religion of Fallen Gate','City of Freeport','City of Freeport',25,6,'I have offered to help Drund Mordgraahl Skullsprain discover proof of a lost religion in the depths of Fallen Gate. I am searching for a religious artifact called the Gong of Uglan within the ruins of the foreign quarter. It is likely that I will find the artifact near the ruins of an arena.',5590243,'I offered to help Drund Mordgraahl Skullsprain in Freeport find relics of a lost religion in the depths of Fallen Gate. I found the Gong of Uglan and copied the glyphs written upon it. This will provide the Drunds with enough proof to request that the Dismal Rage organizes an expedition into Fallen Gate.','Quests/CityofFreeport/the_lost_religion_of_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5318,'Soul Wailer','Wailing Caves','Wailing Caves',15,1,'I\'ve found an odd object - an old dagger. I think there is more to this object than meets the eye.',0,'Applying a little bit of effort, I\'ve been able to change the old dagger into the Soul Wailer.','Quests/WailingCaves/soul_wailer.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5319,'The Crimson Paw Cloak','Wailing Caves','Wailing Caves',10,1,'I found a grimy patchwork cloak with primitive glyphs scrawled onto it. I placed my hand over a glyph resembling a crimson gnoll paw. A strange feeling overtook me. I feel the need to slay orcs, but not just any orcs, I need to seek the Ree who watch over their captive victims, the Ree jailers.',0,'After being driven to slay Ree jailers, I delved deep into the Wailing Caves to slay them. After doing so I found my feeling of hatred gone. The power of the cloak has subsided, but is it gone forever?','Quests/WailingCaves/the_crimson_paw_cloak.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5320,'The Abhorrent Ring ','Wailing Caves','Wailing Caves',10,6,'I\'ve found an odd object - a ring blank. I think there is more to this object than meets the eye.',0,'Applying a little bit of effort, I\'ve been able to change the ring blank into an Abhorrent Ring.','Quests/WailingCaves/the_abhorrent_ring.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5321,'The Sewer it Key','Access Quest','Gobblerock\'s Hideout',25,6,'While adventuring in the Commonlands I came across a peculiar key. Judging by the poor craftsmanship of this key, I\'m willing to bet that it is of Goblin make. The number of teeth on the key also tells me that the lock this goes to is more than likely a Freeport sewer grate, as the tumblers in most Freeportian grates require only a few, but rather large teeth to open.',0,'I have used this old key and entered what appears to be some sort of Goblin hideout.','Quests/GobblerocksHideout/the_sewer_it_key.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5322,'Gobblerock\'s Hideout','Gobblerock\'s Hideout','Gobblerock\'s Hideout',30,1,'I purchased this book from Jerimiah Halstetter in the Commonlands. It appears to be of goblin make, maybe I should read it.',0,'I have read the whole book.','Quests/GobblerocksHideout/gobblerocks_hideout.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5323,'The Trail of Slime','Gobblerock\'s Hideout','Gobblerock\'s Hideout',33,6,'Captain Ista has told me to track the trail of slime into the sewers and then slay the Gobbler once I have found it.',330243,'I have slain the Gobbler.','Quests/GobblerocksHideout/the_trail_of_slime.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5324,'The Stolen Supplies','Gobblerock\'s Hideout','Gobblerock\'s Hideout',28,8,'Master Jaedra has asked me to collect and return some stolen supplies from Sewer System Number 5.',330245,'I have completed my task.','Quests/GobblerocksHideout/the_stolen_supplies.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5325,'Breaking the Seal to the Inner Sanctum','Prestige','The Vault of the Fallen',27,2,'The doorway to the inner sanctum is sealed by the power of the Dragoons.',6420003,'I have found the seals to unlock the doorway into the Inner Sanctum of Bone.','Quests/TheVaultoftheFallen/breaking_the_seal_to_the_inner_sanctum.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5326,'Delving into Fallen Gate','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',23,2,'A Thexian loyalist named Tundis N\'oxyle bid me to venture into the tunnels that they have opened. He mentioned I might find journals of what transpired all those years ago. I do not much care about his plight, but it seems as though the ancient dark elven city may yet hold much to plunder.',330394,'I uncovered one of the journals of the inhabitants of Neriak, and returned with it to Tundis N\'oxyle. I anticipated his reaction to such valuable information would under-play the significance of the find. There was the vaguest hint of surprise and lack of comprehension as he leafed through the book.','Quests/TheCommonlands/delving_into_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5327,'Journal Translation for Tundis N\'oxyle','The Commonlands','The Commonlands',19,1,'Tundis N\'oxyle has sent me to find a colleague of his, a fellow researcher looking into the state of the dark elven city of Neriak. He\'s told me the last known whereabouts of this Teir\'Dal was the ancient spires in the Nektulos Forest.',330394,'Jhos T\'sein has explained that the translation process could take up to several weeks, and that he will take the book back to Tundis. I also get the feeling he doesn\'t fully trust me...','Quests/TheCommonlands/journal_translation_for_tundis_noxyle.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5328,'Prayer Journal Retrieval','Nektulos Forest','Nektulos Forest',25,2,'I\'ve once again sold my services to the Teir\'Dal loyalists. I am now feeling almost as involved in their quest to find out what happened to the ruined city as they are, though I know I certainly do not chafe as much as they seem to in Freeport. I am to visit the depths of the Fallen Gate again, and this time return with some information as to the gods worshiped at an altar deep in the cavern.',1790190,'The unspeakable horror that lies within the foul dungeon claws at my very soul. Even I, such as I am, tremble at the thought of again returning there. Though I proved once again successful, recovering the tome of a long-dead priest for Jhos T\'sein, I have determined that a good rest may be in order.','Quests/NektulosForest/prayer_journal_retrieval.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5329,'Scrawlings in the Dark','Antonica','Antonica',18,1,'I have agreed to assist an old vagabond trader named Rikantus. He wishes me to find an old tome called the \'Scrawlings of Chirannis\' within gnoll infested Blackburrow.',120403,'I gave the tome called \'Scrawlings of Chirannis\' to Rikantus at Evernight Cemetery in Antonica.','Quests/Antonica/scrawlings_in_the_dark.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5330,'The Trials of Sir Morgan   ','Antonica','Antonica',27,2,'I received an old book from Rikantus with a short tale of a knight called \'The Trials of Sir Morgan.\' I should visit the locations and relive the battles mentioned in the book, they seem to exist in the Thundering Steppes.',0,'Visiting the location of the story \'The Trials of Sir Morgan\' has led me to do battle and eventually earned me a useless amulet. Rikantus said it was the \'Amulet of Ullkorruuk\' and that it belonged to his ancestors.','Quests/Antonica/the_trials_of_sir_morgan.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5331,'The Hidden Riddle','Antonica','Antonica',32,1,'Rikantus the vagabond merchant has enlisted me to recover an ancient puzzle box taken from his ancestors called \'The Riddle of Saryrn\'. He says it is located in the remnants of the Keep of Immortality better known as the Ruins of Varsoon.',120403,'I recovered the puzzle box called \'The Riddle of Saryrn\'. I delivered the ancient toy to the rightful owner, Rikantus the vagabond merchant.','Quests/Antonica/the_hidden_riddle.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5332,'Visions of Coldwind Point','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'I have received a book from Quallium, \"Vision\'s of Coldwind Point.\" Perhaps I should read the poems within and visit the locations it speaks of.',0,'I visited all four locations mentioned in the four poems of Quallium found in \"Visions of Coldwind Point.\"','Quests/Antonica/visions_of_coldwind_point.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5333,'Deliveries for Flores','Antonica','Antonica',13,1,'I\'ve taken a job from Flores delivering a couple crates for him, one to Novak out by the lighthouse and one to Geddard out at Gnollslayer keep at the far end of Antonica.',120087,'I managed to deliver both crates and bring back Novak and Geddard\'s pouches to Flores. Those crates just about broke my back! But I suppose not many want to trudge out there with supplies, so every run has got to count.','Quests/Antonica/deliveries_for_flores.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5334,'Getting the Axe','Antonica','Antonica',12,9,'I met Squire Kivan in Antonica. He has asked me to collect ten Sabertooth mining picks from Sabertooth miners, most likely found in Blackburrow.',120431,'I found the ten Sabertooth mining picks.','Quests/Antonica/getting_the_axe.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5335,'Sabertooth Battle Plans','Antonica','Antonica',18,9,'I met Sir Jeager in Antonica. He has asked me to return to the cave that I found and collect the Sabertooth battle plans.',120432,'I have found the Sabertooth battle plans.','Quests/Antonica/sabertooth_battle_plans.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5336,'Tillin\'s Gnoll Woes   ','Antonica','Antonica',17,1,'Sergeant Tillin has tasked me with gathering some items from Blackburrow to keep tabs on what the gnolls are up to there.',120322,'I\'ve gathered all the items that Sergeant Tillin needed.','Quests/Antonica/tillins_gnoll_woes.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5337,'Fishing Hole Hunt','Antonica','Antonica',18,1,'I have agreed to help Blarton Blumble in Windstalker Village by checking on his favorite fishing spots. He has provided me with a list of all of the spots I must visit.',120163,'I have helped Blarton Blumble and checked on all of his favorite fishing spots. Does he need me to do anything else for him?','Quests/Antonica/fishing_hole_hunt.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5338,'The One That Got Away','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'Blarton Blumble in Windstalker Village wants me to find a strange fish by the name of Ol\' One Eye. He says the fish lurks somewhere in the pond near here.',120163,'I have searched the waters of Antonica and found a fish named Ol\' One Eye for Blarton. He was very grateful for all of my help.','Quests/Antonica/the_one_that_got_away.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5339,'Fishing for Bait','Antonica','Antonica',18,1,'Blarton Blumble wants me to recover the tin of bait that his cousin left at a camp to the south of Windstalker Village. Beware, as it may be overrun with gnolls.',120163,'I have found Blarton\'s lost bait and returned it to him.','Quests/Antonica/fishing_for_bait.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5340,'Sparkly or Nothing','Antonica','Antonica',20,1,'Licha has asked me to bring her the shiniest scales I can find.',121308,'I have returned the scales to Licha.','Quests/Antonica/sparkly_or_nothing.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5341,'A New Dress, NOW!','Antonica','Antonica',20,1,'Licha\'s father won\'t buy her a new dress and she asked me to get her a new, fancy one from some merchant in Thundering Steppes.',121308,'I found Licha a new dress.','Quests/Antonica/a_new_dress_now.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5342,'Licha, Dancing Queen','Antonica','Antonica',20,1,'Licha wants me to help gather an audience for her performance.',121308,'I helped Licha\'s dreams come true.','Quests/Antonica/licha_dancing_queen.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5343,'She Had Ribbons In Her Hair','Antonica','Antonica',17,1,'Licha said her ribbons were stolen by some highwaymen. She wants me to go hunt them down and return her ribbons to her.',121308,'I recovered the ribbons from the highwaymen.','Quests/Antonica/she_had_ribbons_in_her_hair.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5344,'Patchwork Rugs','Antonica','Antonica',16,1,'Hartok, the rug maker, has asked me to gather some bear pelts for his new rugs.',121309,'I have acquired several pelts for Hartok.','Quests/Antonica/patchwork_rugs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5345,'Tree within a Tree','Antonica','Antonica',25,1,'Oracle Ulinara, an Erudite at the Tower of the Oracles, asked if I could be of assistance in locating a special tree she saw in a vision while looking into their Karma Pool. I agreed to help and she told me the stars that she saw seemed to indicate that the \"Tree within a Tree\" was located in the center of the region called the Thundering Steppes. She also asked if I would bring back one of the Golden Acorns found on the tree. I\'ve never hunted a tree before, so this should be interesting.',120018,'I found the tree that Ulinara saw and was able to gather an acorn from it. That tree was very tall! She was very pleased and showed me how to use the acorn in a special recipe after I indicated on a map the tree\'s location.','Quests/Antonica/tree_within_a_tree.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5346,'Door to Door Delivery','Antonica','Antonica',16,1,'Hartok is far too busy to deliver his rugs to the Keep of the Gnollslayers. He didn\'t look that busy to me. I should take care of this task for him and perhaps find out why he is reluctant to make his own deliveries.',121309,'I have delivered Hartok\'s rugs. I didn\'t see anything that should make Hartok nervous. Perhaps when I speak to him again he will explain what is going on.','Quests/Antonica/door_to_door_delivery.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5347,'Attack of the Killer Bear','Antonica','Antonica',20,1,'Hartok explained to me that he believes a bear is out to seek revenge on him for hunting in this area. He seems rather shaken up about the whole situation. He informed me that he would be willing to reward me well for my efforts. Hartok last saw this bear while he was in the Shattered Vale, accessed through a pass within the mountain range to the southwest. If I am able to locate a Giantslayer messenger along the way, I may be able to discover how to get inside the druid vale.',121309,'I have slain the beast that has been stalking Hartok. Now that the beast is gone, it appears that Hartok is back to his old ways.','Quests/Antonica/attack_of_the_killer_bear.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5348,'Exploring the Chessboard  ','Antonica','Antonica',23,1,'Breeza Harmet mentioned to me that legend stated the Knights of Thunder would hold their feasts upon a giant chessboard. She said no one has been able to confirm this legend of Stormhold but if I were to ever see such a thing to let her know.',120159,'Upon exploring Stormhold I was able to find the chessboard which Breeza had spoken of. It does seem the Knights of Thunder held banquets here but why on a chessboard? Maybe there is more to this unique room...','Quests/Antonica/exploring_the_chessboard.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5349,'The Balance of Life ','Antonica','Antonica',17,1,'I\'ve met a wood elf named Daryann Stormrider. She monitors the various wildlife in the area and reduces the numbers of predators or prey to keep them in balance. I\'ve offered to help her cull some of the creatures.',121302,'I\'ve done what\'s necessary as a good steward of the lands. I\'ve learned that every animal must have its numbers managed or life\'s balance is upset. Daryann appreciated my help.','Quests/Antonica/the_balance_of_life.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5350,'Letter to Riason','Antonica','Antonica',23,1,'Merchant Cooper needs a letter delivered from the city to a friend of his out by Windstalker pond. I fear for him though, for he seemed furtive in his responses.',120150,'I\'ve delivered the letter to Riason Hanagom as requested of me. I cannot say what will happen now, but the situation certainly seems less than savory.','Quests/Antonica/letter_to_riason.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5351,'A Rediscovered Shrine?','Antonica','Antonica',28,1,'Riason Hanagom in Windstalker Village told me about a shrine after I pried a bit. He hired me to find the exact location of the place in the Thundering Steppes. Early word he got from Trader Cooper is that it is far to the south. This should be an interesting journey.',120150,'That cretin Riason sent me to a shrine of disease! I found the Shrine of Bertoxxulous to the south of the Thundering Steppes covered with gnolls. If I get sick I am going to throttle that man...','Quests/Antonica/a_rediscovered_shrine.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5352,'Running Out Of Beer','Antonica','Antonica',10,1,'I have spoken with a rather strange dwarf named Haddek Vimki. It appears that he is going to require an ale from upstairs before he is going to hand me any work.',120281,'I have given Haddek his ale. Maybe now I can get him to give me some work.','Quests/Antonica/running_out_of_beer.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5353,'Ouch! My Head   ','Antonica','Antonica',12,1,'It appears that Haddek has a bit of a hangover. Rather than just admit he needs some help, he tried to get me to believe he was trying to help his friend, Aroof. I should just humor him and gather the stuff he needs to make a hangover cure.',120281,'I have gathered everything needed to make a hangover cure for Haddek.','Quests/Antonica/ouch_my_head.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5354,'Rise and Shine Wine','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'Apparently Haddek has some plans to make something he calls \"Rise and Shine Wine.\" He wants me to gather some goo from risen protectors to help him make this wine. The risen protectors are on an island off the Coldwind Coast in the northwest area of Antonica.',120281,'I have gathered enough goo for Haddek\'s wine. He was quite grateful and is very excited to complete his brew.','Quests/Antonica/rise_and_shine_wine.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5355,'Practical Joke on Blarton','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'Haddek was very excited about the goo that I delivered to him. Somehow, he feels that it will give his wine an extra kick. Now he wants me to take the wine that he made and deliver it to a friend of his named Blarton.',120281,'I delivered the wine to Blarton. He didn\'t look like he enjoyed the wine much, but somehow I don\'t think that is what Haddek had in mind anyway.','Quests/Antonica/practical_joke_on_blarton.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5356,'Under a Shady Tree','Antonica','Antonica',10,1,'I met a love-struck elf named Landwyn who wants me to gather some flowers for his lover.',121388,'I have picked and delivered the flowers to Landwyn.','Quests/Antonica/under_a_shady_tree.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5357,'A Bow for a Beauty ','Antonica','Antonica',13,1,'Landwyn has asked me to collect earthcrawler leg joints to make a gift for his beauty.',121388,'I have collected all of the earthcrawler leg joints for Landwyn.','Quests/Antonica/a_bow_for_a_beauty.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5358,'She Will Be a Shining Petal','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'Landwyn has asked me to collect thick klicnik shells from klicnik warriors to make a gift for his lady.',121388,'I have collected the klicnik shells for Landwyn.','Quests/Antonica/she_will_be_a_shining_petal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5359,'Peppermints and Potions ','Antonica','Antonica',16,1,'Landwyn has asked me to seek out his lady love and deliver a package to her.',121388,'Unfortunately, I was unable to find his love to deliver the package to.','Quests/Antonica/peppermints_and_potions.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5360,'Song to Prexus','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'My poor friend Landwyn has had his heartbroken. He bid me to throw all the mementos of his love out into the sea from a place known as \"Lonely Isle.\"',121388,'I have disposed of the reminders of Landwyn\'s heartbreak.','Quests/Antonica/song_to_prexus.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5361,'How Did Their Garden Grow?','Antonica','Antonica',20,1,'I met a halfling gardener by the name of Darmen Sproutmore. She told me that rumors have surfaced that explorers have found the last home of the Knights of Thunder, Stormhold. She also mentioned that no one could remember the Knights ever maintaining a farm or ordering food supplies out of Qeynos. She wondered how they provided for themselves.',120366,'After exploring Stormhold, I was able to find an atrium on a lower level. It did appear that plants were grown here. Darmen believed that Karana provided the light and water to sustain these plants\' lives.','Quests/Antonica/how_did_their_garden_grow.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5362,'Anti-venom Components for Brendan','North Qeynos','North Qeynos',10,1,'Medic Brendan would like me to collect some components for an anti-venom he will brew for the local guards who must patrol in hazardous areas. I am to go to the nearby caves and recover several components for this antidote.',2220143,'I was able to return safely with all of the required components for the antidote Brendan wished. With any luck those reagents will save a guard\'s life someday.','Quests/NorthQeynos/antivenom_components_for_brendan.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5363,'Barbaric Chores','South Qeynos','South Qeynos',10,1,'Feodra Iceslayer was planning on going to the Caves to slay some spiders to collect their venom sacs, but since I was looking for work I get to gather them for her. I need to be careful not to damage them.',2310100,'Feodra Iceslayer was pleased with the spider venom sacs I returned with and paid me for my effort.','Quests/SouthQeynos/barbaric_chores.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5364,'Batwing Crunchies for Jerben ','Starcrest Commune','Starcrest Commune',10,1,'I\'m off to gather up some albino bat wings after speaking with Innkeeper Jerben. Apparently his wife likes to bake him batwing crunchies, but hasn\'t been able to get any of the wings in a while now.',2340030,'Jerben Sleepwell was very pleased that he could once again have his favorite dish. He paid me a little coin for my services, but better than that, I know he and his wife will be happy tonight! The extra table is a welcome addition to my needed furniture collection as well.','Quests/StarcrestCommune/batwing_crunchies_for_jerben.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5365,'Working the Down Below','The Down Below','The Down Below',11,1,'While in the Down Below I met a merchant by the name of Adair Barnes. She needed some help gathering items for her customers, so I decided to help.',1990011,'I\'ve helped merchant Adair Barnes gather a bunch of items for her customers in the Down Below. If I\'m going to be in the area for a while perhaps she would like some more help.','Quests/TheDownBelow/working_the_down_below.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5366,'An Intriguing Eye','The Down Below','The Down Below',10,1,'I discovered a bound hollow tome in the Down Below. The image on the book is of an eye circled with a band formed of hands. I am intrigued to know more about this symbol. Perhaps it will gain me access to something hidden from Qeynosian life above.',0,'The symbol has led me to believe there is a secret hideout of some sorts in the Down Below. Who is in the hideout is a mystery I will surely find out and report to the Qeynos Guard.','Quests/TheDownBelow/an_intriguing_eye.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5367,'Defiled Drem Drem','The Down Below','The Down Below',9,1,'Upon seeing the engraving of Drem Drem the Jester on this coffin, I remembered a story I once heard in a tavern about his meddling ways. Unfortunately, someone, or something has taken his bones from their resting place! Drem Drem deserves better than that! I will look for his bones and lay him to rest.',0,'I have found as many of what appear to be Drem Drem\'s bones as I could. I hope he rests peacefully.','Quests/TheDownBelow/defiled_drem_drem.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5368,'The Motley Merchant Manifest','Crows Resting Place','CrowsRestingPlace',10,1,'I have agreed to assist the somewhat civilized gnoll named Fippy Darkpaw. He wants me to provide him with signatures of Qeynos merchants.',2020003,'I have supplied Fippy Darkpaw with the Motley Merchant Manifest. He has rewarded me and noted that should I attempt to report him to the Qeynos Guard he will have me framed as an associate of his illegal thieves band.','Quests/CrowsRestingPlace/the_motley_merchant_manifest.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5369,'An Ancient Scepter','The Down Below','The Down Below',10,1,'I found an ancient scepter on the remains of an unfortunate denizen of the catacombs. The markings seem to place it as a religious scepter from deep in the catacombs. I believe it may be from some sort of skeletal statue.',0,'As I replaced the scepter in its original position, a small ring fell from the finger of the statue. Had I not been returning the scepter to its original resting place, I would have never noticed it.','Quests/TheDownBelow/an_ancient_scepter.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5370,'Visions of Flame','The Feerrott','The Feerrott',39,1,'Those fires burn red for a reason! I must stop the lizardmen of the Feerrott before they gather in strength and try to invade the cities!',0,'I have slain the lizardmen and have stopped what could have been a major invasion!','Quests/TheFeerrott/visions_of_flame.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5371,'Vegalys Keldrane\'s Betrayal','The Crypt of Betrayal ','The Crypt of Betrayal ',20,1,'I encountered the spirit of Vegalys Keldrane. He believes he was betrayed to his death by one of his three lieutenants. I need to find the spirits of those three lieutenants, Adun, Borthen and Vargon, in the Crypt of Betrayal and learn what they might know about Keldrane\'s betrayal.',2010030,'There is much unrest in the Crypt of Betrayal. The passions, both love and hatred, have followed the dead. Hopefully, the information I gleaned from the spirits of his fallen comrades will put Vegalys Keldrane\'s spirit at ease.','Quests/TheCryptofBetrayal/vegalys_keldranes_betrayal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5372,'Forgotten Potion','The Crypt of Betrayal','The Crypt of Betrayal',20,1,'Cryptkeeper Maglus needs ten forsaken shriller wings to make some sort of potion. I offered to find and bring her the necessary ingredient.',2010043,'I obtained ten forsaken shriller wings and gave them to Cryptkeeper Maglus so that she can make her potion.','Quests/TheCryptofBetrayal/forgotten_potion.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5373,'Forgotten Potion - Into the Hive','The Crypt of Betrayal','The Crypt of Betrayal',25,1,'Cryptkeeper Maglus needs fifteen deathly scarab antennae for her potion. I offered to find and bring her the necessary ingredient.',2010043,'I\'ve gotten the deathly scarab antennae for Cryptkeeper Maglus so that she can make her potion.','Quests/TheCryptofBetrayal/forgotten_potion__into_the_hive.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5374,'A Crumpled Note','The Down Below','The Down Below',10,1,'I found a note while exploring the catacombs. At first I wasn\'t particularly interested, but it seems that once I finally opened it, the note contained some information as to a plot. I have decided to take this note to the Three Towers and speak with the mages about it.',2310071,'I gave the note to Amren Talbot in the Three Towers. He seemed less impressed with the find. He believes we are secure, though he did say he would bring it to his superiors.','Quests/TheDownBelow/a_crumpled_note.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5375,'A Crumpled Note','The Down Below','The Down Below',10,1,'I found a note while exploring the catacombs. At first I wasn\'t particularly interested, but it seems that once I finally opened it, the note contained some information as to a plot. I have decided to take this note to the Steel Warriors guild and speak with the fighters about it.',2210218,'I gave the note to Sir Sidan Godard at the Steel Warriors guild hall. He was very interested, and said he would bring it up to his superiors.','Quests/TheDownBelow/a_crumpled_note_warriors_guild.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5376,'Goods Down Below','The Down Below','The Down Below',8,1,'While venturing in the Down Below I came across a merchant by the name of Falin Shaloon. He said his customers want what\'s down here and asked if I\'d help gather a few of these items. I told him I would oblige.\r\n',1990040,'I got everything Falin wanted, though I\'m not sure if it was worth my time, but if I\'m going to be down here anyway maybe I\'ll help him again.','Quests/TheDownBelow/goods_down_below.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5377,'Prime Target','The Crypt of Betrayal','The Crypt of Betrayal',24,2,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these catacombs. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheCryptofBetrayal/prime_target.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5378,'Tactical Report','The Crypt of Betrayal','The Crypt of Betrayal',29,1,'It\'s amazing what you can find down here in these catacombs. This appears to have been some sort of official notice or report or something. I wonder what would happen if I carried out its plan?',0,'Interesting... I guess it was worth it for the experience. I suppose it couldn\'t hurt to take on adventures such as these.','Quests/TheCryptofBetrayal/tactical_report.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
