(5883,'Obtain Adventurer Class','Hallmark','Hallmark',9,1,'I need to speak with Priest Kelian about advancing as a priest.',0,'I have spoken to Priest Kelian about advancing.','Quests/Hallmark/obtain_adventurer_class__fpriest.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5884,'Obtain Adventurer Class','Hallmark','Hallmark',9,1,'I need to speak with Emissary Millia about advancing as a scout.',0,'I spoke to Emissary Millia about advancing.','Quests/Hallmark/obtain_adventurer_class__fscout.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5885,'Antonica Creature Cataloging','Antonica','Antonica',15,1,'I am trying to catalog some creatures I read about in the Antonica creature guide. When I\'m not busy cataloging, I can store the book in my house to show off my culture and learning.',0,'I\'ve successfully catalogued all the creatures in the Antonica creature guide.','Quests/Antonica/antonica_creature_cataloging.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5886,'The Story of the Rat Queen','Vermins Snye','Vermins Snye',20,1,'This rat-chewed volume contains a story about, or possibly even by, a woman known as the \"Rat Queen.\" I\'m not sure I know the whole story, and unless I find the rest of the pages, I might never know.',0,'An interesting tale, told from two different points of view. It\'s not clear whether the woman called the Rat Queen is insane; she sounds perfectly reasonable. I imagine the ratonga wouldn\'t find anything odd in her tale. Or her \"tail.\" Hahaha!','Quests/VerminsSnye/the_story_of_the_rat_queen.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5887,'Far Seas Requisition #DB0372','The Down Below','The Down Below',6,1,'I have discovered a direct delivery Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the client of the Far Seas Trading Co. and receive payment.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the client in Castleview Hamlet. I have been paid in full for this work, but the order was late.','Quests/TheDownBelow/far_seas_requisition_db0372.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5888,'Far Seas Requisition #DB0436','The Down Below','The Down Below',6,1,'I have discovered a direct delivery Far Seas Requisition slip. The hunter charged with filling the order must have been slain. If I hunt down the creatures and fill the order I can deliver the order to the client of the Far Seas Trading Co. and receive payment.',0,'I filled the Far Seas Requisition and delivered the goods to the client in Castleview Hamlet. I have been paid in full for this work, but the order was late.','Quests/TheDownBelow/far_seas_requisition_db0436.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5889,'Freeport to Qeynos - Part 1','Access Quest','Hallmark',15,1,'I have found out that Stilus Graphium, the head of the Freeport Observer, is in truth a spy for Qeynos. I have agreed to join his cause and turn my back on Freeport forever, choosing a life of good over one of evil.',1280410,'I have found and spoken to the head of the Qeynos resistance here in Freeport','Quests/Hallmark/freeport_to_qeynos__part_1.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5890,'Freeport to Qeynos - Part 2','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'I\'ve chosen to live a life of virtue by helping Kenjedeau put a stop to the evil of Freeport. I\'ve agreed to stop an important official from sharing his plans on how to invade Qeynos.',1550077,'I am the victim of a cruel and elaborate hoax intended to coerce people into betraying Freeport, all for the amusement of the Overlord himself. In the end, I still believed in what I said and accepted my fate. For some reason... I\'m still alive.','Quests/Hallmark/freeport_to_qeynos__part_2.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5891,'Freeport to Qeynos - Exile','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'I was rescued by the false executioner Selindi and given a second chance at life. Even though she saved me, I still suffer the effects of the poison used to masquerade my death. It will be a long, long time before the effects wear off. I must flee before the necromancers find my body gone. Freeport considers me a traitor, and Qeynos sees me as a monster. All I have left is my hope.',330235,'During the time I spent in exile, I thought upon what it means to hold the ideals of virtue. I understand that the ends do not justify the means, but rather the path that one takes decides what is good or evil. Though a good life is harder, it is more rewarding.','Quests/Hallmark/freeport_to_qeynos__exile.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5892,'Freeport to Qeynos - Conversion','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'Vishra has shown me that virtue comes not from fighting evil, but rather from becoming the evil that I fight. I have gained the courage to do what is right and will live my life by these ideals. I will go forth and protect those who cannot defend themselves.',120402,'I have done what I can to help Qeynos to ward off the threats that wish to destroy the unity of the city. It will be a never ending fight, but I am willing to do my part, as others have before me. I can only hope the people of Qeynos will accept me for what I really am.','Quests/Hallmark/freeport_to_qeynos__conversion.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5893,'Freeport to Qeynos - Acceptance','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'I have been accepted into the city of Qeynos, my new home. I have been given instructions by Vishra on the final step needed to complete my conversion.',120402,'I have begun my new life in Qeynos with the help of my mentor, Vishra. No longer will I blindly turn away from the evils around me. Perhaps others will follow my example and do the same. If so, I will offer my help to them as others have helped me.','Quests/Hallmark/freeport_to_qeynos__acceptance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5894,'Qeynos to Freeport - Part 1','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I\'ve found out that Cordun Brenland is actually a sinister double-crosser hiding out in Qeynos. I have agreed to join up with him to take from Qeynos what is rightfully mine. When this is done, we\'ll travel to Freeport and live a life of evil.',2210501,'I have found and spoken with Cordun\'s partner, Remy.','Quests/Hallmark/qeynos_to_freeport__part_1.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5895,'Qeynos to Freeport - Part 2','Access Quest','Hallmark',15,1,'I\'ve chosen to live a life of power by helping Remy and Cordun to steal the crown jewels from the Queen. They\'ll cause the distraction while I find the bodyguard who holds the key to the vault... and kill her.',0,'I\'ve been set up by Cordun and Remy. They backstabbed me by setting me up for the fall, all the while getting a reward for their \"heroic\" actions. I\'ll likely be given a life sentence for trying to assassinate the Queen. My life of evil was short and swift.','Quests/Hallmark/qeynos_to_freeport__part_2.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5896,'Qeynos to Freeport - Exile','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'I was rescued by a Freeportian ratonga by the name of Yuri. Even though he saved me, he injected me with a poison that has left me very weak. It will be a long, long time before the effects wear off. Unfortunately, I\'m a wanted fugitive in Qeynos now, and will likely be killed if I try to enter Freeport. I would give anything to kill the two who sold me out.',0,'During my time in exile, I spent day and night cultivating my vengeance towards those who spurned me and betrayed my trust. I can now see my own soul, and find it to be black and twisted. This comforts me.','Quests/Hallmark/qeynos_to_freeport__exile.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5897,'Qeynos to Freeport - Conversion','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'Matthias has removed the taint of virtue and goodwill from my burning heart. Hatred will be my new lover, and vengeance my reason for living. It is time the world pays me for all the suffering I endured. And pay it will... in blood.',0,'I have decimated the enemies of Freeport using the true power of vengeance to guide my way. I have shown Freeport that I am a kindred soul to their beliefs. If they do not accept me within their walls, then they too will suffer my wrath.','Quests/Hallmark/qeynos_to_freeport__conversion.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5898,'Fighter Training','Hallmark','Hallmark',8,1,'I\'ve convinced the Commandant of Freeport to train me in the arts of fighting.',1440465,'I have graduated from Commandant Tychus\' personal academy.  Through his training, I\'ve learned the ways of different classes of Fighter. At the end of my training, the Commandant had let me choose which classification of fighter I wanted to become. ','Quests/Hallmark/fighter_training.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5899,'Becoming A Brawler','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Commandant Tychus told me that if I wanted to be a Brawler I should talk with Korong Shatterjaw out by the arena. Tychus said he would show me how a real brawler fights.',1440465,'I took on all of the Brawler\'s that Korong Shatterjaw threw at me and survived.  He seemed somewhat impressed with my ability and said some day I should be ready to challenge him.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_brawler.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5900,'Becoming a Crusader','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Commandant Tychus as tasked me with finding a group of defectors that want to sneak out of Freeport and head to Qeynos. They will most likely try to sway me to their side. I must be ready for this.',1440465,'I stopped the defection and saved the lives of the misguided.  To be a Crusader I must stand unswerving for my beliefs and that is what I have done.  The Commandant was impressed with my conviction.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_crusader.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5901,'Becoming a Warrior','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Commandant Tychus has given me the task of finding out the name of the man who is providing a safehouse for the Dervish Cutthroats inside of Freeport. Tychus then said he would show me how a real warrior fights.',1440465,'I found out that Bargiss Ranlor was helping out the Dervish Cutthroats survive in the city.  I didn\'t need the Commandant\'s help, I took care of the problem on my own.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_warrior.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5902,'Mage Training','Hallmark','Hallmark',8,1,'Arcanist Sonius has agreed to take me on as a student in my arcane studies. She will present several different courses revolving around the different avenues of arcane learning.',1440463,'I have graduated from Arcanist Sonius\'s courses and chose which dedicated study I will pursue. Though I have seen what a Sorcerer, Enchanter, and Summoner studies... I know which one I will devote myself to.  Grasping the mysteries of arcane knowledge will be a daunting task, but the reward of power will drive me to learn as much as I can. ','Quests/Hallmark/mage_training.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5903,'Becoming an Enchanter','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen the path I wish to study. I want to be an Enchanter. Arcanist Sonius has directed me to take care of some business concerning a couple of Seafury Buccaneers. I need to find these Seafuries in the Back Alley Brewhouse and make an example of them that their character will understand.',1440463,'I convinced a troll named Bulz near the Seafuries to attack the men saving me the trouble of doing it myself.  Unfortunately a member of their crew was wise to my scheme and attacked me directly.  I had to be a little more... direct with him.  I reported back to Arcanist Sonius soon afterwards.  She was pleased with my work and bestowed upon me the title of Enchanter.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_an_enchanter.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5904,'Becoming a Sorcerer','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen the path I wish to study. I want to be a Sorcerer. Arcanist Sonius has directed me to participate in a duel against another pupil of hers, Dasicar T\'Lys. I need to meet Dasicar in the dueling chamber inside the Academy and emerge the stronger if I am to be worthy of the title Sorcerer.',1440463,'I defeated Dasicar T\'Lys in a duel of mages.  Arcanist Sonius was surprised that I won and Dasicar was the vanquished.  It doesn\'t matter.  I am the one that is now the Sorcerer.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_sorcerer.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5905,'Becoming a Summoner','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen the path I wish to study. I want to become a Summoner. Arcanist Sonius informed me that a room has been prepared at the Academy of Arcane Sciences for those Apprentices to wish to become Summoners. I am to create an Earth Elemental then defeat it in combat to demonstrate my abilities.',1440463,'I created the elemental and destroyed it.  I showed the Arcanist the remains of my creation and she seemed quite pleased.  I have rightfully earned the title Summoner.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_summoner.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5906,'Priest Training','Hallmark','Hallmark',8,1,'Priest Kelian has offered to guide my spiritual enlightenment. He plans on showing me the ways of the Priest and where my spirituality may lead to.',1440466,'I have told Proctor Fergus the choice I have made towards my spiritual enlightenment. He has given me his blessing and told me to go forth and spread the word. Soon enough, I shall introduce my new-found faith to the heathens of this world.','Quests/Hallmark/priest_training.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5907,'Becoming a Cleric','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen my spiritual path. I want to become a Cleric. Priest Kelian has sent me to speak to Modinite Z\'Vol in the Temple of War. He will put me through the test known as The Threshing.',1440466,'I survived the pain of the Threshing.  I have emerged purified and worthy of the title I now hold.  I am a Cleric.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_cleric.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5908,'Becoming a Druid','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen my spiritual path. I want to become a Druid. Priest Kelian has sent me to take care of a magic experiment that has gone wrong concerning nature. This is my chance to show that I can be a druid and that the natural world is greater than any mage\'s magical powers.',1440466,'I defeated the plant beast that the mage failed to destroy after creating it.  I have demonstrated that the power of nature is greater than any mages creation.  I am now a Druid.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_druid.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5909,'Becoming a Shaman','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'I have chosen my spiritual path. I want to become a Shaman. Priest Kelian has sent me to seek out rebellious spirits taking up residence in a mansion in the South of Freeport. I will only have a limited time to subdue these spirits with my power. I must act quickly.',1440466,'I subdued the rebellious spirits.  They are now mine to control.  I have emerged as a master of the spirit world.  I am a Shaman.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_shaman.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5910,'Scout Training','Hallmark','Hallmark',8,1,'Emissary Millia has offered to teach me a few tricks about being a scout.',1440464,'I have been given a taste of what the Emissary does for Freeport, and it seems intriguing. With that in mind, I think I\'m going to specialize in certain skills so that one day I might be in a position to do what she does. Either way, I\'m pretty sure I can find some good loot in the meantime. ','Quests/Hallmark/scout_training.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5911,'Becoming a Bard','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Emissary Millia has given me the task of obtaining an important ledger from a party the Coalition of Tradesfolke is having. To do this I need to distract their attention through entertainment before I take the ledger out from under them.',1440464,'I was able to entertain the merchants and distract them with my talents before I swiped the ledger out from under them.  Millia was quite impressed when I turned the ledger over to her.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_bard.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5912,'Becoming a Predator','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Emissary Millia has tasked me with eliminating a threat to the city. I need to silence the rebellious Captain Driftskull before he convinces too many of his men to go rogue and become criminal pirates. Millia said his regular haunt can be found on the upper west level.',1440464,'I was able to take care of Captain Driftskull.  There won\'t be any more talk from him about going independent.  Millia was impressed with my work.  I think I am going to like being a Predator.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_predator.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5913,'Becoming a Rogue','Hallmark','Hallmark',10,1,'Emissary Millia wants me to sneak into the Port Authority harbor master\'s office and steal both of his ship logs. If I can do this I will prove to her I can be a Rogue.',1440464,'I stole the logs from the Port Authority office and handed them over to Emissary Millia.  Millia taught me that being a Rogue is not just about my skills but also how to look for opportunity in any situation.','Quests/Hallmark/becoming_a_rogue.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5914,'Qeynos to Freeport - Acceptance','Hallmark','Hallmark',17,1,'I have been accepted into walls of Freeport, and will from hereon make this city my new home.  I have been given instructions by Matthias on the final step needed to complete my conversion.',0,'I have begun a new life in Freeport with the help of my mentor, Matthias.  No longer will this world keep from me what is rightfully mine.  Those that stand against me will show themselves to be my enemies.   ...May the gods grant them the mercy that I can not...','Quests/Hallmark/qeynos_to_freeport__acceptance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5915,'Twergo\'s Plan','Temple Street','Temple Street',8,1,'The gnome, Twergo Togglesmeet, has asked me to collect zombie brains for his experiment. He plans on creating a mind control device that will cause his customers to buy only from him.',1360025,'Twergo paid me for the brains. I tried to convince him that he could use the device to rule the world, but he was adamant that it couldn\'t be used that way.','Quests/TempleStreet/twergos_plan.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5916,'Qwergo\'s Plan','Temple Street','Temple Street',6,1,'Qwergo the Merchant has a very heated rivalry with the Ratonga on the other side of the plaza. He\'s asked me to help him put an end to the dispute.',1360026,'Qwergo has paid me for picking up a Rumblestick for him. He was busy playing with the buttons and strings on it, so I\'m not too sure what it is used for.','Quests/TempleStreet/qwergos_plan.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5917,'Vlepo\'s Plan','Temple Street','Temple Street',6,1,'Vlepo the merchant has asked me to steal a weapon from someone named Shinska. I should check Temple Street to find this Shinska.',1360018,'Vlepo plans on taking the weapon I stole from Shinska and planting it in the Togglesmeets\' stall. After that he\'ll call the guards, framing the gnomes for the theft. Whether it works or not, I\'ve been paid for my time in coin and drink, which is all that matters.','Quests/TempleStreet/vlepos_plan.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5918,'Netherot Name Calling','Temple Street','Temple Street',10,1,'I\'ve offered my help to the arms dealer known as Shinska. She says that she wants to make her weapons magical, but the netherot chanters have blackballed her. I\'ve offered to kill two of them to teach them a lesson.',1360012,'I\'ve killed the netherot chanters for Shinska the arms dealer. She hopes that with a number of them dead, she\'ll be able to convince some other enchanters to make her weapons magical.','Quests/TempleStreet/netherot_name_calling.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5919,'Not Since the Invention of the Wheel...','Temple Street','Temple Street',7,1,'Zninki Flatzazzle has had one of his inventions stolen from him. He has asked me to collect it for him.',1360032,'I\'ve returned Zninki\'s Bread Bisector to him. He demonstrated the device to me, and I have to say I don\'t think I\'ve ever seen any invention greater than that.','Quests/TempleStreet/not_since_the_invention_of_the_wheel.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5920,'Improving The Design','Temple Street','Temple Street',10,1,'Sparzit, a gnome I met in Temple Street has another idea for his invention and he needs more help with it. I need to gather some samples of bone rot from Undead Pikemen for him. I\'m pretty sure I can find some in the Graveyard.',1360041,'Sparzit offered me some coin for my time that I spent collecting samples of bone rot for him.','Quests/TempleStreet/improving_the_design.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5921,'Keys For Sempronia','Temple Street','Temple Street',6,1,'I\'ve agreed to search through the sewers and find the diseased ratonga who has the old keys to the Freeport Reserve in the Temple Street district... then take them back.',1360020,'I\'ve returned the old vault keys to Sempronia the banker in the Temple Street district.','Quests/TempleStreet/keys_for_sempronia.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5922,'Frizi\'s Stolen Books','Temple Street','Temple Street',9,1,'Frizi the Scribe had some of her books stolen by the Guttersnipe in the Sprawl, and they planned on using them for... well, sanitary purposes.',1360053,'I\'ve killed the Dervish for Frizi. That should be enough to pay them back for stealing her books. Maybe I\'ll kill some more to sweeten the deal.','Quests/TempleStreet/frizis_stolen_books.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5923,'Frizi Figglesnip\'s Ingredients','Temple Street','Temple Street',10,1,'I have agreed to collect several ingredients for Frizi Figglesnip. The components are a glassy crab eye and a  scorpion stinger from the Sunken City and a adder fang  from the Ruins or Sprawl and lastly an oversized rat stomach from where ever.',1360053,'I gathered four ingredients for Frizi Figglesnip. When I returned them to her, she rewarded me with a pair of magical gloves.','Quests/TempleStreet/frizi_figglesnips_ingredients.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5924,'Krasa Isn\'t Taking It Anymore!','Temple Street','Temple Street',6,1,'Krasa the waitress in Temple Street has asked me to give a special message to Spezi who isn\'t supposed to be very far away. Apparently Krasa has a deep abiding hatred toward her sister.',1360040,'It seems Krasa has had a change of heart - at the last moment. Perhaps Krysa might actually live through the night.','Quests/TempleStreet/krasa_isnt_taking_it_anymore.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5925,'Makeup for Krysa','Temple Street','Temple Street',7,1,'Krysa, the entertainment at Pshavost\'s bar, has asked me to get her some more makeup from someone named Brashk.',1360042,'I told Krysa that Brashk didn\'t have any of the makeup and she had a conniption fit. I never even got my free drink!','Quests/TempleStreet/makeup_for_krysa.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5926,'An Enchanting Evening With Krysa','Temple Street','Temple Street',9,1,'I\'ve agreed to help Krysa again. She wants me to speak with some Erudite by the name of Raban. Supposedly this Erudite has something to do with making Krasa \"ugly\".',1360042,'Those three women have no idea how badly they\'re being played. Their vanity is so great that Raban the Erudite is playing them like little marionettes. It seems that Raban has been casting some type of special enchantment to make Krasa and Spezi ugly. I think it\'s best to not get involved at this point.','Quests/TempleStreet/an_enchanting_evening_with_krysa.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5927,'Natasha\'s Note','Graveyard','Graveyard',10,1,'It seems I have come across a bit of information while rummaging through a grave robber\'s corpse. It mentions something about a crypt and a meeting somewhere, and someone named Tarakh. I have no idea where the crypt or meeting spot is, but this Tarakh that is mentioned may find it valuable.',0,'Looks like I turned that worthless paper into a little coin. Tarakh wasn\'t happy the note contained so little information. Too bad for him.','Quests/Graveyard/natashas_note.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5928,'Shivo\'s Arcane Rod','The Sprawl','The Sprawl',10,1,'I have found an unusual magic rod on the corpse of a strange ratonga mage. I can\'t seem to make it do anything. I should probably find someone to show it to.',0,'It turns out the rod was originally the possession of Claudia Quart. The Great Shivo stole it from her some time ago. I returned the rod to Claudia for a reward.','Quests/TheSprawl/shivos_arcane_rod.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5929,'Eliminate Geraufl','World Event','World Event',30,1,'The note which Kath carried on her person told of a continued and determined effort to free Geraufl from the prison. It may be time to simply eliminate the froglok, rather than allow it to continue to fester and bring the simpering Qeynosians over in droves.',0,'My intentions were good, but I unfortunately failed in my mission to kill the froglok. He escaped the jail while I was stunned, likely fled into the sewers. Unfortunately, I suppose this may mean we\'ll start to see more of them in the future.','Quests/Freeport/AnIncriminatingLetter.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5930,'The Puzzled Tactician','World Event','The Lost Village of Kugup',35,1,'Timrek, the Froglok tactician, has been troubled by a logic puzzle and unable to work on formulating battle plans. I am going to attempt to help him solve the logic puzzle so he can get back to work!',1230001,'I solved the logic puzzle for Timrek.','Quests/TheLostVillageofKugup/the_puzzled_tactician.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5931,'A History Lesson','World Event','The Lost Village of Kugup',35,1,'Euurp the school teacher has given me a tome of Froglok History. I must read this tome and learn about the Froglok people. When I\'m finished, Euurp is going to test my knowledge.',1230006,'I\'ve passed the test! My knowledge of the Frogloks is immense.','Quests/TheLostVillageofKugup/a_history_lesson.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5932,'Staffing Up','World Event','The Lost Village of Kugup',35,1,'I am trying to find a nice, solid tree branch to give to Fruppen so he can start training to become a monk someday.',1230017,'I\'ve found a strong tree branch and given it to Fruppen so he can practice to be like his brother.','Quests/TheLostVillageofKugup/staffing_up.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5933,'Sprawl Giantslayer Sweep','The Sprawl','The Sprawl',6,1,'I\'ve been recruited to aid the Freeport Militia. Liege Aquila has ordered me to deal with a band of ruffians known as the Giantslayers here in the Sprawl.',8400018,'There are a few less Giantslayers in the Sprawl that will disrespect Freeport.  I have done as Liege Aquila had ordered.  I should return to him only if I desire to continue doing this sort of work.','Quests/TheSprawl/sprawl_giantslayer_sweep.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5934,'Sprawl Guttersnipe Sweep','The Sprawl','The Sprawl',6,1,'I\'ve been recruited to aid the Freeport Militia. Liege Aquila has ordered me to take care of a lively lot in the Sprawl that goes by the name of the Guttersnipe.',8400018,'I\'ve taken care of the dervishes here in the Sprawl, just like Liege Aquila asked.  I should return to him only if I desire to continue doing this sort of work. ','Quests/TheSprawl/sprawl_guttersnipe_sweep.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5935,'A Worthy Teacher','Scale Yard','Scale Yard',8,1,'Zekvila is having problems with her incantations and needs advice from an Erudite by the name of Raban. I should be able to find her in Stonestair Byway.',1390128,'Zekvila was outraged over the response she got from Raban. She even forgot to pay me. I don\'t think I should press the issue, though.','Quests/ScaleYard/a_worthy_teacher.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5936,'Uncovering the Froglok Secret','World Event','The Lost Village of Kugup',25,1,'I\'ve teleported into a hidden Froglok village. I am going to investigate the city and see if I can discover its secrets, and perhaps unlock the secret of the Frogloks.',0,'I\'ve completed all of the tasks for the Froglok villagers and spoken with Chief Kaorf. The Chief gave me a Talisman that I can use to find the village again someday.','Quests/TheLostVillageofKugup/uncovering_the_froglok_secret.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5937,'Will Fight for Fun','The Sprawl','The Sprawl',8,1,'I found a lock of hair in The Sprawl that obviously belongs to outsiders. Possible Qeynosian spies, perhaps! I must rid the city\'s outskirts of this threat!',0,'I\'ve culled the Sprawl of a potential threat. Their tears were satisfying as I cut them down!','Quests/TheSprawl/will_fight_for_fun.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5938,'Kallon\'s Vengeance','The Sinking Sands','The Sinking Sands',45,1,'Kallon Ebbtide has asked me to avenge his fallen comrades. This entails hunting down the bandit, named Fasul, who murdered his comrades and robbed them. He indicated that a guide in the crocodile hunter camp would be a good place to start.',730125,'I\'ve avenged Kallon\'s comrades by slaying Fasul and terrifying Jaza into submission. Kallon can now rest easy and work towards getting back to his homeland.','Quests/TheSinkingSands/kallons_revenge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5939,'Sewer Problem: A Gnome Solution','Thieves Way','Thieves Way',10,1,'Foreman Asprenus persuaded me to investigate the sewers concerning reports he has received about the recent increase in drain stoppages and overflows. He told me to contact Engineer Veebert who should be working on machinery down in the Thieves\' Way.',0,'I was able to get the key to Storage Room 303 where the gnomes have been storing their unstable Goo Grease. It looks like it is up to me to get into the room and take care of the problem.','Quests/ThievesWay/sewer_problem_a_gnome_solution.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5940,'Fight the Invaders','Montaa XP','Thunderdome',2,1,'Bubbles has asked me to help fight off the invading goblins. He says they can be found right behind him.',3250014,'Bubbles was happy with my efforts. He gave me a few coins for my efforts.','Quests/IsleofRefuge/fight_the_invaders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5942,'Attack of the Zombies','Stormhold','South Qeynos',15,1,'Undead from Stormhold have been emerging at night to scout the walls of Qeynos. Pupil Adept Wazzlefop of the Concordium has petitioned me to forestall a potential attack by slaying the zombie scouts.',415095,'The potential attack against Qeynos has been hindered now that I have slain a number of the undead knights.','Quests/SouthQeynos/attack_of_the_zombies.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5944,'Are You There, Tom? It\'s Me, Pona.','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',7,0,'I met Pona, a Kerran who now lives on the streets of Stonestair Byway ever since she lost her denmate. I\'ve offered to kill undead fighters in the Graveyard to exact revenge for her loss.',1350028,'','Quests/StoneStairByway/are_you_there_tom_its_me_pona.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5946,'Eviction!','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',8,0,'Zahar the Innkeeper has offered to rent out a place to me. The catch is that the place is currently being lived in by Galenus Vatia. If he doesn\'t have the rent money, then I can live there.',1350021,'','Quests/StoneStairByway/eviction.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5947,'Let Me Count The Ways...','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',12,1,'Tobial wants to impress a certain lady, but he is a coward at heart. He asks you to do the deed for him by killing ten Diseased Ratonga in the The Sprawl and return to him.',1350046,'Tobial accepted the ratonga and plans on giving them to Miala. I barely got my reward before he turned on me, as well.','Quests/StoneStairByway/let_me_count_the_ways.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5948,'Kazar\'s Focus','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',6,0,'I\'ve met an Erudite at a tavern in Stonestair Byway. He insulted me and told me to get his \'foci\' for him, as if I was nothing more than a simple errand runner! I\'ll get this foci for him... then break it.',1350038,'Kazar was infuriated that his foci wasn\'t done. That was worth the effort it took to do this for him. I even got a few coins from it.','Quests/StoneStairByway/kazars_focus.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5949,'Kazar and the Vial','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',8,0,'Kazar the Erudite wants me to pick up something for him from a crazy troll named Crantik. This \'vial of secretion\' supposedly will work for his ritual. Once I have it, I plan on breaking it in front of that condescending son-of-a-goo!',1350038,'Kazar was quite upset over not getting that vial. He even went so far as to threaten destroying this city if he couldn\'t complete his ritual today. I doubt he\'ll live long enough after what he said about the Kerrans.','Quests/StoneStairByway/kazar_and_the_vial.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5950,'Nosno\'s Prophecy','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',6,0,'Nosno the Naysayer preaches destruction of Norrath and the need to flee. I\'ve been asked to deliver these messages to all Kerran women, but I think I\'m just going to try speaking with two of them.',1350120,'Nosno seemed not to mind too much about the women turning him down. I think he\'s lost in his own world somewhere.','Quests/StoneStairByway/nosnos_prophecy.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5951,'The Contest','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',10,0,'Lirosi, the Kerran hunter, claimed I couldn\'t kill an orc. I\'m going to kill ten orcs and gather up their fingers to prove him wrong. That should do the trick.',1350000,'Lirosi was shocked that I managed to kill the orcs. He refused to acknowledge who the better hunter is.','Quests/StoneStairByway/the_contest.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5952,'Easy Acceptance','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',10,1,'Lirosi has offered me the \'Hunter\'s Mantle\' that was owned by his father. He said his brother is waiting to give it to me. Judging by the way he looks, I would assume his brother is one of those Dervish crooks out in the Sprawl. Lirosi must take me for a fool if he thinks I\'ll easily fall into this trap.',1350000,'I\'ve let Lirosi know I managed to find his bait, but the trap wasn\'t enough to finish me.','Quests/StoneStairByway/easy_acceptance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5954,'Jezrina\'s Prophecy','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',5,1,'Jezrina the seer claims that I have a destiny lurking about me, but she cannot see it. If I find and bring her a tumor infested heart from vermin, she may be able to tell me more. I may have to kill a number of them before I find one exactly as she needs.',1350031,'Jezrina is nothing more than a charlatan!! Were it not for the fact there are guards all around, I\'d kill her then and there. SHE MADE ME EAT THAT HEART!!! She will pay for this one day, I swear!','Quests/StoneStairByway/jezrinas_prophecy.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5955,'Rori\'s Proposal','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',8,1,'While slipping through the side streets in Stonestair Byway, I just happened to bump into the local tough guy, Rori. For some reason he thinks I can hook him up with Manny\'s gang based out of Beggar\'s Court. He says I should speak with Manius in the Sunken City.',1350034,'A thug by the name of Rori tried to enlist the help of some of the other scum in the districts to try and strengthen his gang. Looks like by the way things went he will be going on the lamb for a bit instead.','Quests/StoneStairByway/roris_proposal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5956,'Rori\'s Back','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',10,1,'Poor Rori is at it again. He got lucky... he dodged the blade that Crispen had been sharpening for him! Now he wants me to go and kill a bunch of orcs out in the Ruins for him? Guess this guy doesn\'t think he has enough enemies since he wants me to bring their hides back to him!',1350034,'Rori paid me for each of the hides and keeps mumbling that all of his problems will be solved now. Whatever, as long as I have my coins he can mumble to the bottom of the ocean for all I care. I guess I now know what that Erudite meant by a fool and his platinum...','Quests/StoneStairByway/roris_back.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5957,'Juma And Habika\'s Story','Stonestair Byway','Stonestair Byway',19,1,'Juma is in love with Habika, yet her parents have forced them apart. He would do anything to be with her, despite her parents\' stance in the matter, and he asked me to help him get back with Habika.',1350007,'I\'ve contacted Habika for Juma and he is pleased with the outcome. I\'m not usually the romantic type, but this kind of got to me. The reward didn\'t hurt, either.','Quests/StoneStairByway/juma_and_habikas_story.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5958,'Dismal Tidings','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'I\'ve offered my services to a high ranking member in the Church of Dismal Rage. She has asked me to investigate the old cemetery found deep in the Commonlands. According to her directions, it should be found west of the Freeport Gates.',1440071,'Soulinus in the Temple of War was rather upset when she heard that her reports were indeed true. She believes the Necromancers that study at the Academy of Arcane Sciences are involved with the situation, if not wholly responsible. She has asked me to undertake another task for her.','Quests/NorthFreeport/dismal_tidings.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5959,'The Mouth of Evil','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'Soulinus has now asked me to travel to the Wailing Caves and investigate the area for signs of undead. According to her, the Wailing Caves were once the site of a battle between the Freeport Militia and the undead. Soulinus wants to know if the undead have returned, this time by part of the necromancers of the Academy of Arcane Sciences.',1440071,'Soulinus is quite upset over the undead appearing in both the Old Cemetery and the Wailing Caves. I wasn\'t able to see far into the caves, but I\'m certain there are more inside.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_mouth_of_evil.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5960,'Gathering Brittle Bones','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'Augurer Valgus doubts the rage in my eyes. Valgus has tasked me with recovering bones from four brittle skeletons out in the Commonlands. I will show him I have the rage in my heart.',1440043,'I have gathered four brittle bones and have given them to Augurer Valgus. Apparently I took too long for them to be of substantial use. At least my time was compensated for.','Quests/NorthFreeport/gathering_brittle_bones.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5961,'The Mariner\'s Rhyme','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,0,'The Augurer of the Dismal Rage told me to seek out a sailor named Javvy in one of the taverns of Freeport. Javvy has an ancient mariner\'s rhyme that he is bringing to the Dismal Rage.',1440043,'I delivered the mariner\'s rhyme to the temple Augurer as agreed. He was quite pleased with it and promised to pray for my conversion. At least the pay was not bad.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_mariners_rhyme.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5962,'Message for Anessa','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'Augurer Valgus would like a very important message to be delivered to Anessa Bonefetter. Anessa can be found in a pub in West Freeport.',1440043,'I have delivered Augurer Valgus\'s message to Anessa Bonefetter. She sure didn\'t appreciate the effort I put into getting it to her.','Quests/NorthFreeport/message_for_anessa.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5965,'In Search of Spiritkeepers','West Freeport','West Freeport',17,2,'Lieutenant Darrius of the Freeport Militia has hired me to venture into the depths of Wailing Caves where I am to hunt down no less than some form of caster called a spiritkeeper. Their existence could all just be a myth, but I may as well check it out.',1680056,'I was hired by the Freeport Milita officer, Lieutenant Darrius, to hunt down rumored spiritkeepers in the Wailing Caves. I slew no less than five Ree spiritkeeprs and returned with their scalps as proof. For this service, I was paid handsomely.','Quests/WestFreeport/in_search_of_spiritkeepers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5966,'Key to Fallen Gate','Access Quest','North Freeport',18,1,'Kanos X\'aphon has tasked me to track down a key to a place called the Fallen Gate. He claims the gate is the entrance to the ancient home of the dark elves, a city called Neriak. If he is correct, there could be untold riches buried in the long-dead city.',1440080,'After slaying every Thexian in the building, I managed to get both a key for myself and Kanos. He certainly took his time in getting to the meeting, that\'s for certain. He\'s covered up the mess, but only at the cost of enlisting my services at an unnamed point in the future.','Quests/NorthFreeport/key_to_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5967,'The Lost Religion of Fallen Gate','North Freeport','North Freeport',25,6,'I have offered to help Drund Mordgraahl Skullsprain discover proof of a lost religion in the depths of Fallen Gate. I am searching for a religious artifact called the Gong of Uglan within the ruins of the foreign quarter. It is likely that I will find the artifact near the ruins of an arena.',1440018,'I offered to help Drund Mordgraahl Skullsprain in Freeport find relics of a lost religion in the depths of Fallen Gate. I found the Gong of Uglan and copied the glyphs written upon it. This will provide the Drunds with enough proof to request that the Dismal Rage organizes an expedition into Fallen Gate.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_lost_religion_of_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5969,'Vibias Wailing Cave Ingredients','North Freeport','North Freeport',13,1,'Vibia Valens has asked me to gather some ingredients from the Wailing Caves. The ingredients are two primordial seep glands and the venom sac of a spider named Soulspike.',1440065,'I have successfully collected two primordial seep bile samples and the venom sac from Soulspike the spider queen of the Wailing Caves. Vibia rewarded me with a dagger and some coin for a job well done.','Quests/NorthFreeport/vibias_wailing_cave_ingredients.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5970,'Graverobber Spoils','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'A rather unpleasant dark elf at the Temple of War would like me to dispatch some grave robbers that have been sacking the cemetery out in the Commonlands. He would like me to return with what they\'ve stolen.',1440056,'I eliminated the grave robbers and returned to the Temple of War with what they\'ve stolen. Missionary G\'Zule was less than grateful for my efforts, though it matters not for I received my reward.','Quests/NorthFreeport/graverobber_spoils.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5971,'Note for Lusius','No','North Freeport',10,1,'Scribe Jabir has asked me to deliver a message to banker Lusius Ulixes.',1440022,'I have delivered the message to banker Lusius Ulixes just as scribe Jabir wanted.','Quests/NorthFreeport/note_for_lusius.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5972,'Shipment for Jabir','North Freeport','North Freeport',10,1,'Scribe Jabir seems to be a very important person and he answers to even more important people. He needs me to get his shipment for him from merchant William in the Commonlands.',1440022,'I have retrieved scribe Jabir\'s shipment from merchant William. William was a coward and Jabir was happy to have his shipment back although he didn\'t show it.','Quests/NorthFreeport/shipment_for_jabir.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5973,'Golem Testing','North Freeport','North Freeport',19,1,'I must do field testing for Euphemius\'s Golem research.',1440033,'The golem field test was a success.','Quests/NorthFreeport/golem_testing.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5974,'Golem Research','North Freeport','North Freeport',24,1,'Euphemius Granius has asked that I travel to Fallen Gate to retrieve the remains of undead ogres and trolls to help further his golem research.',1440033,'I have delivered the required components to Euphemius Granius.','Quests/NorthFreeport/golem_research.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5975,'The Stein of Moggok:  It Can Be Rebuilt...','Heritage','East Freeport',40,3,'I learned of an old item that was last seen in the Age of Turmoil while talking to Rumdum Clurg in the Seafarer\'s Roost. I think I\'ll travel to the Feerrott and see what I can turn up concerning the Stein of Moggok.',1280030,'I was able to rebuild the Stein of Moggok! I\'ll be sure not to mention this to Rumdum...','Quests/EastFreeport/the_stein_of_moggok_it_can_be_rebuilt.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5976,'Armadillo Hides','South Freeport','South Freeport',10,1,'Merchant Nipius Malchus has told me that he and the armor makers of Freeport need 15 armadillo hides to help them make a better armor they are trying out.',1660027,'I have turned in the 15 armadillo hides that merchant Nipius Malchus wanted.','Quests/SouthFreeport/armadillo_hides.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5977,'Armor Delivery','South Freeport','South Freeport',10,1,'Merchant Nipius Malchus wants me to deliver some armor for him to Lieutenant Darrius. Darrius can be found at the militia house.',1660027,'I have given Lieutenant Darrius his armor crafted by Nipius.','Quests/SouthFreeport/armor_delivery.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5978,'Find Pythus the Rogue','South Freeport','South Freeport',14,1,'Sergeant Nominus has hired me to track down and slay a rogue operating in the area.',1660034,'I have found the rogue Pythus. Once found, he proved easy prey. Sergeant Nominus paid me well for my services.','Quests/SouthFreeport/find_pythus_the_rogue.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5979,'Hunting Henchmen','South Freeport','South Freeport',23,1,'Lucilla Quietus has explained that the murkwater henchmen have been increasing their lawbreaking activities and stealing her stuff. She has asked me to go to the Edgewater Drains and eliminate seven of them.',1660054,'Lucilla shouldn\'t have to worry about the murkwater henchmen stealing her stuff. Not after the dent I put in their resident population. That\'s what happens when you get caught.','Quests/SouthFreeport/hunting_henchmen.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5981,'Message for Merchant Valary','South Freeport','South Freeport',10,1,'Lucilla Quietus would like me to go into the Commonlands and deliver a message to merchant Valary at the Crossroads.',1660054,'I have delivered Lucilla\'s message to merchant Valary at the Crossroads in Commonlands.','Quests/SouthFreeport/message_for_merchant_valary.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5982,'Note for Sergius','South Freeport','South Freeport',10,1,'Clodia Laeca would like a very personal letter delivered to Sergius Mordanticus.',1660028,'I have given Sergius the letter from Clodia Laeca, he was not too happy to receive it.','Quests/SouthFreeport/note_for_sergius.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5983,'Offerings of the Faithful','South Freeport','South Freeport',10,1,'Clara Maius has charged me with the task of collecting three offerings from the faithful. I need to find the people and gather their offerings to the Dismal Rage.',1660037,'Clara conned me into collecting offerings for Dismal Rage from people who didn\'t sound like they were too happy to offer these donations. She didn\'t even give me a reward for my help.','Quests/SouthFreeport/offerings_of_the_faithful.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5984,'Speckled Rattler Profit','South Freeport','South Freeport',8,1,'I\'ve struck a bargain with merchant Clodia, speckled rattler skins for currency. I\'ll collect as many as I can from the Commonlands and see what price they bring.',1660028,'That\'s one sharp merchant. Right after I get paid for my part, she tries to get me to spend it on her wares. I\'ll bet she\'s one of the more profitable merchants here in Freeport.','Quests/SouthFreeport/speckled_rattler_profit.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5985,'The Crossroads','East Freeport','East Freeport',10,1,'I met a well-to-do citizen of Freeport who used to live at the Crossroads out in the Commonlands. I might want to check out the place if I ever find myself traveling outside of Freeport.',1280045,'The Crossroads is as desolate as Asprenus had said it was. I don\'t know why anyone would want to live out here with dangers lurking behind every bush.','Quests/EastFreeport/the_crossroads.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5986,'Dalals Message','East Freeport','East Freeport',10,1,'I\'ve been given a job by Dalal Akilia. All I have to do is deliver this note to someone named Nyjuss. All the note says is - \"The seabirds will be roosting for the winter. Everyone knows they\'re the fairest of all game\".',1280010,'Dalal Akilia has given an odd message to Nyjuss. The message pertained to seabirds roosting, and I\'m not sure what it meant. This is something I might want to look into at a later time.','Quests/EastFreeport/dalals_message.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5987,'Delivery to the Crossroads','East Freeport','East Freeport',8,1,'I have been sent on an errand by Viducius Festus. He wants me to deliver a package to merchant Valary at the Crossroads Village in the Commonlands.',1280098,'I was sent on an errand to deliver a package to the Crossroads Village. I found the village and delivered the package to merchant Valary. In exchange, I received some coin, but something seemed suspicious. I will remember this encounter.','Quests/EastFreeport/delivery_to_the_crossroads.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5988,'Kill the Giantslayers','East Freeport','East Freeport',8,1,'It seems that the Giantslayer gang has been running amok, and Julie Danerous would like me to slay ten of them. I have accepted this task and can find them in the Sprawl.',1280214,'I\'ve confronted the Giantslayers and taught them that it\'s not nice to steal coin or life, by slaying ten of their kind.','Quests/EastFreeport/kill_the_giantslayers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5989,'Kouryick\'s Missing Cargo','East Freeport','East Freeport',22,1,'I met a drunk Seafury by the name of Kouryick. He told me a Seafury ship went down off the coast of the Nektulos Forest and asked me to recover some lost cargo he suspects is in the hands of Nerius pirates.',1280093,'After returning the recovered manifest to Kouryick, he rewarded me well. But I heard him mumble something that makes me suspect he was actually in league with those Nerius marauders somehow.','Quests/EastFreeport/kouryicks_missing_cargo.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5990,'Message for Boomba','East Freeport','East Freeport',8,1,'Annia Velithe needs help delivering a message to Boomba, who can be found near the gate to the Commonlands.',1280118,'I have delivered Annia Velithe\'s message to Boomba, who I found near the gate to the Commonlands. He paid me with a few coins and a nice lunch.','Quests/EastFreeport/message_for_boomba.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5991,'Message for Mallius','East Freeport','East Freeport',8,1,'Julie Danerous would like me to take a message on her behalf to Mallius Otho.',1280214,'I have delivered Julie Danerous\'s message to Mallius Otho. Mallius sells bows.','Quests/EastFreeport/message_for_mallius.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5992,'Message for Sergius','East Freeport','East Freeport',10,1,'Sirraw Swiftpaw needs help delivering a message to Sergius Mordanticus who can be found outside the militia house.',1280019,'I have delivered Sirraw Swiftpaw\'s message to Sergius Mordanticus.','Quests/EastFreeport/message_for_sergius.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5993,'Putting Zombies to Rest','East Freeport','East Freeport',10,1,'Sergeant Typhoeus has basically dared me to go to the Graveyard and slay twelve putrid zombies. I am not afraid and I will do this without a problem.',1280021,'I have slain twelve putrid zombies in the Graveyard.','Quests/EastFreeport/putting_zombies_to_rest.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5994,'Scribe Zizwold\'s List','East Freeport','East Freeport',25,1,'Scribe Zizwold has seemingly mistaken me for someone else. He has given me a list with detailed instructions regarding items he needs. Although I am not the courier he thinks me to be, I could gather the items on the list and receive the payment he mentioned. I just need to collect one perfect owlbear feather, five shimmering blue wings and five leaper blood hairs in Nektulos.',1280056,'Scribe Zizwold mistook me for a servant of his client and gave me a list with details about some items he needed. Although I was not the courier he thought me to be, I gathered the items on the list and received payment for my troubles.','Quests/EastFreeport/scribe_zizwolds_list.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5995,'Sewer Problem: A Gnome Solution','East Freeport','East Freeport',22,1,'Foreman Asprenus persuaded me to investigate the sewers concerning reports he has received about the recent increase in drain stoppages and overflows. He told me to contact Engineer Veebert who should be working on machinery down in the Thieves\' Way.',1280045,'I was able to get the key to Storage Room 303 where the gnomes have been storing their unstable Goo Grease. It looks like it is up to me to get into the room and take care of the problem.','Quests/EastFreeport/sewer_problem_a_gnome_solution.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5996,'Typhoeus\' Blackmail','East Freeport','East Freeport',11,1,'I said the wrong thing to the wrong Sergeant. Now if I don\'t head out to the Commonlands and take care of his orc problem, I\'ll be the one with the problem. I\'m to bring him their tattered armor as proof.',1280021,'I\'ve returned to Sergeant Typhoeus with the tattered orc armor as proof. I should be more careful of what I say to the militia in the future.','Quests/EastFreeport/typhoeuss_blackmail.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5997,'In Search of the Feerrott','East Freeport','East Freeport',34,1,'While in Freeport I came across an ogre who wants to find the Rallosian homeland, the Feerrott. I chose to aid the ogre in her quest. There is no telling what treasure awaits.',1280068,'With much running about Zek we found a map to the Feerrott. Now the real adventure begins.','Quests/EastFreeport/in_search_of_the_feerrott.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5998,'Aelia and the Butcher','West Freeport','West Freeport',10,1,'Aelia Catus wants me to visit Julia Florens and remind her of an outstanding loan debt. I have been directed to the merchant\'s location and will need to return with her reply. Aelia Catus promised that I would be handsomely rewarded for my part in this extortion.',1680046,'Aelia Catus paid me to give Julia Florens a threatening reminder of debts owed. I\'m not sure of Julia Floren\'s affiliations, but hopefully this won\'t be held against me. After all, I was just the messenger.','Quests/WestFreeport/aelia_and_the_butcher.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(5999,'Head of Marius','West Freeport','West Freeport',15,1,'I\'ve been conscripted to serve the Freeport militia. Another way to put it is I\'ve offered to do Darrius\'s work for him. I\'m to go to Thieves\' Way, find the felon Marius and retrieve stolen goods and his head.',1680056,'That\'s gratitude for you. I do the Freeport militia a favor and all they can do is complain about the way I did it. I retrieved the stolen goods and brought back Marius\'s head... So they were in the same sack, big deal.','Quests/WestFreeport/head_of_marius.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6000,'Killing Bats','West Freeport','West Freeport',10,1,'Sergius Mordanticus wants me to cull the numbers of the bat swarms out in the Commonlands. Supposedly the bats are randomly attacking people.',1680144,'I went to the Commonlands and killed ten of the swarm bats as requested by Sergius Mordanticus.','Quests/WestFreeport/killing_bats.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6001,'The Marauder Eye Patches','West Freeport','West Freeport',23,1,'After foolishly approaching the second mate of the Seafury Buccaneers, Anessa Bonefetter, I have been spared a beating from her bodyguard and instead have been hired to hunt Nerius marauders along the ashy beaches of Nektulos. She must have noticed something special in me.',1680158,'Anessa Bonefetter, the second mate of the Seafury Buccaneers, hired me to slay six Nerius marauders in order to obtain six of their marauder eye patches. She paid me quite well for my services.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_marauder_eye_patches.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6002,'Message for Lollia','West Freeport','West Freeport',10,1,'Anessa Bonefetter, eager to offer employment, would like me to deliver a message to Scribe Lollia Parnesius.',1680158,'I\'ve delivered the message to Lollia Parnesius and all I got was grief for the messages timeliness.','Quests/WestFreeport/message_for_lollia.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6003,'Message for Typhoeus','West Freeport','West Freeport',10,1,'Anessa Bonefetter would like me to deliver a message to Sergeant Typhoeus. The Sergeant can be found on the docks.',1680158,'I\'ve delivered the message to Sergeant Typhoeus at the docks.','Quests/WestFreeport/message_for_typhoeus.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6004,'Trials of the Soldier','West Freeport','West Freeport',10,1,'In order to gain a deeper understanding of what the Freeport Militia does for the city, Sergius Mordanticus has ordered me to kill ten orcs and return for your reward.',1680144,'In order to gain a deeper understanding of what the Freeport Militia does for the city, Sergius Mordanticus ordered me to kill ten orcs. When I returned to him after completing this task, he awarded me with some coin, ale, and offered me the opportunity to learn more about the Militia\'s duties.','Quests/WestFreeport/trials_of_the_soldier.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6005,'Averus, Part I','West Freeport','West Freeport',12,1,'I met an individual by the name of Averus Justarius. Instead of getting into a fight with him, I\'ve actually struck a deal with the half-elf. It seems he has a plan that involves a place in the Commonlands called the Wailing Caves.',1680136,'I\'ve gone into the Wailing Caves and scoped out the place for Averus. According to the stories, the place should be littered with undead exclusively, but I think I saw a few living orcs in there.','Quests/WestFreeport/averus_part_i.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6006,'Averus, Part II','West Freeport','West Freeport',13,1,'Averus has come up with a way to make even more money. I need to kill living orcs inside the Wailing Caves and bring something proving I have killed them.',1680136,'I\'ve managed to find proof that there are living orcs in the Wailing Caves.','Quests/WestFreeport/averus_part_ii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6007,'Averus, Part III','West Freeport','West Freeport',13,1,'Averus has come up with yet another plan on making money. I\'m now off to find an orcish fugitive wanted by the Seafuries. It seems his bounty is still available.',1680136,'I\'ve brought Averus the head of Garreg Stonecrusher.','Quests/WestFreeport/averus_part_iii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6008,'Averus, Part IV','West Freeport','West Freeport',14,1,'Averus Justarius believes he has found a perfect way of making some cold, hard coin. After all of the work I\'ve done, I hope he\'s right.',1680136,'Averus has the audacity to claim he\'s done most of the work in our ventures together. He has kept the lion\'s share of the money, leaving me with a piddling amount of coin as my share. If there\'s ever a way for me to pay him back, so to say, I most defintely will.','Quests/WestFreeport/averus_part_iv.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6009,'Varski, Part I','West Freeport','West Freeport',21,1,'I\'ve met a ratonga named Varski. He claims to be a fan of mine and through much persuasion, he\'s offered me a suggestion on something I can find in Fallen Gate. If I bring these items back to him, he claims he can make them into something else.',1680189,'Varski held true to his word and has made me a bronzed club from the two things I\'ve brought him. His hands were moving so fast, I was unable to see how he made the club.','Quests/WestFreeport/varski_part_i.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6010,'Varski, Part II','West Freeport','West Freeport',23,1,'Varski seems to know a lot more about Fallen Gate than I had originally thought. He has sent me after several objects in Fallen Gate, being even more specific than last time. I wonder what he\'ll make from these objects?',1680189,'I\'m beginning to distrust this little rat. After giving him three obviously magical objects, all he managed to turn them into was a gilded crown! The thing isn\'t even made from real gold. Then again, he\'s using some weird kind of magic to make these things, so I shouldn\'t distrust him too much.','Quests/WestFreeport/varski_part_ii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6011,'Varski, Part III','West Freeport','West Freeport',22,1,'I\'ve agreed to get one last thing for the ratonga, Varski. He claims this one will be the best, but rather dangerous. I\'ll give this rat one last chance.',1680189,'Varski used a tradeskill technique I\'ve never seen before. He turned the mithril key into an earrings by putting it into one pocket and pulling it out of another. I still don\'t know how it changed from mithril to pyrite.','Quests/WestFreeport/varski_part_iii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6012,'Varski, Part IV','West Freeport','West Freeport',25,1,'I finally figured out who Varski is! He\'s the ratonga who helped Averus make all that money! Instead of that guy getting rich, I\'m going straight to the source! Varski has confessed he knows how to make BIG money and told me where it is!',1680189,'Varski used his magic one last time to make the golden ingot weigh less. The little rat turned it into the size of a coin. I\'m fairly certain there\'s something else going on here.','Quests/WestFreeport/varski_part_iv.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6013,'Free the Decaying Deadlings','East Freeport','East Freeport',10,1,'Sirraw Swiftpaw wants me to head to the Sunken City and lay to rest six of the decaying deadlings that roam the streets.',1280019,'I have laid to rest six of the decaying deadlings in the Sunken City, just as Sirraw Swiftpaw requested.','Quests/EastFreeport/free_the_decaying_deadlings.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6014,'Cold Forged Armor - Part I','East Freeport','East Freeport',20,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me for my services in collecting these ingredients with some specially made armor.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with a pair of gauntlets using his cold forged technique for collecting some cold grave dust and \"delivering a message\" to an Anders Blackhammer he didn\'t seem to care much for.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_i.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6015,'Cold Forged Armor - Part II','East Freeport','East Freeport',21,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me with a pair of bracers for my services in collecting these ingredients with some specially made armor.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with a pair of cold forged bracers for collecting some ethereal plating, uncorroded metal, and snake skins.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_ii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6016,'Cold Forged Armor - Part III','East Freeport','East Freeport',22,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me with a pair of boots for my services in collecting these ingredients with some specially made armor.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with a pair of cold forged boots for collecting ogre zombie hearts and the spiked collars from the constructs of malice within The Fallen Gate.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_iii.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6017,'Cold Forged Armor - Part IV','East Freeport','East Freeport',23,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me with new armor to protect my shoulders if I collect these ingredients for him.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with new armor for my shoulders after collecting some new tools.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_iv.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6018,'Cold Forged Armor - Part V','East Freeport','East Freeport',24,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me with new greaves if I collect these ingredients for him.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with a pair of cold forged greaves for collecting beaver pelts, corroded chainmail, hard shell plates from Nerius crabs, and Teir\'Dal greaves from a member of the Gul\'Thex Elite Guard.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_v.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6019,'Cold Forged Armor - Part VI','East Freeport','East Freeport',25,1,'Dyric Pire has asked me to collect ingredients he needs to make some special armor. He\'s agreed to pay me with new chest armor if I collect these ingredients for him.',1280012,'Dyric has paid me with a cold forged chest piece for collecting fairy wings, essence of calling from ashland wisps, corroded shields, and a shipment of high quality steel.','Quests/EastFreeport/cold_forged_armor__part_vi.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6020,'Ripe for the Picking','City Tasks','North Qeynos',11,1,'Gnoll bandits have been ambushing refugees who venture out into Antonica. Squire-Guard Williamson of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to remove this menace by slaughtering the Darkpaws.',2220036,'The new refugees should find safer Antonica now that I have slaughtered a number of the gnolls.','Quests/NorthQeynos/ripe_for_the_picking.lua',0,1,1000,2000,0),
(6021,'The Supply Lines','City Tasks','North Qeynos',14,1,'Bears have been mauling the fruit vendors who deliver produce from Antonica to Qeynos. Squire-Guard Williamson of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to protect the merchants by destroying the ravenous kodiaks.',2220036,'The path is safer for fruit merchants to journey between Antonica and the city now that I have destroyed a number of bears.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_supply_lines.lua',0,1,1000,2000,1),
(6022,'Champion of the Refugees','City Tasks','North Qeynos',15,1,'Refugees have been stumbling into Stormhold only to be butchered by the undead patrols. Squire-Guard Williamson of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to protect the adventurers by slaying the skeleton sentries.',2220036,'The threat to the refugees has been reduced now that I have slain a number of the undead sentries.','Quests/NorthQeynos/champion_of_the_refugees.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6023,'Unsettling Developments','City Tasks','North Qeynos',16,1,'Decaying creatures from Stormhold are clawing a tunnel through to the Qeynos Catacombs. Squire-Guard Williamson of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to slow their advancement by destroying the zombie diggers.',2220036,'The digging operation has been slowed now that I have destroyed a number of zombie workers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/unsettling_developments.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6024,'Slimed!','City Tasks','North Qeynos',18,1,'Rancid goos have been creeping out from the depths of Stormhold to drain the moisture from Antonica. Squire-Guard Williamson of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to kill the goos before the farmlands turn into desert.',2220036,'The sapping of moisture from the farmlands has been disrupted now that I have killed a number of the putrid goos.','Quests/NorthQeynos/slimed.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6025,'Earth and Water','City Tasks','North Qeynos',30,1,'Reports from the Orcish Wastes describe the outpost as under continuous fire from Deathfist catapults. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to end this siege by destroying the catapult operators.',2220043,'Excursions into the Orcish Wastes have resumed now that I have destroyed a number of the orcish engineers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/earth_and_water.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6026,'The Gathering Shadows','City Tasks','North Qeynos',33,1,'Deathfist legionnaires have been massing along the shores of the Orcish Wastes in preparation for an invasion of Qeynos. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to slaughter the orc raiders before they launch an assault against the city.',2220043,'The Deathfist army has been scattered now that I have slaughtered a number of Zek grunts.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_gathering_shadows.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6027,'No One Sees Us','City Tasks','North Qeynos',34,1,'Scouts commissioned to map the frontiers have encountered lurking danger from giant adders. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to defend the surveyors by killing dust snakes within the Orcish Wastes.',2220043,'The poisonous attacks against the explorers have slowed now that I have killed a number of vipers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/no_one_sees_us.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6028,'Sinew vs. Steel','City Tasks','North Qeynos',34,1,'Knights attempting to reach Deathfist Citadel have been repelled by burly orcish sentries. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to open a corridor for the adventurers by slaying Zek defenders within the Orcish Wastes.',2220043,'The crusaders have found easier their journeys to the Citadel now that I have slain a number of orc sentinels.','Quests/NorthQeynos/sinew_vs_steel.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6029,'Muzzle The Carnivores','City Tasks','North Qeynos',36,1,'Bears in search of food have been shredding the tents and pack mules of adventurers within the Orcish Wastes. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to defend the camps by destroying the marauding grizzlies.',2220043,'The attacks against explorers have slowed now that I have destroyed a number of the ravenous kodiaks.','Quests/NorthQeynos/muzzle_the_carnivores.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6030,'Blind To All Else','City Tasks','North Qeynos',36,1,'Monks attempting to reach Deathfist Citadel by crossing the mountain peaks have encountered fierce resistance from Sullon outpost defenders. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to create a diversion, drawing the guards out of position, by slaughtering orc centurions within the Orcish Wastes.',2220043,'The mountain passes have been left lightly patrolled now that I have slaughtered a number of the Zek legionnaires.','Quests/NorthQeynos/blind_to_all_else.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6031,'Legacy of Xanuusus','City Tasks','North Qeynos',37,1,'Chaos treants within the Orcish Wastes have been calling down lightning upon the trees and brush, sparking fires that scorch the steppes. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to kill the rotting deadwoods before an inferno consumes the outpost.',2220043,'The incidence of forest blazes has been reduced now that I have killed a number of the treant fiends.','Quests/NorthQeynos/legacy_of_xanuusus.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6032,'The Roar of the Colossal','City Tasks','North Qeynos',38,1,'Spies report that Deathfist Citadel is building giant barges to transport siege towers, catapults, and troops to the shores of Antonica. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to disrupt the assembly of these rafts by killing Sullon loggers within the Orcish Wastes.',2220043,'Construction of the barges has halted now that I have killed a number of the orc laborers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_roar_of_the_colossal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6033,'Underneath The Bridge','City Tasks','North Qeynos',39,1,'Scouts attempting to approach Deathfist Citadel undetected by way of the surrounding rivers and streams have found themselves attacked by schools of vicious piranhas. Sergeant Ironcast of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to assist the rangers by destroying the ferocious needlefish within the Orcish Wastes.',2220043,'The scouts have found it easier to reach the Citadel now that I have destroyed a number of the razortooth piranhas.','Quests/NorthQeynos/underneath_the_bridge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6034,'We Pruned the Hedges','City Tasks','North Qeynos',40,1,'Explorers attempting to return from the darkest corners of the Feerrott have been unable to pass through swamps infested with mature gutterbeasts. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to rescue the trapped adventurers by slaughtering the pusblooms.',2220044,'Some of the explorers have managed to escape the jungle now that I have slaughtered a number of the fetid guttermaws.','Quests/NorthQeynos/we_pruned_the_hedges.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6035,'It\'s Just Your Imagination','City Tasks','North Qeynos',41,1,'Swamp adders have been ambushing and drowning refugees commissioned to harvest pearls from the rivers of the Feerrott. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to remove this threat by killing the giant snakes.',2220044,'Fortune seekers have found safer the jungle streams now that I have killed a number of the vipers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/its_just_your_imagination.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6036,'Unspeakable Malice','City Tasks','North Qeynos',42,1,'Adventurers attempting to reach the Temple of Cazic-Thule have receded in terror from the depraved abominations that guard the ruins. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to serve as a heroic example by slaying the manticores within the Feerrott.',2220044,'Qeynosians have been inspired to continue their assaults against the Temple of Cazic-Thule now that I have slain a number of manticore dreadclaws.','Quests/NorthQeynos/unspeakable_malice.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6037,'It Is the Soldier','City Tasks','North Qeynos',43,1,'Frightened peasants have reported the sudden presence of horrific, nocturnal beasts within Antonica. The source of this vile summoning has been traced to thoughtbleeder wraiths, the vassals of Thule, within the Feerrott. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to destroy these fiendish regents before all of Antonica is consumed by darkness and fear.',2220044,'The sightings of Thulian monstrosities have waned now that I have destroyed a number of the wraith lords.','Quests/NorthQeynos/it_is_the_soldier.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6038,'Pillars of Perseverance','City Tasks','North Qeynos',43,1,'Legionnaires commissioned by Queen Antonia to expunge the minions of terror from the Temple of Cazic-Thule have found it impossible to defeat the living statues that patrol the gates. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to weaken the temple defenses by slaughtering animated guardians within the Feerrott.',2220044,'The siege against the Temple of Cazic-Thule has intensified now that I have slaughtered a number of the statues.','Quests/NorthQeynos/pillars_of_perseverance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6039,'First the Fin, Then the Head','City Tasks','North Qeynos',45,1,'Soldiers and Scouts dispatched to hold our interests in Everfrost are short of supplies, they do enjoy sharkfin soup though. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to resupply the soldiers and scouts of Everfrost with the ingredients needed for sharkfin soup.',2220044,'The bellys of the soldiers and scouts are now warm and toasty with their fresh supply of shark parts.','Quests/NorthQeynos/first_the_fin_then_the_head.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6040,'Not As Convincing','City Tasks','North Qeynos',45,1,'Disguised Bitterwind scouts have been dispatched to infiltrate our camps around Everfrost. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to kill the Bitterwind pioneers at their source within Everfrost before the entirety of our camps is known to them.',2220044,'The secrets of Qeynos have remained secure now that I have killed a number of the Bitterwind pioneers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/not_as_convincing.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6041,'Squishiness','City Tasks','North Qeynos',46,1,'Winter clothing is in short supply for out soldiers in Everfrost, but animals with strong wintercoats are not. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to resupply the local artisans with good wool from the bighorned dashers.',2220044,'The soldiers stationed in the Everfrost area are warmer now with their new winterclothing.','Quests/NorthQeynos/squishiness.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6042,'Without Due Process','City Tasks','North Qeynos',47,1,'Emissaries sent to negotiate peace with the giants of Permafrost have been slain by the icy undead. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to avenge the representatives by slaughtering the icy shivers within Everfrost.',2220044,'The emissaries have been avenged now that I have slaughtered a number of the icy shivers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/without_due_process.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6043,'Until the End','City Tasks','North Qeynos',48,1,'Minions of Thule are gathering to perform a sacrifice, intended to unleash eternal darkness upon Qeynos. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to prevent this ritual from completing by slaying the amygdalans within the Temple of Cazic-Thule.',2220044,'The dangerous rituals have been interrupted, and Qeynos stands for another day, now that I have slain a number of the arms of Thule.','Quests/NorthQeynos/until_the_end.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6044,'Columns of Steam','City Tasks','North Qeynos',48,1,'Galebreaker pilgrims have been causing the waters of Everfrost to boil, preventing adventurers from progressing through the tundra. Knight-Captain Steelgaze of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to quiet the waters by killing Galebreaker pilgrims within Everfrost.',2220044,'The waters of Everfrost have subsided and calmed now that I have killed a number of the Galebreakers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/columns_of_steam.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6045,'Pestilence','City Tasks','North Qeynos',11,1,'Darkpaw seers have been conjuring insects and disease to pollute the streams that flow from Antonica into Qeynos. Caretaker Nogfizzle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to cleanse the water supply by slaying the gnoll mystics.',2220133,'The streams that flow into Qeynos have been cleansed of filth and sickness now that I have slain a number of the gnoll seers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/pestilence.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6046,'Disturbing the Dead','City Tasks','North Qeynos',14,1,'Giant badgers have been digging up graves within Antonica, releasing skeletons and spirits that attack adventurers. Caretaker Nogfizzle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to end these unearthings of the dead by killing badgers.',2220133,'The graves have been protected from disturbances now that I have killed a number of badgers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/disturbing_the_dead.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6047,'Scatter the Bones','City Tasks','North Qeynos',15,1,'Undead squires have been organizing around Stormhold to move against Qeynos. Caretaker Nogfizzle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to remove this threat before the skeleton army is large enough to attack the city.',2220133,'The skeleton army has been scattered now that I have destroyed a number of forsaken squires.','Quests/NorthQeynos/scatter_the_bones.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6048,'Wasteland','City Tasks','North Qeynos',17,1,'Filth from the corrupted zombies of Stormhold has oozed up through the earth and sterilized the farmlands of Antonica. Caretaker Nogfizzle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to purify the soil by slaying zombies.',2220133,'The farmlands have been cleansed of filth now that I have slain a number of decaying zombies.','Quests/NorthQeynos/wasteland.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6049,'The Path of Enlightenment','City Tasks','North Qeynos',17,1,'Temple representatives attempting to locate the source of power within Stormhold have encountered resistance from skeleton guards. Caretaker Nogfizzle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to thin the undead defenses by slaughtering the defiled knights.',2220133,'The path has been cleared for crusaders to explore Stormhold now that I have slaughtered a number of undead knights.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_path_of_enlightenment.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6050,'The Stuff of Screams','City Tasks','North Qeynos',21,1,'Zealous scarecrows have been forcing settlers to flee their farms in Thundering Steppes, allowing weeds and thorned vines to infest the fields. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to cleanse the farmlands by destroying the scarecrow invaders.',2220144,'The fields have been cleared for the return of the farmers now that I have destroyed a number of scarecrows.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_stuff_of_screams.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6051,'Crush the Horde','City Tasks','North Qeynos',22,1,'Undead brigades have been laying siege to the gates of Qeynos. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to slay these skeleton invaders at their source in Thundering Steppes.',2220144,'The undead assaults against Qeynos have slowed now that I have slain a number of the skeleton attackers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/crush_the_horde.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6052,'Hallowed Vengeance','City Tasks','North Qeynos',24,1,'Temple acolytes returning from Thundering Steppes have reported encounters with brutal undead warriors. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to thin the ranks of these legions by killing skeleton soldiers.',2220144,'The undead menace has been reduced now that I have killed a number of skeleton warriors.','Quests/NorthQeynos/hallowed_vengeance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6053,'Under Pressure','City Tasks','North Qeynos',23,1,'The growing volume of animated corpses trapped within the Qeynos catacombs has alarmed the Temple of Life. Were the blighted hordes to break free from their tomb the city might well fall. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me forestall such a scenario by destroying undead within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220144,'The threat of an undead attack from the catacombs has been reduced now that I have destroyed a number of the blighted creatures.','Quests/NorthQeynos/under_pressure.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6054,'Defend the Acolytes','City Tasks','North Qeynos',26,1,'Temple attendants returning from descents into the catacombs have described opposition from burning skeletons. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to clear a path for the acolytes by slaying these undead warlocks within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220144,'The attendants should find easier their adventures through the catacombs now that I have slain a number of the skeletal sorcerers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/defend_the_acolytes.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6055,'Bedlam','City Tasks','North Qeynos',27,1,'The groans of despair rising from the catacombs are engendering fear and pessimism within the citizens of Qeynos. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to clear this cloud of gloom by killing agonized souls within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220144,'Qeynosians should find their minds and spirits cleared of despair now that I have killed a number of the tortured undead.','Quests/NorthQeynos/bedlam.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6056,'Fight It, Fight It, Fight It','City Tasks','North Qeynos',29,1,'Bloodsabers have at night been slithering up from the catacombs to recruit refugees into their organization. Disciple Telas\'velle of the Celestial Watch has urged me to remove this temptation by slaughtering the fanatics within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220144,'The noxious influence of the Bloodsabers has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the recruiters.','Quests/NorthQeynos/fight_it_fight_it_fight_it.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6057,'Happiness in Zealotry','City Tasks','North Qeynos',32,1,'Deathfist Citadel has conscripted the nymphs within the Orcish Wastes and threatened to unleash their corrupted magic against the walls of Qeynos. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to disrupt the orcish plans by destroying chaos nymphs.',2220160,'The Deathfist Orcs have found their army insufficient to besiege the city now that I have destroyed a number of nymph frenzies.','Quests/NorthQeynos/happiness_in_zealotry.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6058,'Starvation','City Tasks','North Qeynos',33,1,'The acolytes of Zek have been harvesting ingredients in preparation for the summoning of a Deathfist champion to the Orcish Wastes. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to slay the zealots before the ritual is completed.',2220160,'The orcs have been unable to gather sufficient resources for the summoning now that I have slain a number of Zek enthusiasts.','Quests/NorthQeynos/starvation.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6059,'The Dark Prowlers','City Tasks','North Qeynos',33,1,'Temple ambassadors attempting to establish a shrine within the Orcish Wastes have endured nightly attacks from great cats. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to protect the evangelists by killing gorge lionesses.',2220160,'The aggressions against the acolytes have slowed now that I have killed a number of night huntresses.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_dark_prowlers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6060,'Bloodlust of Zek','City Tasks','North Qeynos',34,1,'The Fury of Rallos has descended upon the Orcish Wastes, infecting the beasts with rage and frenzy. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to cleanse the lands by slaughtering corrupted grizzlies.',2220160,'The grip of Zek has been loosened now that I have slaughtered a number of the enraged bears.','Quests/NorthQeynos/bloodlust_of_zek.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6061,'Garden in the Shade','City Tasks','North Qeynos',36,1,'Temple seers have determined that a lost ship filled with Erollisian artifacts was scuttled off the coast of the Feerrott. Gnomish divers hired to locate the shipwreck have been swarmed by ravenous manta rays. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to protect the treasure hunters by destroying the devilfish.',2220160,'The search for the lost artifacts of Marr has resumed now that I have destroyed a number of the mantas.','Quests/NorthQeynos/garden_in_the_shade.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6062,'Sulfuric Sputterings','City Tasks','North Qeynos',37,1,'Putrid guttermaws have been churning grime and rot into the misty air of the Feerrott. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to kill the pestilence blooms before the jungle denizens are choked to death by the foulness.',2220160,'The stench and filth have begun to lift now that I have killed a number of the lesser pusbeasts.','Quests/NorthQeynos/sulfuric_sputterings.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6063,'The Seed of Morell-Thule','City Tasks','North Qeynos',37,1,'Temple emissaries sent to seek within the jungles of the Feerrott the forgotten worshippers of Zek have suffered vicious attacks from dread sattars. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to defend the acolytes by slaying vexed manticores.',2220160,'The aggressions against the missionaries have slowed now that I have slain a number of the enraged manticores.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_seed_of_morellthule.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6064,'Rise to the Challenge','City Tasks','North Qeynos',38,1,'Temple crusaders have discovered deep within the Feerrott an ancient shrine, guarded by savage ettin conscripts. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to clear a path to the island ruins by slaughtering the giant defenders.',2220160,'The paladins have resumed their assaults against the jungle temple now that I have slaughtered a number of the ettin guardians.','Quests/NorthQeynos/rise_to_the_challenge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6065,'Close Your Eyes','City Tasks','North Qeynos',38,1,'Rallosian acolytes have been preparing a bone sacrifice intended to reawaken the Avatar of War against Qeynos. Missionary Jenson of the Celestial Watch has urged me to disrupt these designs by destroying the undead adherents within the Feerrott.',2220160,'The ritual to unleash the force of Zek has been forestalled now that I have destroyed a number of the putrid ogre skeletons.','Quests/NorthQeynos/close_your_eyes.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6066,'In Defense of Meritocracy','City Tasks','North Qeynos',40,1,'Explorers attempting to navigate by raft the Anaconda River have found the waters impassably muddied by waste from sludge goos. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to ensure the flow of fresh water at its source by destroying festering beasts within the Temple of Cazic-Thule.',2220161,'The jungle rivers have begun to flow again now that I have destroyed a number of the putrid goos.','Quests/NorthQeynos/in_defense_of_meritocracy.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6067,'Know without Thinking','City Tasks','North Qeynos',40,1,'Temple acolytes charged with destroying the artifacts of dark power that seed the terrors within the Temple of Cazic-Thule have encountered fanatical resistance from Tae Ew berserkers. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to remove this obstacle by killing the lizardmen warriors.',2220161,'The disciples have found it easier to reach the inner catacombs now that I have killed a number of lizardmen guardians.','Quests/NorthQeynos/know_without_thinking.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6068,'Misery Unchained','City Tasks','North Qeynos',41,1,'Tae Ew ritualists have been capturing and torturing refugees in anticipation of a mass sacrifice intended to awaken the daughter of Thule. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to slaughter the lizardmen acolytes within the Temple of Cazic-Thule before waking nightmares are unleashed upon the Shattered Lands.',2220161,'The ritual to summon Terris-Thule has been interrupted now that I have slaughtered a number of the lizardmen embalmers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/misery_unchained.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6069,'The Abyss of Thule','City Tasks','North Qeynos',44,1,'Crusaders charged with destroying all worshippers of The Faceless have been succumbing to the hidden pit traps dug throughout the Temple of Cazic-Thule by giant spiders. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to remove this threat by slaying the fanged spiders.',2220161,'The avengers have found it easier to hunt the Thulian zealots now that I have slain a number of the spineslicer spiders.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_abyss_of_thule.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6070,'Through Fog and Filthy Air','City Tasks','North Qeynos',44,1,'Scouts commissioned to map the Temple of Cazic-Thule have been driven back by the stench emitted from toxic goos. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to reduce this pollution by killing the putrid slags.',2220161,'Qeynosian surveyors have reported the air as less offensive now that I have killed a number of the foul goos.','Quests/NorthQeynos/through_fog_and_filthy_air.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6071,'Second-Generation Gatherers','City Tasks','North Qeynos',45,1,'Harvesters searching for rare whistleroots within the caves of Everfrost have suffered paralyzing ambushes from giant wolves lurking in the snowy plains. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to ensure the collected herbs reach Qeynos by killing the ice wolves.',2220161,'Entrepreneurs have found it safer to explore the icy caverns now that I have killed a number of the ice wolves.','Quests/NorthQeynos/secondgeneration_gatherers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6072,'No Stranger to Enmity','City Tasks','North Qeynos',45,1,'Temple oracles attempting to discover the fate of Lady Vox have been forced back by the ice wolves patrolling the path to Permafrost. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to clear a path for the acolytes by slaughtering the ice wolves within Everfrost.',2220161,'The emissaries have been able to access Permafrost, and continue their search for the white dragon, now that I have slaughtered a number of the ice wolves.','Quests/NorthQeynos/no_stranger_to_enmity.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6073,'A Wonderland at Night','City Tasks','North Qeynos',46,1,'Adventurers attempting to locate the frozen dungeon of Permafrost have been buried beneath avalanches triggered by arctic wyrms within the mountain passes through Everfrost. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to protect the explorers by slaying the arctic wyrms.',2220161,'Fewer Qeynosians have been lost along the path to Permafrost now that I have slain a number of the arctic wyrms.','Quests/NorthQeynos/a_wonderland_at_night.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6074,'Read the Signs and Rejoice','City Tasks','North Qeynos',47,1,'Temple laborers seeking within the northern oceans the lost temples of Prexus have suffered brutal attacks at the hands of ice walkers. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to protect the excursion by destroying the ice walkers within Everfrost.',2220161,'Seers and divers have continued their dredging of the frozen seas now that I have destroyed a number of ice walkers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/read_the_signs_and_rejoice.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6075,'Tempest-Tossed','City Tasks','North Qeynos',48,1,'Drifting rafts overladen with refugees have been succumbing to the fierce giants that reside in Everfrost. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to shield the wayward vessels by killing the Kromise hermits.',2220161,'Fewer refugees have perished in the arctic waters now that I have killed a number of the Kromise hermits.','Quests/NorthQeynos/tempesttossed.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6076,'Submerged in Terror','City Tasks','North Qeynos',49,1,'Sunken Halasians have attacked Temple representatives attempting to recover artifacts lost with the sinking of a merchant ship during the Shattering. Partisan Keladerouo of the Celestial Watch has urged me to slaughter these phantasms before the treasures are buried forever beneath the seabed.',2220161,'Laborers have resumed their aquatic operations now that I have slaughtered a number of sunken Halasians.','Quests/NorthQeynos/submerged_in_terror.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6077,'Sabertooth Skulkers','City Tasks','North Qeynos',21,1,'Sabertooth scouts have been ambushing refugees who travel beyond Antonica. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to remove this threat to the adventurers by slaughtering gnolls within Thundering Steppes.',2220074,'The refugees should find their adventures safer now that I have slaughtered a number of the Sabertooth gnolls.','Quests/NorthQeynos/sabertooth_skulkers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6078,'Flying Artillery','City Tasks','North Qeynos',22,1,'Scouts venturing into Thundering Steppes have been falling to the arrows of centaur archers. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to interrupt these assaults by killing centaurs.',2220074,'The attacks against the scouts have slowed now that I have killed a number of centaur archers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/flying_artillery.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6079,'The Wall of Thunder','City Tasks','North Qeynos',23,1,'Steelhoof warriors are converging in preparation for an invasion of the Qeynosian encampments within Thundering Steppes. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to disrupt these plans by slaying the centaurs.',2220074,'The gathering centaur army has been scattered now that I slain a number of the soldiers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_wall_of_thunder.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6080,'It Came from Below!','City Tasks','North Qeynos',25,1,'Massive goos have been seeping up from the sewers to terrorize citizens. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to reduce this scourge by destroying the creatures within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220074,'The infestation of slimes has been slowed now that I have destroyed a number of the monstrous goos.','Quests/NorthQeynos/it_came_from_below.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6081,'Help the Helpless','City Tasks','North Qeynos',25,1,'Powerful beasts have been butchering refugees who stumble into the city catacombs. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to protect the adventurers by slaughtering minotaurs within the Crypt of Betrayal.',2220074,'The danger to wandering refugees has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the crypt minotaurs.','Quests/NorthQeynos/help_the_helpless.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6082,'Proaction','City Tasks','North Qeynos',26,1,'Scouts returning from the Crypt of Betrayal have reported sightings of Bloodsaber attendants. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to kill the acolytes before they are able to organize and pose a threat to the city.',2220074,'The potential threat from the Bloodsabers has been reduced now that I have killed a number of the soldiers.','Quests/NorthQeynos/proaction.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6083,'The Bringer of Terror','City Tasks','North Qeynos',27,1,'Rumors suggest that Bloodsaber priests within the Crypt of Betrayal are attempting to summon an avatar to destroy the city. Knight-Guard Rellin\'thir of the Qeynos Guard has ordered me to disrupt these rituals by slaying the acolytes.',2220074,'The possible summoning of an avatar has been thwarted now that I have slain a number of the Bloodsaber zealots.','Quests/NorthQeynos/the_bringer_of_terror.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
