(6111,'Nicks and Scratches','City Tasks','South Qeynos',46,1,'Sages of the Three Towers sent to examine the ancient writings and symbols etched into the walls of Lavastorm have encountered goblins intent on driving intruders from their mining fields. Exalted Milanthroo of the Concordium has petitioned me to support the research by destroying the goblin rockpickers.',2310082,'Acolytes have reported it safer to navigate the lands of Lavastorm now that I have destroyed a number of the Sootfoot rockpickers.','Quests/SouthQeynos/nicks_and_scratches.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6112,'Whistling in the Shadows','City Tasks','South Qeynos',46,1,'Adventurers attempting to rest along the scorched walls of Lavastorm have been startled from their meditations by fierce attacks at the hands of the Sootfoot harvesters who mine the area. Exalted Milanthroo of the Concordium has petitioned me to protect the underlings by slaughtering the Sootfoot harvesters.',2310082,'Neophytes have suffered fewer attacks during their meditations now that I have slaughtered a number of the Sootfoot harvesters.','Quests/SouthQeynos/whistling_in_the_shadows.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6113,'Rolling Home','City Tasks','South Qeynos',48,1,'Shadowed thieves hired by the Three Towers to uncover the secrets of Solusek\'s Eye have been unable to elude the watchful eye of the living magma that patrol the fiery landscape. Exalted Milanthroo of the Concordium has petitioned me to protect the scouts by killing the living magma.',2310082,'The discoveries of ancient chambers and forgotten treasures have increased now that I have killed a number of the living magmas.','Quests/SouthQeynos/rolling_home.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6114,'The Rustling of Papers','City Tasks','South Qeynos',48,1,'Librarians sent by the Three Towers to recover ancient tomes from the depths of Permafrost have found their escape routes cut off by Kromise savages. Exalted Milanthroo of the Concordium has petitioned me to slaughter ice giants before the philosophers are discovered and slain.',2310082,'Most of the sages have managed to flee from Permafrost now that I have slaughtered a number of the frost giant savages.','Quests/SouthQeynos/the_rustling_of_papers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6115,'It Fell with a Crash','City Tasks','South Qeynos',49,1,'Qeynosian settlers of the fiery wastelands have been driven from their camps by fetid drones descending from high upon the mountain. Exalted Milanthroo of the Concordium has petitioned me to protect the prospectors by destroying the fetid emissions at their source within Lavastorm.',2310082,'Settlers have continued to spread out across the fiery wastelands of Lavastorm now that I have destroyed a number of the fetid emissions.','Quests/SouthQeynos/it_fell_with_a_crash.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6116,'Serenity Lost','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',11,1,'Animated scarecrows have been attacking the animals of Antonica and forcing them to flee their burrows. Wanderer Greencoast of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the creatures by destroying the scarecrows.',2070037,'The wild animals should be safer within their lairs now that I have destroyed a number of the frenzied scarecrows.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/serenity_lost.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6117,'The Darkpaw Defilers','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',13,1,'Gnoll mystics are corrupting the trees of Antonica, twisting and sharpening their branches to injure adventurers and animals. Wanderer Greencoast of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to remove the scourge by slaughtering Darkpaws.',2070037,'The trees have returned to their natural forms now that I have slaughtered a number of Darkpaw mystics.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_darkpaw_defilers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6118,'Sabertooth Poachers','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',16,1,'Gnolls have been emerging from caves and tunnels to butcher the deer within Antonica. Wanderer Greencoast of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to end this slaughter by killing Sabertooths within Blackburrow.',2070037,'The Antonican deer should be safer now that I have killed a number of the gnoll guards.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/sabertooth_poachers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6119,'Sickness through Subterfuge','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',16,1,'Gnoll mystics have been poisoning the water table beneath Antonica, causing the farm animals that drink well water to fall ill. Wanderer Greencoast of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the water supply by slaying the Sabertooths within Blackburrow.',2070037,'The farmers throughout Antonica have found the well water potable now that I have slain a number of the gnoll witchdoctors.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/sickness_through_subterfuge.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6120,'The Darkest Devourers','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',18,1,'Qeynosian foragers attempting to harvest rare mushrooms within the deepest caverns of Blackburrow have encountered resistance from fanged spiders. Wanderer Greencoast of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to clear a path for the collectors by destroying the giant creatures.',2070037,'The foragers should find their task of collecting mushrooms easier now that I have destroyed a number of the blighted spiders.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_darkest_devourers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6121,'Slithering and Striking','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',20,1,'Adders have been killing the wandering deer within Thundering Steppes. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the creatures by slaying the venomous snakes.',2070046,'The deer should be safer now that I have slain a number of snakes.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/slithering_and_striking.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6122,'Some Animals Are More Equal than Others','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',22,1,'Bear cubs have been falling prey to the giant griffawns of Thundering Steppes. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to kill the griffawns before an entire generation of bears vanishes.',2070046,'The bear population has recovered now that I have slain a number of the griffawns.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/some_animals_are_more_equal_than_others.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6123,'Pools of Carnage','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',23,1,'Octopi have been devouring small animals that bathe and play in the shallows off of Thundering Steppes. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to reduce this threat to the creatures by destroying the octopi.',2070046,'The animals should find safer their excursions into the water now that I have destroyed a number of ravenous octopi.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/pools_of_carnage.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6124,'Entanglement','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',26,1,'Monstrous spiders have been spinning webs to entrap the small animals that stumble into the freshly unearthed Ruins of Varsoon. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect these woodland creatures by slaughtering the poisonous crawlers.',2070046,'The attacks against confused forest creatures have been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the venomous spiders.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/entanglement.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6125,'Not All Vampire Bats Suck Blood','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',26,1,'Swarms of vampiric bats have at night been emerging from caves to feed off Antonican deer. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to defend the deer by slaying the bats at their source within the Ruins of Varsoon.',2070046,'The assaults against the deer have slowed now that I have slain a number of the giant bats.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/not_all_vampire_bats_suck_blood.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6126,'The Salted Earth','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',28,1,'Slime and ooze from goos deep beneath the surface have poisoned the soil and left the plants of Thundering Steppes stunted and withered. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to remove this pollution of the earth by killing the huge goos within the Ruins of Varsoon.',2070046,'The plants have prospered from the nutritious earth now that I have killed a number of the goos.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_salted_earth.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6127,'Forest Preserver','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',29,1,'Scouts have sighted undead laborers harvesting timber within Antonica for transport to the Ruins of Varsoon. Naturalist Tummyfill of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to destroy the skeletal workers before the forests are reduced to fields of stumps.',2070046,'The deforestation of Antonica has been slowed now that I have destroyed a number of the undead loggers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/forest_preserver.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6128,'Unsustainable Population Growth','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',32,1,'Orc invaders have been scavenging for what little plant life remains within the Orcish Wastes, exacerbating the starvation of the native grazing species. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to defend the natural order by slaughtering the orcish foragers.',2070041,'The animals have found food more plentiful now that I have slaughtered a number of the Tallon scavengers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/unsustainable_population_growth.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6129,'In Memoriam: Karana','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',33,1,'The Deathfist Empire has carved vast mines into the mountains surrounding the Citadel, inducing erosion and landslides. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the legacy of the ancient Jaggedpine Forest by slaying the miners within the Orcish Wastes.',2070041,'The orcish mining operations have been disrupted now that I have slain a number of Vallon diggers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/in_memoriam_karana.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6130,'Isolation Through Immolation','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',33,1,'Great cougars have been felled by a crippling disease, threatening the harmony between predators and prey. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to quarantine the plague by killing hill cats within the Orcish Wastes.',2070041,'The contagion has been contained now that I have killed a number of steppe cougars.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/isolation_through_immolation.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6131,'Ungulate Advocate','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',34,1,'Stumbling into holes dug along the beaches by giant crabs, deer have been spraining and fracturing their legs. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the deer by destroying crab excavators within the Orcish Wastes.',2070041,'Waves and sand have filled the holes now that I have destroyed a number of shoreline diggers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/ungulate_advocate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6132,'Get the Balance Right','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',36,1,'Thulian lizards have spilled out from the darkness of the Feerrott to feast upon the peaceful sloths that dangle from the jungle branches. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to slaughter the giant monitors before the sloths are rendered extinct.',2070041,'The population of sloths has stabilized now that I have slaughtered a number of the lizards.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/get_the_balance_right.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6133,'Green Greasy Guardians','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',37,1,'Scouts commissioned to survey the ancient ruins of Zek have encountered fierce resistance from lizardmen within the Feerrott. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to clear a path for the explorers by killing the Evol Ew protectors.',2070041,'Scouts commissioned to survey the ancient ruins of Zek have encountered fierce resistance from lizardmen within the Feerrott. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to clear a path for the explorers by killing the Evol Ew protectors.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/green_greasy_guardians.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6134,'The Heavy Boot of Civilization','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',37,1,'Fiendish troglodytes have been hurling spears and boulders at the Qeynosian vessels ordered to scout the coasts of the Feerrott. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the ships by slaying the Huuptic brutes.',2070041,'Fiendish troglodytes have been hurling spears and boulders at the Qeynosian vessels ordered to scout the coasts of the Feerrott. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the ships by slaying the Huuptic brutes.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_heavy_boot_of_civilization.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6135,'Stench of the Void','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',38,1,'Putrid beasts have transformed the rivers of the Feerrott into gutters of sewage, inhospitable to all life. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to defend the water animals by destroying the pungent chokemaws.',2070041,'Filth has begun to recede from the waters now that I have destroyed a number of the vile gutterbeasts.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/stench_of_the_void.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6136,'The Imbibers','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',38,1,'Giant dragonflies have been injecting into the creatures of the Feerrott a fatal disease that subjects its victims to rapid thickening of the blood. Shepherd Sell\'ar of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to slaughter the plague flies before this contagion spreads across the sea and fells the animals of Antonica.',2070041,'The incidence of infection has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the fetid insects.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_imbibers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6137,'Command These Elements to Silence','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',40,1,'Seafarers attempting to navigate the icy waters surrounding Everfrost have found their vessels assaulted by massive sharks. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to remove this danger by slaying the elder frostfins.',2070038,'Explorers have reported as safer the passage across Everstorm Bay now that I have slain a number of gargantuan sharks.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/command_these_elements_to_silence.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6138,'No, I Am the Prettiest!','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',42,1,'Valkyries dueling for dominance of Everfrost have been summoning blizzards to uproot and crash ancient evergreens against one another. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to slaughter the tempest valkyries before their fury flattens the forests.',2070038,'The evergreens have prospered now that I have slaughtered a number of the hailstorm valkyries.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/no_i_am_the_prettiest.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6139,'One End over Another','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',42,1,'Skinners and provisioners have been butchering the tundra bears of Everfrost. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the animals by destroying Bitterwind furriers.',2070038,'The population of arctic bears has recovered now that I have destroyed a number of the trappers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/one_end_over_another.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6140,'Cataclysm Averted','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',43,1,'Scattered to Everfrost by the Rending, equatorial monitor lizards have thrived despite the frigid conditions. Lacking predators and surrounded by wildlife unadapted to their viciousness, the great reptiles threaten to destroy the natural order of the tundra. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to prevent an ecological disaster by killing the exotic monitors.',2070038,'Species native to the arctic have reappeared now that I have killed a number of the giant lizards.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/cataclysm_averted.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6141,'Encaged in Ice','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',44,1,'Explorers commissioned by Queen Antonia to locate medicinal lichen within the frozen caverns of Everfrost have suffered harsh attacks from undead. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the gatherers by slaughtering the blighted frights.',2070038,'The harvesters have found it easier to collect the rare plants now that I have slaughtered a number of frost skeletons.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/encaged_in_ice.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6142,'O\'er the Towering Steep','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',46,1,'Scouts attempting to slip into Solusek\'s Eye through the northern seas have reported their skiffs under attack from the Sootfoot laborers who work the coastline of Lavastorm. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to clear a path by destroying the Sootfoot laborers.',2070038,'The boats have found it easier to land along the fiery shore now that I have destroyed a number of the Sootfoot laborers.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/oer_the_towering_steep.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6143,'The Wild Hunt','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',46,1,'Mighty beasts once dominated the fiery horizon but have greatly declined in numbers with the encroachment of goblins uprooted by the Cataclysm. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to defend the majestic beasts by slaying Sootfoot peons within Lavastorm.',2070038,'The mighty beasts have increased their territory now that I have slain a number of the Sootfoot peons.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/the_wild_hunt.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6144,'Unnatural Circle of Life','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',1,1,'The fauna of Everfrost has begun to show signs of attack by the frozen undead that walk the caves leading to Miragul\'s Menagerie. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to ensure the long-term survival of the creatures by killing the ice fright skeletons within Everfrost.',2070038,'Fewer creatures have been attacked by the frozen undead now that I have killed a number of the ice fright skeletons within Everfrost.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/unnatural_circle_of_life.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6145,'Between a Rock and Lava','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',48,1,'Gatherers commissioned to collect diamonds from the deep crevasses along the lava tubes of Lavastorm have suffered brutal assaults from monstrous lizards. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to remove this threat to the harvesters by slaying the scaled beasts.',2070038,'The collection of diamonds within Lavastorm has resumed now that I have slain a number of the monstrous lizards within the searing landscape.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/between_a_rock_and_lava.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6146,'Don\'t Try to Look Beneath the Surface','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',48,1,'Cartographers commissioned by Queen Antonia to map the changes wrought by the Shattering have found the frigid plains of Everfrost impassable on account of the terrors that lurk beneath its icy surface. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to protect the adventurers by destroying tundra terrors.',2070038,'The exploration and documentation of the hinterland has continued now that I have destroyed a number of tundra terrors.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/dont_try_to_look_beneath_the_surface.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6147,'Purification','City Tasks','The Elddar Grove',48,1,'A volcanic eruption has threatened the beasts of Lavastorm, the starving beasts have turned to eating their young. Preservationist Reynolds of the Tunarian Alliance has beseeched me to ensure the long-term survival of the species by killing the adult magma beasts.',2070038,'Fewer young have been killed now that I have killed a number of the magma worms.','Quests/TheElddarGrove/purification.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6148,'Orcish Miners','City Tasks','West Freeport',11,1,'Reports indicate that the orcs are attempting to tunnel under the walls between the Commonlands and Freeport. Trooper Bonesaw of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slay some of these invaders before they are able to penetrate the city.',1680060,'The attempt to burrow under the walls of Freeport has been disrupted now that I have slain a number of the orc invaders.','Quests/WestFreeport/orcish_miners.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6149,'Punish the Pachyderms','City Tasks','West Freeport',15,1,'Settlers seeking to expand the influence of Freeport have encountered opposition from herds of elephants that trample the homesteads. Trooper Bonesaw of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I end this destruction by killing elephants within the Commonlands.',1680060,'The settlers should be able to continue their expansion now that I have killed a number of elephants.','Quests/WestFreeport/punish_the_pachyderms.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6150,'Thinning the Herd (Commonlands)','City Tasks','West Freeport',11,1,'Vulriches have been breeding too quickly and slaughtering inexperienced refugees who venture forth from Freeport. Trooper Bonesaw of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I reduce the casualties by slaying the foul carrion birds.',1680060,'The new refugees should find their excursions from Freeport safer now that I have slain a number of the aggressive flightless birds.','Quests/WestFreeport/thinning_the_herd.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6151,'Orcish Threats','City Tasks','West Freeport',13,1,'Trooper Bonesaw of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I defend the city by killing as many Bloodskull warriors as I can find.',1680060,'The city should be a little safer after my slaying of Freeport\'s enemies.','Quests/WestFreeport/orcish_threats.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6152,'Horrors of the Past','City Tasks','West Freeport',16,1,'Patrols have reported horrific undead lurking within the ruins of Val\'Marr. Trooper Bonesaw of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I kill the undead beasts before they are able to emerge from their ruined home and ravage unwary travelers.',1680060,'The danger to Freeport travelers from the undead horrors should be lessened now that I have killed a number of the monsters.','Quests/WestFreeport/horrors_of_the_past.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6153,'Ravenous Grizzlies','City Tasks','West Freeport',24,1,'Huge beasts have been mauling spice suppliers traveling from the Enchanted Lands. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove the threat to the merchants by destroying the fearsome bears within Nektulos.',1680075,'The threat to the spice merchants should be lessened now that I have destroyed a number of the giant kodiaks.','Quests/WestFreeport/ravenous_grizzlies.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6154,'The Pursuit of Happiness','City Tasks','West Freeport',22,1,'Bandits from Nektulos have been sneaking into the Commonlands and pillaging from the settlements. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I stop the vandalism by slaughtering the thieves.',1680075,'The vandalism of the settlements has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the bandits.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_pursuit_of_happiness.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6155,'Goblin Lurkers','City Tasks','West Freeport',23,1,'Bands of goblins have been ambushing and slaughtering refugees who wander into Nektulos. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I protect the adventurers by killing goblin bandits.',1680075,'The new refugees should find their excursions into Nektulos safer now that I have killed a number of the goblins.','Quests/WestFreeport/goblin_lurkers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6156,'Thinning the Herd (Fallen Gate)','City Tasks','West Freeport',22,1,'Undead creatures have been crawling up out of Fallen Gate and slaughtering inexperienced refugees who venture forth from Freeport. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I reduce the casualties by slaying the foul attackers.',1680075,'The new refugees should find their excursions from Freeport safer now that I have slain a number of the undead attackers.','Quests/WestFreeport/thinning_the_herd_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6157,'Nocturnal Feeders','City Tasks','West Freeport',24,1,'Mindless undead have been emerging each night from Fallen Gate to devour the farm animals that provide Freeport with sustenance. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I defend the animals by destroying the undead.',1680075,'The farm animals should be safer now that I have destroyed a number of the undead attackers.','Quests/WestFreeport/nocturnal_feeders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6158,'Horrors of the Abyss','City Tasks','West Freeport',25,1,'Patrols have reported horrific monstrosities lurking within the ancient lair of Fallen Gate. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I kill the undead beasts before they are able to emerge from their subterranean tomb and ravage the city.',1680075,'The danger to Freeport from the undead horrors should be lessened now that I have killed a number of the monsters.','Quests/WestFreeport/horrors_of_the_abyss.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6159,'The River of Promise','City Tasks','West Freeport',25,1,'Prospectors attempting to pan for gold within the Torrent have been ambushed and drowned by fierce goblin guards. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove this obstacle by slaying grinnins within Nektulos.',1680075,'The prospectors have found it easier to seek their fortunes within the forest now that I have slain a number of the river goblins.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_river_of_promise.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6160,'Famine','City Tasks','West Freeport',26,1,'Swarms of giant bees have been devouring the fields of sweet corn that surround the city walls and provide food to the Citadel. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I destroy the bees at their source in Nektulos before the fields are emptied of crops.',1680075,'The supply of corn to the Citadel has increased now that I have destroyed a number of the deadly bees.','Quests/WestFreeport/famine.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6161,'The Wood Began to Move','City Tasks','West Freeport',26,1,'Rallied by Antonican infiltrators, rumbleroots have assembled within Nektulos in preparation for an assault upon the Freeport walls. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I scatter the rising army by killing the elder treants.',1680075,'The assemblage of ancient treants has been dispersed now that I have killed a number of the rumbleroots.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_wood_began_to_move.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6162,'Dark Feeders','City Tasks','West Freeport',27,1,'The population of giant bats within Nektulos has swelled to such proportions that colonies of the shriekers descend at night to feast upon the inhabitants of Freeport. Liege Helvanica of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I reduce the competition for food by slaughtering bats within the forest.',1680075,'The giant shrillers have found food sources within the forest to be adequate now that I have slaughtered a number of the bats.','Quests/WestFreeport/dark_feeders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6163,'Exterminate the Klakroks','City Tasks','West Freeport',31,1,'Klakroks have been chewing through the support posts of the pier in the Enchanted Lands. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slay these giant beetles before the wharf is destroyed and connection with Freeport severed.',1680068,'The destruction of the docks has slowed now that I have slain a number of the klakrok devourers.','Quests/WestFreeport/exterminate_the_klakroks.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
