(6165,'Shielding the Surveyors','City Tasks','West Freeport',33,1,'Rabid bears have been mauling scouts and surveyors who venture into the Enchanted Lands. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove this danger by killing the savage creatures.',1680068,'The explorers have found safer their excursions now that I have killed a number of bears.','Quests/WestFreeport/shielding_the_surveyors.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6166,'Sir Lucan Will Find Work for Idle Hands to Do','City Tasks','West Freeport',33,1,'Mercenaries and laborers commissioned to establish a guard tower beside the road to Rivervale have fallen beneath the dark magic of the Seamist sirens. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove this obstacle to occupation by slaughtering the fairies within the Enchanted Lands.',1680068,'The construction of the tower has proceeded now that I have slaughtered a number of the Seamist avengers.','Quests/WestFreeport/sir_lucan_will_find_work_for_idle_hands_to_do.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6167,'Gnashers and Gnawers','City Tasks','West Freeport',38,1,'Surveyors commissioned by the Citadel to catalogue the known world have had their progression through Runnyeye thwarted by savage boar beasts. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I advance the mission by destroying the warboar slayers.',1680068,'The attacks against the explorers have slowed now that I have destroyed a number of the enraged warboars.','Quests/WestFreeport/gnashers_and_gnawers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6168,'More of the Same','City Tasks','West Freeport',38,1,'Spies have discovered a Clan Runnyeye plot to assassinate the Overlord and seize Freeport during the resultant chaos. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I defend the Master by slaying goblin predators within Runnyeye.',1680068,'The designs against the Citadel have been thwarted now that I have slain a number of the goblin cutthroats.','Quests/WestFreeport/more_of_the_same.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6169,'Oral Traditions','City Tasks','West Freeport',38,1,'Reports indicate that Clan Runnyeye has signed an agreement to share with Concordium apprentices the secrets of the Warlock. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I prevent the dissemination of this knowledge by killing goblin sorcerers within Runnyeye.',1680068,'Qeynos has found it difficult to discover the secrets of destructive magic now that I have killed a number of Runnyeye summoners.','Quests/WestFreeport/oral_traditions.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6170,'Quicksand!','City Tasks','West Freeport',38,1,'Agents report that goblin mages are researching methods to summon a sinkhole large enough to swallow all of Freeport. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I protect the city by slaughtering goblin conjurors within Runnyeye.',1680068,'The plan to destroy Freeport has been disrupted now that I have slaughtered a number of the Runnyeye goblins.','Quests/WestFreeport/quicksand.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6171,'The Best Defense Is a Good Offense','City Tasks','West Freeport',38,1,'Informants have revealed a collaboration between Qeynos and Clan Runnyeye to construct warships in preparation for an attack against Freeport. Baron Zafimus of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slay goblin miners within Runnyeye before materials sufficient to construct the vessels can be gathered.',1680068,'The invasion has been impeded now that I have slain a number of the goblin diggers.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_best_defense_is_a_good_offense.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6172,'Bent in the Undergrowth','City Tasks','West Freeport',41,1,'Darkflight hatemelders have been corrupting the hedges and vines surrounding the Enchanted Lands, choking off outlying paths. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slaughter the twisted painweavers within Rivervale before all travel is made impossible.',1680150,'Wild thickets and briars have begun to recede from the roads leading into Rivervale now that I have slaughtered a number of the corrupted fairies.','Quests/WestFreeport/bent_in_the_undergrowth.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6173,'The Mysterious Oocyte','City Tasks','West Freeport',41,1,'Divers commissioned by the Citadel to mine a rare iron from the beds of the ponds and streams in Rivervale have suffered brutal attacks from underwater spirits. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I ensure the continued flow of the mineral by destroying the water elementals.',1680150,'The shipments of ore to Freeport have resumed now that I have destroyed a number of the aquatic globules.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_mysterious_oocyte.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6174,'See with Your Heart','City Tasks','West Freeport',42,1,'Adventurers to Rivervale have disappeared into the dark woods, lured by the suggestive songs of unseen lamiae. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove this temptation by killing lamia deathsingers.',1680150,'Fewer explorers have vanished into the wilds now that I have killed a number of the lamiae.','Quests/WestFreeport/see_with_your_heart.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6175,'The Sound Is Deep','City Tasks','West Freeport',42,1,'Woodcutters commissioned by the Citadel to harvest lumber from the ancient trees of Rivervale have encountered fierce resistance from desecrated treants. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I protect the laborers by slaying the corrupted hill oaks.',1680150,'The attacks against the woodsmen have slowed now that I have slain a number of the twisted treants.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_sound_is_deep.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6176,'Our Elaborate Plans','City Tasks','West Freeport',43,1,'Dimios Litakes was a legionnaire of the Citadel before betraying the Master and fleeing to the Enchanted Lands. In exchange for knowledge of the Chaos Tongue he has revealed critical information to the fearsome nightbloods, advancing their attacks against Freeport outposts and settlements. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I disrupt this conspiracy by destroying the nightblood transgressors within Rivervale.',1680150,'The beasts of the Shattered Lands recognize the price to be paid for opposing the Citadel now that I have destroyed a number of nightblood despisers.','Quests/WestFreeport/our_elaborate_plans.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6177,'Feral Awakening','City Tasks','West Freeport',45,1,'Sages commissioned by the Citadel to scour the wastelands of Everfrost for undiscovered arcana have fallen victim to wolves in those tundra. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I diminish the number of wolves in the tundra of Everfrost.',1680150,'The assaults against the researchers have slowed now that I have slaughtered a number of ice wolves.','Quests/WestFreeport/feral_awakening.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6178,'Playing with Fire','City Tasks','West Freeport',45,1,'The Bitterwind explorers are hindering our own exploration of Everfrost. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I kill the Bitterwind pioneers before they find something of interest to Freeport.',1680150,'The gathering explorers has been dispersed now that I have killed a number of the Bitterwind pioneers.','Quests/WestFreeport/playing_with_fire.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6179,'Mangy Mutts','City Tasks','West Freeport',46,1,'In exchange for a legendary, ice-sheathed sword recovered from the depths of Permafrost, the Citadel has agreed to assist the Bitterwind explorers against the vicious wolves that are multiplying throughout Everfrost. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slaughter ice growlers within Everfrost.',1680150,'The debt to Bitterwind explorers has been repaid now that I have slain a number of the ice growlers.','Quests/WestFreeport/mangy_mutts.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6180,'Frivolous Crusade','City Tasks','West Freeport',47,1,'The Galebreakers have been slaughtering our troops as part of a pilgrimage. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I return the favor to these Galebreaker pilgrims in Everfrost.',1680150,'Soldiers in Everfrost are no longer hunted by the Galebreaker pilgrims within Everfrost.','Quests/WestFreeport/frivolous_crusade.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6181,'The Road Home','City Tasks','West Freeport',47,1,'Trading vessels transporting refugees to Freeport have been split asunder and capsized by powerful storms. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I slow these attacks at their source by destroying Frosthorn stormcallers within Everfrost.',1680150,'The ships have found safer their journeys to Freeport now that I have destroyed a number of the Frosthorn stormcallers.','Quests/WestFreeport/the_road_home.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6182,'Aggressive Negotiations','City Tasks','West Freeport',48,1,'Ambassadors sent to \"negotiate\" the surrender of the denizens of Solusek\'s Eye have been getting attacked by the living magma within Lavastorm. Viscount Gelvonius of the Freeport Militia has demanded that I remove this obstacle by extinguishing the floating magma within Dagger Spires Pass.',1680150,'The emissaries have been able to reach the gates of the Temple of Solusek Ro now that I have extinguished a number of the living magma.','Quests/WestFreeport/aggressive_negotiations.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6183,'Betrayal From Within','City Tasks','North Freeport',11,1,'Zilvua Quantog was a promising student within the Academy before betraying its teachings and fleeing Freeport. Now she seeks to raise an undead army against the city. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to weaken the grip of this necromancer by destroying her skeleton drudges within the Commonlands.',1440011,'Zilvua Quantog was a promising student within the Academy before betraying its teachings and fleeing Freeport. Now she seeks to raise an undead army against the city. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to weaken the grip of this necromancer by destroying her skeleton drudges within the Commonlands.','Quests/NorthFreeport/betrayal_from_within.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6184,'Pride of the Commonlands','City Tasks','North Freeport',17,1,'Last week two Academy field researchers were killed by a pride of lions and since the incident pupils have been forbidden from exiting the city gates. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to thin the lion population within the Commonlands.',1440011,'The pupils of the Academy should find safer their excursions into the Commonlands now that I have killed a number of lions.','Quests/NorthFreeport/pride_of_the_commonlands.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6185,'A Plague of Problems','City Tasks','North Freeport',15,1,'The Academy is alarmed by reports that there are so many scourge rats skittering across the savannah of the Commonlands. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to kill the diseased rats before they can become an infestation.',1440011,'The danger to Freeport has been reduced now that I have slain a number of the diseased rodents.','Quests/NorthFreeport/a_plague_of_problems.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6186,'Quell the Infestation','City Tasks','North Freeport',15,1,'For the past month the number of stone beetles has been steadily increasing. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to reduce this number by slaying the creatures at their origin.',1440011,'The infestation of beetles has been somewhat reduced I have slain a number of the pests.','Quests/NorthFreeport/quell_the_infestation.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6187,'Aggressive Carrion Feeders','City Tasks','North Freeport',17,1,'The Academy has detected the rise in the number of the carrion eating giant vulriches within the Commonlands. Neophyte Jhanov of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to thin the numbers of these loathsome and dangerous birds.',1440011,'The number of giant vulriches within the Commonlands has been reduced thanks to my selective hunting.','Quests/NorthFreeport/aggressive_carrion_feeders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6188,'Castus Interruptus','City Tasks','North Freeport',22,1,'Shrieking bats have been disturbing the mass casting experiments conducted within Nektulos by the Academy. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to impose quiet upon the forest by slaughtering the firelight bats.',1440020,'The experiments can continue without disruption now that I have slaughtered a number of the firelight shriekers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/castus_interruptus.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6189,'Slash and Burn','City Tasks','North Freeport',24,1,'Academy researchers attempting to reach the walls of Nektropos Castle have been beaten back by the living saplings of the forest. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to clear a path through Nektulos by destroying the plant horrors.',1440020,'The path is cleared for researchers to reach Nektropos Castle now that I have destroyed a number of the root horrors.','Quests/NorthFreeport/slash_and_burn.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6190,'Venomous Creepers','City Tasks','North Freeport',22,1,'Hidden creatures have been leaping out from the trees to kill Academy initiates who venture into Nektulos. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to remove this threat to the students by slaying forest spiders.',1440020,'The poisonous threat to the students has been reduced now that I have slain a number of the hidden spiders.','Quests/NorthFreeport/venomous_creepers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6191,'Undead Mercenaries','City Tasks','North Freeport',23,1,'The Academy is alarmed by reports that the spirits of sorcerers inhabit the unearthed catacombs of Fallen Gate. Were a lich or necromancer to gain control of these undead even the combined forces of Freeport might not stand against such a powerful army. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to destroy the undead mages while they are still without a master.',1440020,'The danger to Freeport has been reduced now that I have destroyed a number of the undead mages.','Quests/NorthFreeport/undead_mercenaries.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6192,'Subterranean Rituals','City Tasks','North Freeport',23,1,'The Academy has detected the conducting of ancient summoning ceremonies beneath the surface of the Shattered Lands. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to disrupt these rituals by destroying the undead mages within Fallen Gate.',1440020,'The ceremonies have been interrupted now that I have destroyed a number of the undead mages.','Quests/NorthFreeport/subterranean_rituals.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6193,'Repel the Invaders','City Tasks','North Freeport',24,1,'For the past month walking corpses have been appearing at dusk to besiege the Freeport gates. Through a divination spell the Academy traced the source of these actions to the depths of Fallen Gate. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to slow the attacks by slaying the creatures at their origin.',1440020,'The attacks against Freeport have been slowed now that I have slain a number of the anguished gluttons.','Quests/NorthFreeport/repel_the_invaders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6194,'The World Left Them Behind Long Ago','City Tasks','North Freeport',25,1,'Academy scholars attempting to study ancient Teir\'Dal monuments within Nektulos have been chased from the forest by Thexian loyalists. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to clear a path for the researchers by killing the bandits.',1440020,'The forest is cleared for researchers to continue their studies now that I have killed a number of the ruffians and scouts.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_world_left_them_behind_long_ago.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6195,'The March of Progress','City Tasks','North Freeport',26,1,'Reports categorize the treants of Nektulos as highly resistant to the magic of Academy students. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to remove a potential obstacle to exploitation of the forest by destroying the treants.',1440020,'The forest is more susceptible to experimentation and exploitation now that I have destroyed the elder treants.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_march_of_progress.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6196,'Ghoulish Grievance','City Tasks','North Freeport',26,1,'Ghouls have been terrorizing adventurers who camp along the foothills of Nektulos. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to slaughter the ghouls to keep the trade routes clear.',1440020,'The refugees have found it safer to pitch their camps within Nektulos now that I have slaughtered a number of the ghouls.','Quests/NorthFreeport/ghoulish_grievance.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6197,'Wall of Stone','City Tasks','North Freeport',29,1,'Academy scribes assigned to investigate the ancient artifacts within Nektropos Castle have encountered fierce resistance from the entrance guardians. Archivist Jindlefog of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to remove this obstacle by slaying the fiendish gargoyles within Nektulos.',1440020,'The scribes have been able to enter Nektropos Castle now that I have slain a number of demented gargoyles.','Quests/NorthFreeport/wall_of_stone.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6198,'Claustrophobia','City Tasks','North Freeport',32,1,'Students ordered by the Academy to survey the caverns beneath the Enchanted Lands have found themselves lost within the twisted, deadly web of subterranean passages. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to destroy the creatures of Runnyeye before they are able to discover the scholars.',1440012,'The immediate threat to the scribes has been removed now that I have destroyed a number of the minotaur taskmasters.','Quests/NorthFreeport/claustrophobia.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6199,'Stand Up and Be Slaughtered','City Tasks','North Freeport',32,1,'The enslaved creatures of Runnyeye have rejected encouragement from Academy emissaries to revolt against their goblin masters. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to punish this lack of due regard by killing the warboar slaves.',1440012,'Reference to the Academy once again bestirs respect now that I have killed a number of the disdainful warboars.','Quests/NorthFreeport/stand_up_and_be_slaughtered.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6200,'Dust And Diamonds In Teak Chests','City Tasks','North Freeport',33,1,'Seers have discovered an entombed, heavily-guarded library deep within the halls of Runnyeye. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to clear a path for researchers by slaughtering the goblin defenders.',1440012,'The scribes have recovered ancient tomes and artifacts from the caverns now that I have slaughtered a number of the goblin guards.','Quests/NorthFreeport/dust_and_diamonds_in_teak_chests.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6201,'Scuttle the Man-o-War','City Tasks','North Freeport',33,1,'Clan Runnyeye has stolen a Far Seas Trading Co. vessel and is reportedly overhauling the boat for an assault against Freeport. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to disrupt this plot by slaying the goblin shipwrights within Runnyeye.',1440012,'The outfitting of the warship has halted now that I have slain a number of goblin engineers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/scuttle_the_manowar.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6202,'Attack of the Arachnids','City Tasks','North Freeport',36,1,'Apprentices ordered to the Enchanted Lands on an expedition to locate an ancient passage have been forced by ravenous spiders to retreat to the wharf. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to protect the operation by slaughtering the spiders.',1440012,'The students have been able to continue their search for the lost tunnel now that I have slaughtered a number of giant spiders.','Quests/NorthFreeport/attack_of_the_arachnids.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6203,'The Orb of Confusion','City Tasks','North Freeport',36,1,'Academy sages have detected a sprawling energy field that disrupts spellcasting, increasing the prospect of an interruption or fizzle. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to dismantle this field at its source by killing the orbs of darkness within the Enchanted Lands.',1440012,'The seers have identified a weakening of the anti-arcana field now that I have killed a number of chaos goos.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_orb_of_confusion.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6204,'Wildwood','City Tasks','North Freeport',36,1,'Treant guardians have been attacking Academy drudges sent to scour for charms and relics the abandoned halfling huts within the Enchanted Lands. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to remove this threat to the scavengers by destroying the knotted treants.',1440012,'The laborers should find safer their searches of the huts now that I have destroyed a number of the treant avengers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/wildwood.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6205,'Curators of Bone','City Tasks','North Freeport',37,1,'Academy naturalists attempting to collect skulls from all known creatures have suffered attacks from fairy guardians within the Enchanted Lands. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to support this research by slaying the Darkflight fiends.',1440012,'The harvesting of skulls has continued now that I have slain a number of the corrupted fairies.','Quests/NorthFreeport/curators_of_bone.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6206,'Xenocidal Propensities','City Tasks','North Freeport',39,1,'Nightbloods have brutally butchered a contingent of Academy representatives arrived to negotiate the division of dominion over the Enchanted Lands. Paragon Jalex of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to punish this affront by killing the nightblood tormentors.',1440012,'The slaughter of the emissaries has been partially avenged now that I have killed a number of nightblood crusaders.','Quests/NorthFreeport/xenocidal_propensities.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6207,'Mauling Pups','City Tasks','North Freeport',42,1,'Academy acolytes attempting to siphon energies from the frigid trenches of Everfrost have been mauled by ice wolf pups. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to lessen this danger by slaying a number of the ice wolf pups within the Bitterwind Trench.',1440030,'Fewer apprentices have been attacked by wolf pups now that I have culled their population within Everfrost.','Quests/NorthFreeport/mauling_pups.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6208,'Bullied by Arcane Scientists','City Tasks','North Freeport',43,1,'There are rumors that the Frosthorn minotaurs have some very powerful arcane items, possibly stolen from Miragul\'s Menagerie. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to slay Frosthorn minotaurs within Everfrost in search of such items.',1440030,'I did not find any arcane items of significance on the Frosthorn minotaurs that I slayed within Everfrost, but Thaumaturge Ranollious is satisfied with my thorough search.','Quests/NorthFreeport/bullied_by_arcane_scientists.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6209,'Hunting the Iofer Stalkers','City Tasks','North Freeport',43,1,'Arctic lizards have been devouring stalks of a rare herb, Iofer, found only within the ice covered land of Everfrost. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to protect a sufficient quantity of these ingredients by slaughtering arctic monitors and arctic behemoths.',1440030,'Academy harvesters have reported a burgeoning of herbs in Everfrost now that I have slaughtered a number of the arctic lizards.','Quests/NorthFreeport/hunting_the_iofer_stalkers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6210,'Hot Crab Legs!','City Tasks','North Freeport',45,1,'Aggressive smoldering king crabs have interrupted the meditations of Temple applicants seeking knowledge from the Order of Flame at the Shrine of Thunder. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to remove this dangerous disruption by slaying the crustaceans that lurk under the waves around the shrine in Lavastorm.',1440030,'Acolytes have found their studies more productive now that I have slain a number of smoldering king crabs around the Shrine of Thunder in Lavastorm.','Quests/NorthFreeport/hot_crab_legs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6211,'Vicious Wormlings','City Tasks','North Freeport',45,1,'Academy researchers commissioned to survey the creatures of Lavastorm have suffered from attacks by the vicious magma wormlings surrounding Magma Grotto. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to protect the explorers by killing the magma wormlings.',1440030,'Adventurers have reported fewer attacks now that I have killed a number of the magma wormlings.','Quests/NorthFreeport/vicious_wormlings.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6212,'Perfectly Motionless','City Tasks','North Freeport',46,1,'Clockwork shredders forged in the fires beneath Lavastorm have been spotted converging within the Commonlands, though for what purpose it is unknown. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to slaughter ones collecting the materials for these machines within Lavastorm before an army of machines is assembled against Freeport.',1440030,'Fewer clockwork scrappers have emerged within the Commonlands now that I have slaughtered a number of the workers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/perfectly_motionless.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6213,'Rivers of Mana','City Tasks','North Freeport',46,1,'Goblin Laborers have tapped in to the arcane pools stretching for miles beneath the surface of the Shattered Lands. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to ensure a supply of energy for adventurers by slaying Sootfoot Laborers.',1440030,'The subterranean ether of magic has begun to refill now that I have slain a number of the Sootfoot Laborers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/rivers_of_mana.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6214,'Cold Bones of Death','City Tasks','North Freeport',47,1,'Academy acolytes attempting to reach Miragul\'s Menagerie in search of lost arcane knowledge have found the entrances heavily guarded by ice fright skeletons. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to clear a path for the researchers by killing the ice fright skeletons in Everfrost.',1440030,'The road to the ancient entrance to Miragul\'s Menagerie has been smoothed now that I have killed a number of the ice fright skeletons in Everfrost.','Quests/NorthFreeport/cold_bones_of_death.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6215,'Secrets of the Flame','City Tasks','North Freeport',48,1,'Strange occurrences of flame have been noticed throughout the lands of Freeport, the Citidel believe this is tied into with activity of flame creatures in Lavastorm. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me slay some beings of fire within Lavastorm to see if this reduces these odd occurrences.',1440030,'The strange occurrences have subsided now that I have slain some magma worms.','Quests/NorthFreeport/secrets_of_the_flame.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6216,'The Forbidden Passages of Ro','City Tasks','North Freeport',48,1,'Adventurers commissioned by the Academy to retrieve ancient texts from the chambers of Solusek\'s Eye have been ambushed by lizards hidden within the searing landscape of Lavastorm. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to protect the hirelings by slaughtering the monstrous lizards.',1440030,'Explorers have found safer passage across Lavastorm and to the tunnels of Solusek\'s Eye now that I have slaughtered a number of the monstrous lizards.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_forbidden_passages_of_ro.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6217,'Cubes of Coal','City Tasks','North Freeport',49,1,'Academy seers sent deep into Solusek\'s Eye to study the mystic metallurgy of Thyr have become trapped, unable to move for fear of alerting the fire giants to their presence. Thaumaturge Ranollious of the Arcane Scientists has asked me to save these lost researchers by slaying the giant guardians that surround their position.',1440030,'The lost acolytes have been able to move from their hidden position now that I have slain a number of the fire giant champions.','Quests/NorthFreeport/cubes_of_coal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6218,'Wisdom of the Bloodskulls','City Tasks','North Freeport',12,1,'The Temple has discovered practitioners of the healing and protective arts among the orcs of the Commonlands. Convert Y\'ral of the Dismal Rage has requested that I remove this growing danger by slaughtering the orcish priests.',1440055,'The potential threat from the orcs has been diminished now that I have slaughtered a number of the priests.','Quests/NorthFreeport/wisdom_of_the_bloodskulls.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6219,'The Vandals','City Tasks','North Freeport',12,1,'Temple faithful have reported their shrines, placed outside Freeport to absorb the life energy from the land, upended and soiled by the native young vulriches. Convert Y\'ral of the Dismal Rage has requested that I end this defilement by killing vulriches within the Commonlands.',1440055,'The vandalism of the outlying shrines has been slowed now that I have killed a number of the young vulrich defilers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_vandals.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6220,'Travel Troubles','City Tasks','North Freeport',16,1,'Temple missionaries, unwilling to travel through the Ruins of Val\'Marr for fear of inviting notice from the undead denizens, are complaining about the menace. Convert Y\'ral of the Dismal Rage has requested that I destroy the fallen inhabitants.',1440055,'The potential threat against the missionaries has been reduced now that I have destroyed a number of the walking corpses.','Quests/NorthFreeport/travel_troubles.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6221,'The Gathering of Bones (Commonlands)','City Tasks','North Freeport',17,1,'Temple priests have noticed an unusual massing of tortured souls near the pass to Nektulos Forest. Convert Y\'ral of the Dismal Rage has requested that I destroy several of these undead within The Commonlands.',1440055,'The gathering undead have been scattered now that I have slain a number of the tortured souls.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_gathering_of_bones_commonlands.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6222,'Traitorous Designs (Commonlands)','City Tasks','North Freeport',17,1,'Several acolytes have fled from the Temple and hidden themselves among the Dervish cutthroats. Convert Y\'ral of the Dismal Rage has requested that I set an example to this band of brigands by killing several of their number. The Dismal Rage does not tolerate those who would betray their duties and oaths.',1440055,'The allies of the traitorous acolytes have been weakened now that I have killed a number of the Dervish cutthroats.','Quests/NorthFreeport/traitorous_designs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6223,'The Unseen Master','City Tasks','North Freeport',20,1,'The power of an unknown sorcerer inside Nektropos Castle has increased the appetite of the undead that inhabit the surrounding forest. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I weaken the influence of this necromancer by slaying the skeletons within Nektulos.',1440044,'The grip of Nektropos Castle upon the surrounding lands has been weakened now that I have slain a number of the skeleton minions.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_unseen_master.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6224,'Web of Aggression','City Tasks','North Freeport',22,1,'The giant arachnids of Nektulos threaten to extend their territory into the Commonlands. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I stop their expansion by slaughtering spider hatchlings.',1440044,'The growth of the spider population has been slowed now that I have slaughtered a number of spiders.','Quests/NorthFreeport/web_of_aggression.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6225,'Natural Resources','City Tasks','North Freeport',24,1,'Shadowed men are draining all life from Nektulos, leaving Temple followers unable to fuel their powers when adventuring in the area. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I destroy the dark creatures before the energy of the forest is entirely consumed.',1440044,'The acolytes should find life to consume within the forest now that I have destroyed a number of the shadowed creatures.','Quests/NorthFreeport/natural_resources.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6226,'The Gathering of Bones (Fallen Gate)','City Tasks','North Freeport',21,1,'Temple priests have detected the massing of subterranean creatures against Freeport. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I delay an invasion of the city by slaying the blighted undead within Fallen Gate.',1440044,'The gathering undead army has been scattered now that I have slain a number of the vengeful minions.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_gathering_of_bones_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6227,'Trapped!','City Tasks','North Freeport',21,1,'Temple missionaries, unwilling to move for fear of inviting notice from the undead denizens, are trapped within Fallen Gate. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I slaughter the blighted inhabitants before they are able to discover the missionaries.',1440044,'The potential threat against the missionaries has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the walking corpses.','Quests/NorthFreeport/trapped.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6228,'Traitorous Designs (Fallen Gate)','City Tasks','North Freeport',21,1,'Several acolytes have fled from the Temple and hidden themselves deep below the surface. From their subterranean lair they seek to command the inhabitants of Fallen Gate against the city of Freeport. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I diminish this threat by destroying the undead minions.',1440044,'The power of the traitorous acolytes has been weakened now that I have killed a number of the undead invaders.','Quests/NorthFreeport/traitorous_designs_fallen_gate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6229,'Vivisection','City Tasks','North Freeport',25,1,'Enraged treants have been attacking Temple librarians who attempt to collect blood and tissue samples from the creatures of Nektulos. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I protect the sages by killing the treants.',1440044,'The collection of samples has continued without disruption now that I have killed a number of the treant guardians.','Quests/NorthFreeport/vivisection.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6230,'Submission through Suffering','City Tasks','North Freeport',26,1,'The Nektulos Dragoons have refused to submit to the authority of the Temple. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I convince these sentinels of their mistake by slaying the Teir\'Dal.',1440044,'The Teir\'Dal watchers have been more willing to serve the Dismal Rage now that I have slain a number of the forest sentinels.','Quests/NorthFreeport/submission_through_suffering.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6231,'The Word is Hate','City Tasks','North Freeport',27,1,'Gargantuan brutes have been razing the shrines constructed within Nektulos by Temple zealots. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I support the missionary work by slaughtering patchwork giants within the forest.',1440044,'The destruction of the shrines has slowed now that I have slaughtered a number of the giants.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_word_is_hate.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6232,'Blighted Sentries','City Tasks','North Freeport',28,1,'Temple neophytes have reported their magic ineffective against the undead that surround Nektropos Castle. Occultist Levonicus of the Dismal Rage has requested that I remove this obstacle by destroying the decaying creatures within Nektulos.',1440044,'The acolytes have found their excursions to Nektropos Castle safer now that I have destroyed a number of the wretched minions.','Quests/NorthFreeport/blighted_sentries.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6233,'Emptiness Is Loveliness','City Tasks','North Freeport',31,1,'Temple emissaries to the Enchanted Lands have reported as distasteful the sight of dikdik grazing upon lush meadows. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I fashion a setting more agreeable to the elders by killing the thicket fawns.',1440050,'The Temple ambassadors have praised the landscape of the Enchanted Lands now that I have killed a number of the dikdik.','Quests/NorthFreeport/emptiness_is_loveliness.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6234,'The Badgers','City Tasks','North Freeport',32,1,'Diggers attempting to discover ancient ruins beneath the Enchanted Lands have endured vicious attacks from the badgers whose burrows and tunnels are inadvertently disturbed. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I remove this threat to the laborers by slaying the thicket badgers.',1440050,'The assaults against the tomb robbers have slowed now that I have slain a number of the badgers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_badgers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6235,'Screech and Scratch Go to Freeport','City Tasks','North Freeport',33,1,'Temple sages have detected higher sentience within the giant bats of the Enchanted Lands. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I slaughter the shriekers as a precaution against the threat that they might present to Freeport.',1440050,'The potential danger posed by intelligent bats has been reduced now that I have slaughtered a number of the chaos shrillers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/screech_and_scratch_go_to_freeport.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6236,'Sanctioned Servitude','City Tasks','North Freeport',34,1,'Slave traders in pursuit of halflings have found the path to Rivervale blocked by ferocious kholrats. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I defend the trade routes by destroying brutish lashers within the Enchanted Lands.',1440050,'The supply to Freeport of halfling slaves has resumed now that I have destroyed a number of the savage kholrats.','Quests/NorthFreeport/sanctioned_servitude.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6237,'An Equal and Opposite Reaction','City Tasks','North Freeport',36,1,'Halfling thugs have been robbing Temple emissaries sent to collect tribute from the denizens of Rivervale. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I demonstrate the consequences of such transgressions by killing the bandits.',1440050,'Those who stole from the Dismal Rage have been punished now that I have killed a number of the tainted brigands.','Quests/NorthFreeport/an_equal_and_opposite_reaction.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6238,'Blood Cleansing','City Tasks','North Freeport',36,1,'Packs of rabid dogs have been attacking Temple acolytes and crusaders. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I prevent an epidemic of crazed, frothing zealots by slaying the plague hounds within Rivervale.',1440050,'The incidence of rabies infections has been reduced now that I have slain a number of the contaminated dogs.','Quests/NorthFreeport/blood_cleansing.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6239,'A Small Price to Pay','City Tasks','North Freeport',37,1,'In exchange for protection against the beasts of the forest, the Storm Shepherds have revealed the identities of Qeynosian agents within Freeport. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I uphold the agreement by slaughtering kholrat ravagers within Rivervale.',1440050,'The Temple has completed its transaction with the halflings now that I have slaughtered a number of kholrats.','Quests/NorthFreeport/a_small_price_to_pay.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6240,'Forests of Faith','City Tasks','North Freeport',38,1,'Temple laborers, commissioned to erect altars from Rivervale saplings, have suffered vicious ambushes from wood nymphs. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I advance the missionary work by destroying these nymph guardians.',1440050,'Construction of the shrines has continued now that I have destroyed a number of the forest nymphs.','Quests/NorthFreeport/forests_of_faith.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6241,'The Sharp Stick','City Tasks','North Freeport',39,1,'Discouraged by the unwillingness of the Overlord to annihilate the Rivervale denizens who have resisted the plague, the Temple is attempting to provoke the halflings to action against Freeport, thereby forcing a harsh response from the Citadel. Blight Sage Destroz of the Dismal Rage has requested that I engender chaos and hate by killing water nymphs.',1440050,'The city gates have been under siege from the denizens of Rivervale, prompting the Overlord to consider destroying all life within the forest, now that I have killed a number of the tainted nymphs.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_sharp_stick.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6242,'Frostfin Hunting','City Tasks','North Freeport',41,1,'Temple dignitaries, dispatched to negotiate the subjugation of the denizens of Everfrost, have been rebuffed by the deadly sharks surrounding Stormedge Isle. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I cull the waters of primal frostfin sharks in order to make the icy waters easier to traverse.',1440045,'The icy waters surrounding Stormedge Isle are a bit easier to traverse now that I have culled the number of primal frostfin sharks swimming about in Everfrost.','Quests/NorthFreeport/frostfin_hunting.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6243,'Eternal Horizon','City Tasks','North Freeport',43,1,'Acolytes commissioned by the Temple to investigate sightings of the gods have found their excursions into Everfrost interrupted by attacks from arctic lizards. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I clear a path by slaughtering the arctic monitor lizards in Everfrost.',1440045,'The representatives will find their travels through Everfrost less treacherous now that I have slaughtered a number of arctic monitor lizards.','Quests/NorthFreeport/eternal_horizon.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6244,'Random Violence','City Tasks','North Freeport',44,1,'Neophytes ordered by the Temple to explore the frozen waste lands have vanished, fallen to the beasts and shadows of the icy realm. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I avenge the slain by killing arctic behemoths and arctic wyrms in Everfrost.',1440045,'Justice has been exacted, and the terror of Freeport established, now that I have killed a number of arctic behemoths and arctic wyrms in Everfrost.','Quests/NorthFreeport/random_violence.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6245,'Separate the Righteous from the Wicked','City Tasks','North Freeport',45,1,'Temple seers have uncovered a series of attempts by Clan Sootfoot to summon to the scorched plains of Lavastorm an Avatar of Ro. As pitiful as theses attempts may be, Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I slaughter Sootfoot whelps as a deterrent against further attempts to open the astral gates.',1440045,'The goblins have abandoned their studies of dark arcana now that I have destroyed a number of the Sootfoot whelps.','Quests/NorthFreeport/separate_the_righteous_from_the_wicked.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6246,'Bad Case of Crabs','City Tasks','North Freeport',45,1,'Temple investigators sent to uncover the fate of the legendary sorceress Najena have encountered searing hot crustaceans within the waters around The Shrine of Thunder. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I assist the research by slaying the smoldering king crabs within Lavastorm.',1440045,'Explorers have found it easier to enter Lavastorm now that I have slain a number of the smoldering king crabs.','Quests/NorthFreeport/bad_case_of_crabs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6247,'Her Former Tooth','City Tasks','North Freeport',46,1,'Nal J\'Raen, an eminent Temple scholar, has betrayed the Overlord for the false promises of Qeynos. She seeks now to summon from all ends of the Shattered Lands an army of golems against Freeport. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I prevent an assault upon the city walls by killing Sootfoot harvesters gathering materials for her within Lavastorm.',1440045,'The supplies of the army of Nal J\'Raen have been thinned now that I have slaughtered Sootfoot harvesters.','Quests/NorthFreeport/her_former_tooth.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6248,'Nothing to Wash Out','City Tasks','North Freeport',45,1,'The Overlord has expressed alarm at reports of goblins tunneling in Lavastorm in search of a lost artifact. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I slaughter the rockpickers to ensure that the treasure remains buried and forgotten.',1440045,'The inhabitants of Lavastorm have slowed their excavations now that I have slaughtered a number of the Sootfoot rockpickers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/nothing_to_wash_out.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6249,'Breaking Frigid Bones','City Tasks','North Freeport',47,1,'The corpses of slain explorers to Everfrost have been dismembered by frigid skeletons, frightening off further treasure seekers by diminishing hopes of resurrecting the fallen. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I encourage unrestrained exploitation of the Shattered Lands by killing the icy shivers.',1440045,'The defiling of corpses has slowed now that I have killed a number of the icy shiver skeletons.','Quests/NorthFreeport/breaking_frigid_bones.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6250,'The Sootfoot Ritualists','City Tasks','North Freeport',48,1,'The goblins of Lavastorm have been using the magic of flame walkers for centuries and they refuse to share it with the city of Freeport. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I thin their source of magic by slaying these flame walkers.',1440045,'The goblins have been more amenable to sharing their knowledge of forgotten arcana now that I have slain a number of the flame walkers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_sootfoot_ritualists.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6251,'Paving The Way Through Flame','City Tasks','North Freeport',48,1,'The lizards of Lavastorm have thinned the number of explorers that we sent to document the recesses of Lavastorm. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I avenge this insult by thinning the number of flame walkers and magma worms in Lavastorm\'s Dagger Spires Pass.',1440045,'The lizards of Lavastorm are now more wary about attacking explorers as they venture around Dagger Spires Pass.','Quests/NorthFreeport/paving_the_way_through_flame.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6252,'The Inmost Recesses of the Catacombs','City Tasks','North Freeport',48,1,'Temple researchers attempting to locate the shrines to Solusek Ro buried deep below the cauldrons of Lavastorm have encountered fierce resistance from armored rumblers camouflaged amid the stones. Forbidden Lore of the Dismal Rage has requested that I clear a path by destroying the reinforced lashers within Solusek\'s Eye.',1440045,'Acolytes have found it easier to reach the depths of Solusek\'s Eye now that I have destroyed a number of the ancient rumblers.','Quests/NorthFreeport/the_inmost_recesses_of_the_catacombs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6253,'Hunting the Predators','City Tasks','South Freeport',11,1,'Packs of carrion hounds have been stalking poachers throughout the Commonlands, waiting until the hunters are burdened with their kills before attacking. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to reduce the threat to poachers by killing the hounds.',1660012,'The danger to the poachers has been lowered now that I have killed a number of the carrion hounds.','Quests/SouthFreeport/hunting_the_predators.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6254,'Enforcement','City Tasks','South Freeport',15,1,'Clans of poachers once loyal to Siren have declared their independence and refused to pay tribute. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to enforce discipline by slaughtering the rebellious hunters within the Commonlands.',1660012,'The uprising against Siren has been weakened now that I have slaughtered a number of the insurrectionists.','Quests/SouthFreeport/enforcement.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6255,'Feathers for Arrows','City Tasks','South Freeport',11,1,'Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to slay the young vulriches within the Commonlands for their feathers. The supply of arrow fletching has apparently been running low.',1660012,'All the vulriches that were needed for the arrows have been hunted and slain.','Quests/SouthFreeport/feathers_for_arrows.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6256,'Supplying the Scouts','City Tasks','South Freeport',12,1,'The supply of reptile skin leather has been running low. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to gather some of the raw hides needed by hunting monitor lizards in the Commonlands.',1660012,'I have given a good supply of reptile hides to Squab Kalina.','Quests/SouthFreeport/supplying_the_scouts.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6257,'Plundering the Ruins of the Dead','City Tasks','South Freeport',17,1,'Scouts returning from the ruins of Val\'Marr describe artifacts guarded by fallen crusaders. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for treasure hunters by killing the undead crusaders.',1660012,'Scouts returning from the ruins of Val\'Marr describe artifacts guarded by fallen crusaders. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for treasure hunters by killing the undead crusaders.','Quests/SouthFreeport/plundering_the_ruins_of_the_dead.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6258,'Logjam','City Tasks','South Freeport',21,1,'Beavers within Nektulos have been constructing dams that slow the addition of water to the sea, allowing algae and barnacles to flourish along the coast and impairing the docking of ships. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to ensure the rivers continue to fill the Nerius Flow by slaughtering beavers.',1660006,'The rivers leading into Nerius Flow should be unimpeded by dams now that I have slaughtered a number of beavers.','Quests/SouthFreeport/logjam.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6259,'The Chitinous Defenders','City Tasks','South Freeport',21,1,'Pirates attempting to land on the shores of Nektulos are being attacked and wounded by huge crabs. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear the way for plunderers by killing the crustaceans.',1660006,'The path is cleared for pirates seeking to pillage from Nektulos now that I have killed a number of the giant crabs.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_chitinous_defenders.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6260,'Defending the Cartographers','City Tasks','South Freeport',24,1,'Surveyors from Freeport have been finding the skeleton patrolmen a dangerous impediment to venturing forth into Nektulos. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to reduce the threat to the scouts by slaying the undead Dragoons.',1660006,'The scouts should find it easier to survey the forest now that I have slain a number of the skeleton guards.','Quests/SouthFreeport/defending_the_cartographers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6261,'Plundering the Tombs of Neriak','City Tasks','South Freeport',19,1,'Scouts returning from the recently unearthed city of Fallen Gate describe rooms filled with artifacts guarded by fierce dark elves. Squab Kalina of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for the treasure hunters by killing the interlopers.',1660006,'The path is cleared for treasure seekers to loot the tombs now that I have killed a number of the Thexians.','Quests/SouthFreeport/plundering_the_tombs_of_neriak.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6262,'Secrets of the Overlord','City Tasks','South Freeport',21,1,'Undead scouts have been stealthing out from the depths of Fallen Gate to uncover the weaknesses of Freeport. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the secrets of the city by destroying the tortured rangers.',1660006,'The secrets of Freeport are safe now that I have destroyed a number of the undead rangers.','Quests/SouthFreeport/secrets_of_the_overlord.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6263,'The Grim Diggers','City Tasks','South Freeport',21,1,'Reports indicate that the undead of Fallen Gate are attempting to tunnel through to Freeport. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to slay the blighted attackers before they are able to reach the city sewers.',1660006,'The subterranean threat to Freeport has been slowed now that I have slain a number of the undead invaders.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_grim_diggers.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6264,'The Sea Serpents','City Tasks','South Freeport',26,1,'Poisonous eels have been breeding within the sewers and then slipping out into the bay to lunge from the water at deckhands and dockworkers. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to remove this danger by destroying the eels within Edgewater Drains.',1660006,'The sailors and longshoremen should find safer their labor now that I have destroyed a number of the pestilent eels.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_sea_serpents.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6265,'Turtle Eggs','City Tasks','South Freeport',26,1,'Rogues attempting to scavenge the eggs of aquatic creatures within Edgewater Drains have encountered fierce resistance from giant turtles. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for the harvesters by killing the turtles.',1660006,'The gathering of eggs has been made easier now that I have killed a number of the rockshell turtles.','Quests/SouthFreeport/turtle_eggs.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6266,'Plumbing the Depths','City Tasks','South Freeport',27,1,'The pipes emptying into Edgewater Drains have been obstructed with rocks gathered and piled by giant crabs. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to slaughter the crabs before the clogged pipes explode, spilling their filth out onto the city streets.',1660006,'The flow into the sewers has increased now that I have slaughtered a number of the muckwater crabs.','Quests/SouthFreeport/plumbing_the_depths.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6267,'Dismemberment','City Tasks','South Freeport',29,1,'Shivers of sharks have been butchering refugees who fall down into the sewers. Boatswain Fomas of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the adventurers by slaying sharks within Edgewater Drains.',1660006,'The threat to wandering refugees has been reduced now that I have slain a number of the savage sharks.','Quests/SouthFreeport/dismemberment.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6268,'Seaside Expansion','City Tasks','South Freeport',31,1,'Carpenters attempting to construct a new wharf along the coast of the Enchanted Lands have been attacked by enraged fairies. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to end these disturbances by destroying the fog fairies.',1660013,'The construction of the port has continued without interruption now that I have destroyed a number of the fairy guardians.','Quests/SouthFreeport/seaside_expansion.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6269,'Aquatic Quarantine','City Tasks','South Freeport',32,1,'Disease and rot have been spreading from the Enchanted Lands to throughout the fish population, threatening to decimate the supply of seafood to Freeport. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to halt this contagion by killing the trout that are its source.',1660013,'The plague has been contained now that I have killed a number of infected trout.','Quests/SouthFreeport/aquatic_quarantine.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6270,'The Snapping Turtles','City Tasks','South Freeport',33,1,'Merchants digging for turtle eggs along the beaches of the Enchanted Lands have encountered ferocious resistance from sea creatures. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to remove this threat by slaughtering the giant turtles.',1660013,'The merchants have been able to harvest buried eggs now that I have slaughtered a number of the sea turtles.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_snapping_turtles.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6271,'Hazardous Waters','City Tasks','South Freeport',34,1,'Aquatic goblins have been sinking ships that drop anchor along the shores of the Enchanted Lands. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the fleet by slaying goblin plunderers.',1660013,'The boats from Freeport have found it safer to dock now that I have slain a number of fog goblins.','Quests/SouthFreeport/hazardous_waters.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6272,'Enfeebler','City Tasks','South Freeport',36,1,'Raiders attempting to infiltrate Runnyeye have encountered fierce resistance from the entrance guards within the Enchanted Lands. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to thin the defenses by killing Runnyeye menders.',1660013,'The mercenaries have reported as more successful their assaults against Runnyeye now that I have killed a number of the goblin protectors.','Quests/SouthFreeport/enfeebler.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6273,'The Stronger Shell','City Tasks','South Freeport',36,1,'Ships traveling along the coast of the Enchanted Lands have been colliding with giant turtles, ripping holes in the hulls of the vessels. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the boats by destroying the hulking snappers.',1660013,'The ships have suffered fewer collisions now that I have destroyed a number of the sea turtles.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_stronger_shell.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6274,'Grip of the Sirens','City Tasks','South Freeport',37,1,'Beautiful lamiae have been devouring the life from those seamen who fall into the hands of the seductresses. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the pirates by slaying lamiae within the Enchanted Lands.',1660013,'Sailors are able to resist the deadly allure of the lamiae now that I have slain a number of the enchantresses.','Quests/SouthFreeport/grip_of_the_sirens.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6275,'The Eye of Rulgax','City Tasks','South Freeport',37,1,'Freeport brigands attempting to stealth around the Enchanted Lands have encountered evil eyes adept at detecting and unmasking the pillagers. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to reduce this danger by slaughtering the evil eye seers.',1660013,'Plunderers have been able to successfully sneak about now that I have slaughtered a number of the evil eyes.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_eye_of_rulgax.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6276,'Obstructed Aortae','City Tasks','South Freeport',38,1,'Tainted nymphs have been warping the Enchanted Lands to reroute, siphon, and block the tributaries that flow into the surrounding ocean. Marauder Kindolus of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to ensure that the rivers remain navigable by destroying the nymphs.',1660013,'The waterways have resumed their original course now that I have destroyed a number of the corrupted nymphs.','Quests/SouthFreeport/obstructed_aortae.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6277,'Bite Out of Crime','City Tasks','South Freeport',41,1,'Merchants attempting to transport the artifacts recovered from the frozen sepulchers of Everfrost have found their ships attacked by the giant sharks that surround Stormedge Isle. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to protect the traders by killing primal frostfin sharks.',1660005,'The supply to Freeport of ancient treasures has stabilized now that I have killed a number of the primal frostfin sharks swimming within the waters that surround Stormedge Isle.','Quests/SouthFreeport/bite_out_of_crime.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6278,'Pups on the Rise','City Tasks','South Freeport',42,1,'Freeport miners believe that there are reservoirs of minerals and gems that cut deep through the ice covered cliffs of Everfrost, but they are constantly attacked by ice wolves. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to cull the increasing numbers of ice wolfs by hunting their young pups.',1660005,'Freeport miners will be able to lay claim to the large veins of minerals and gems hidden within the ice covered cliffs of Everfrost now that I have slaughtered a number of ice wolf pups.','Quests/SouthFreeport/pups_on_the_rise.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6279,'Troubles Melt','City Tasks','South Freeport',43,1,'Adventurers commissioned by the Citadel to assess the entirety of Everfrost have reported fierce opposition from the Frosthorn minotaurs. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for the explorers by slaying the frigid beasts.',1660005,'Surveyors have found it easier to continue their documentation now that I have slain a number of the Frosthorn minotaurs.','Quests/SouthFreeport/troubles_melt.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6280,'To Sulphurous and Tormenting Flames','City Tasks','South Freeport',45,1,'Koba Monimaja was a famed lieutenant within the Citadel before betraying the Overlord and fleeing Freeport. Now he seeks to recruit an army against his old master. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to tarnish the legend of this traitor by destroying his Sootfoot mercenaries within Lavastorm.',1660005,'The threat to Freeport from Koba Monimaja has been lessened now that I have destroyed a number of his goblin underlings.','Quests/SouthFreeport/to_sulphurous_and_tormenting_flames.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6281,'Wormling Defenses','City Tasks','South Freeport',45,1,'Explorers attempting to scour the depths of Lavastorm have suffered scorching burns from the magma wormlings that surround the entrance within Magma Grotto. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to remove this threat to the treasure hunters by killing the scalding lizards.',1660005,'The plunderers have found it safer to enter the volcanoes and fiery gorges of Lavastorm now that I have killed a number of the magma wormlings.','Quests/SouthFreeport/wormling_defenses.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6282,'Nosy Neighbors','City Tasks','South Freeport',45,1,'Boats sailing from Freeport have been sunk on the shores of Everfrost. The Bitterwind explorers that reside along the beaches must have done this. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to strike fear into the hearts of the Bitterwind explorers by slaughtering a few of their men.',1660005,'The boats may now once again supply our forces around Everfrost as the Bitterwind explorers have been successfully quelled.','Quests/SouthFreeport/nosy_neighbors.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6283,'Perils of the Sea','City Tasks','South Freeport',45,1,'Scouts have reported higher than normal activity in the shark population on the coasts of Everfrost. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to thin their numbers by slaughtering the sharks within the waters of Everfrost.',1660005,'The sharks of Everfrost numbers have thinned now that I\'ve slaughtered a fair number of them.','Quests/SouthFreeport/perils_of_the_sea.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6284,'The Hermits','City Tasks','South Freeport',48,1,'Entrepreneurs attempting to collect herbs for sale within the markets of Freeport have suffered brutal attacks from giants within Everfrost. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to assist the harvesters by slaughtering the Kromise hermits.',1660005,'The collectors have been able to safely plunder the herbs now that I have slaughtered a number of the Kromise hermits.','Quests/SouthFreeport/the_hermits.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6285,'Hiding Won\'t Save You','City Tasks','South Freeport',46,1,'Looters commissioned by Freeport to retrieve the riches buried within the valleys of Everfrost but they keep getting eaten by giant lizards. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path for the treasure hunters by destroying ice walkers.',1660005,'The plunderers have found it easier to access the valleys of Everfrost now that I have destroyed a number of the ice walkers.','Quests/SouthFreeport/hiding_wont_save_you.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6286,'Looking For a Good Meal','City Tasks','South Freeport',47,1,'Sailors stationed around Everfrost are running low on supplies, wooly mammoth calfs provide some excellent meals for them. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to butcher some wooly mammoth calfs for the sailors.',1660005,'The sailors stationed around Everfrost should be well fed for a while, now that I have killed a number of wooly mammoth calfs.','Quests/SouthFreeport/looking_for_a_good_meal.lua',0,1,0,0,0),
(6287,'No Alternative Paths','City Tasks','South Freeport',48,1,'Adventurers commissioned by the Citadel to lay siege to the legions of Thyr have encountered resistance from animated golems patrolling the lava bridges that lead down to the subterranean temples. Corsair G`kex of the Seafury Buccaneers has solicited me to clear a path by slaying stone giants within Solusek\'s Eye.',1660005,'The attacks against the fire giants have resumed now that I have slain a number of the cinder golems.','Quests/SouthFreeport/no_alternative_paths.lua',0,1,0,0,0);
